(3, 1, 'Villa Kanti', 'villa-kanti', 4, 1, '<p>Far from the energetic activity of daily Balinese life, <strong>Villa Kanti</strong> is casually elegant situated on the border of a small, undisturbed Balinese village. It is located near Mas Village; as well as Sukawati the art market and Celuk Village, where you can find stuffs of gold and silver.</p><p>All corners of the villa are decorated with a plethora of antiques, crafts and artifacts from the around Indonesian islands as Bali, Java, Borneo, Moluccas. These decorative and contemplative pieces enrich the discreetly cultural yet meditative atmosphere of the house.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>KANTI</strong> is the ''Sanskrit'' word for "light" and the residence is bathed in natural light while protecting the privacy of our residents - it is both magical and unforgettable.</p><p>From that first moment of entry into&nbsp;Villa Kanti, you will be welcomed by the sound of water rippling down the cascades to the bottom of the plantation. Tropical flowers, shrubs and trees are swept in by the refreshing breeze where you will find a virtual celebration of nature and life.</p><p>Villa Kanti&nbsp;has been built in perfect harmony with traditional Balinese culture. Designed by Gede Agus, a young Balinese architect, Villa Kanti is a perfect blend of the contemporary concept of indoor/outdoor living combined with every possible amenity amid a stunning landscape designed by famous local landscaper, Ketut Hendrawan. All this blends seamlessly into the surrounding environment of rice fields and coconut palms.</p><p>Villa Kanti consists of five spacious bedroom suites located in three pavilions which sleep a total of ten guests in perfect comfort (the Master Pavilion, the Temple Pavilion and the Rice field Pavilion) which sleep a total of ten guests in perfect comfort. The main pavilion is the Living and Dining Pavilion, connected to the kitchen on the side of the property by a soaring "alang alang" (thatched) roof. The master pavilion, this is a two-storey pavilion located at the top-end of the property and contains a bedroom suite on each floor, identical in size. The temple pavilion, comprised of two different bedroom types (queen bed at ground floor and twin bed upper floor) is very ideal for a family. The rice field pavilion, a one bedroom pavilion built with tropical wood, Merbau and decorated with precious artifacts from the islands of Indonesia. The living and dining pavilion, this pavilion includes dining area, living area which has open view to the terraced rice fields and also open to the swimming pool, fish pond with water cascades above the pond.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Serving daily breakfast American or Continental for 2 pax.</li>	<li>Complimentary laundry (exclude dry clean).</li>	<li>Daily cleaning.</li>	<li>Free shuttle service to/from Ubud area.</li>	<li>The cooks will prepare lunch and dinner upon guests request according to set of menus.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools:&nbsp;20 x 4 meter lap swimming pool and the children pool.</li>	<li>Living areas: 5 luxurious spacious bedrooms, separate into 3 pavilions (The Master, The Temple and The Rice Field); open-air living and dining pavilion connected to the kitchen.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;a spectacularly large screen 67 inch satellite TV, home theatre with an extensive DVD collection of international movies and music;&nbsp;a large selection of books, guide books, art books</li>	<li>Communications: PC with high-speed Wi Fi internet and a printer.</li>	<li>Other facilities: A small and tranquil pavilion for&nbsp;relaxation (hot Jacuzzi and Hammam an oriental steam room);&nbsp;private garden&nbsp;is&nbsp;decorated with a plethora of antiques and crafts from Bali and the around Indonesian islands;&nbsp;terrace with panoramic views to a verdant rice fields, ponds, tropical garden and river.</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>The Master Pavilion&nbsp;</strong></p><p>This two-storey pavilion located at the top-end of the property contains one bedroom with en-suite bathroom on each floor identical in size.</p><p>The spacious ground floor bedroom decorated with antiques and crafts from Bali, Java, Sumatra and other islands, features a King-size bed canopied with a mosquito net, a long writing table and a sofa facing to a private garden. It is individually controlled air conditioning. The outdoor en-suite bathroom with a soaking bathtub, huge rain-head shower, is nestled in a tropical garden in complete privacy.&nbsp;</p><p>The upper floor bedroom has been specially designed to enjoy the breathtaking panoramic view of the surrounding natural environment. Sliding louvered glass windows all over the bedroom allows refreshing breeze to circulate through the room and a ceiling fan above a king-size bed is keeping the room pleasantly fresh. The en-suite bathroom with louvered glass windows also provides a panoramic rice field view from a soaking terrazzo tub and a separate huge rain-head shower.</p><p><strong>The Temple Pavillion</strong></p><p>This is a two-storey pavilion ideal for a family of four. Both bedrooms are air-conditioned with spacious terrace where a beautiful nature lies on the surrounding pavilion.</p><p>The ground floor bedroom features a king-size bed canopied with a mosquito net, it has a tranquil and peaceful view to the Villa Temple, rice fields and shooting feeling from the sound of the small river below. The spacious outdoor en-suite bathroom with soaking bathtub, huge rain-head shower and tropical garden allows complete privacy in the open area.</p><p>The upper bedroom decorated with Asian artifacts features twin bed. The clear glass window above the head beds overlooks the rice fields and coconut trees behind the villa. The en-suite bathroom has the same overwhelming rice field view and the wooden shutters on the glass window will ensure guests privacy whilst in the bathroom.</p><p><strong>The Rice Field Pavilion</strong></p><p>This one bedroom pavilion has been built with tropical Merbau wood and decorated with precious artifacts from the islands of Indonesia. The bedroom with individually controlled air conditioning features a super King-size bed canopied with a mosquito net overlooks a private garden and rice fields.</p><p>In the open en-suite bathroom, a stunning wall depicting a temple ceremony has been carved in front of a long black terrazzo vanity counter and soaking bathtub. To complete this delightful tropical experience, a huge rain-head shower is located under the shade of trees, yet in total privacy.</p><p><strong>Living and Dining</strong></p><p>This pavilion of 120 square meters includes living, dining and entertainment areas. It offers an open view to the terraced rice fields, swimming pools, fishponds and water cascades.</p><p>Connected to the pavilion is a fully equipped kitchen, staffed with Balinese chefs who are able to prepare both European and Balinese cuisine and ensure guests dining requirements.</p><p>On the mezzanine above the Living Pavilion, PC with high-speed WiFi internet and a printer, a large selection of books, guide books, art books are available at guest’s convenience.</p><p>Media and entertainment room is located few steps down from the living area and next to it there is a bathroom designed with a&nbsp;<i>‘Zen garden’</i>.</p>', '<p>Ten staff will assist and offer the highest level of personal service while providing absolute discretion and privacy. Each of them will be at your service to ensure your stay is one of total relaxation and comfort.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include Airport transfer roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates subject to 15.5&nbsp;% Tax and Service charge.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 11:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;<strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.26769920', '-8.57217900', 10, 5, 5, 10, NULL, 2, '2016-09-03 12:20:11', '2016-10-04 18:45:06', NULL),
(4, 1, 'Villa Alamanda', 'villa-alamanda', 4, 0, '<p>Villa Alamanda is a special place. After four years searching for the perfect location to create their dream holiday home, the owners decided on the lush jungle setting near Ubud, and their affection for this tropical paradise is evident as soon as you open the villa doors.</p><p>Carefully designed to harmonise with the environment, the villa combines traditional architecture and materials to create an enchanting tropical oasis. Fully staffed, including a fabulous in-house chef, guests need only focus on lazing by the pool, indulging in scrumptious home-cooked meals, being pampered with deluxe spa treatments, or simply admiring the views.</p><p>This four-bedroom villa epitomises peace and tranquillity and is the perfect retreat for those seeking a quiet and relaxing holiday within easy reach of Bali’s exotic cultural centre.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Alamanda&nbsp;</strong>situated ten minutes east of the cultural town of Ubud, is approached through the traditional Balinese woodcarvers'' village of Tengkulak. Perched high on a ridge above the Petanu River, with valley views, the graceful architecture of this thatched hideaway blends contemporary elegance with ethnic charm. Designed to harmonise with the environment and utilising local materials, this exclusive villa comfortably sleeps up to eight people in four stylish and spacious air-conditioned bedrooms, each with an en-suite bathroom.&nbsp;Elegant teak furniture is complemented by clean lines, natural colours and local artwork. A sizeable, open-air lounge and dining terrace overhangs the jungle, creating a real feeling of space. Villa Alamanda presents tropical living at its best.</p><p>The villa is built on the side of a hill; the living area and bedrooms are all on the same level with steps leading down into the garden. A large gate opens onto a paved parking area, where indigenous ''serai'' stone walls portray a jigsaw of shapes. Timeworn statues of comical characters greet the guests as they step into the cool interior of the villa through a set of antique double doors. Inside, the hallway extends towards a T-shaped wooden terrace. Furnished with antiques, this breezy open-air living area runs the length of the house and boasts a delightful dining section that just out over the tranquil gardens as they tumble into the steep ravine.</p><p>The garden and pool area provide the perfect spot for relaxation. The garden is equipped with a large bale with plenty of space to stretch out and enjoy the afternoons in luxurious style. The garden area is large enough for children play or for you to entertain friends.</p><p>Villa Alamanda is&nbsp;an hour and fifteen minutes'' drive from Ngurah Rai international airport, Ubud is Bali''s centre for fine arts, dance and music; while the surrounding villages are home to Bali''s most accomplished painters, dancers, musicians and carvers. This remarkable town is encompassed by magnificent terraced rice fields, rivers, traditional villages, art and craft communities, ancient temples and palaces. It is located 300 metres above sea level in the foothills of the central mountain range; this gives it a fresher, more pleasant climate than the southern coastal regions.<br />The numerous art galleries in Ubud feature traditional and modern work; the museums showcase the island''s rich history, and the shops and the market stalls sell handicrafts, jewellery, woodcarvings, textiles, paintings and antiques. There are many, well-presented, cultural performances staged in the town, in particular the Hindu epic, the Ramayana; also the Kecak dance, the fire dance, the monkey dance and the Legong dance. The countryside around Ubud is particularly beautiful, with an abundance of trails offering memorable walks through the peaceful rice fields.&nbsp;The location is convenient for tours all over the island and is only a forty-minute drive from the coast.</p><p>Villa Alamanda is an ideal choice for those looking for modern luxury in peaceful surroundings; an enchanting retreat where guests can enjoy a relaxing experience with personalised service.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary&nbsp;Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Welcome drink and cool towel upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily assisting from Butler.</li>	<li>Night time security</li>	<li>Chef prepares dishes&nbsp;Western, Asian, vegetarian cuisines, including children’s menu (be able to&nbsp;requests&nbsp;special diets), and also&nbsp;Indonesian cooking classes learning (extra cost).</li>	<li>Organizing&nbsp;renting cars and providing drivers for guests&nbsp;(seating up to seven passengers) for eight hours a day at a cost of USD$25++/day (excluding petrol).&nbsp;</li>	<li>Laundry services (extra charge).</li>	<li>In-house service Spa treatment, and babysitting (surcharge).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: Private swimming pool size 13m x 9m</li>	<li>Living areas: Open-sided living and dining terrace; air-conditioned media room; poolside&nbsp;balé;&nbsp;4 fully air-conditioned bedrooms;&nbsp;4 en-suite bathrooms.</li>	<li>Communications:&nbsp;Wireless internet connection;&nbsp;Telephone (land line) with IDD and local call service</li>	<li>Entertainments: Satellite TV and DVD player;&nbsp;Stereo system with CD player;&nbsp;Book library.</li>	<li>Families: Baby Cot;&nbsp;Baby High Chair;&nbsp;Children''s books, games and toys;&nbsp;Childrens videos and DVDs</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;Computer with Broadband internet connection;&nbsp;Safety box in all bedrooms;&nbsp;4 hair dryer (s);&nbsp;4 pool deck chairs / Sun loungers</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Description</strong></p><p>Villa Alamanda - Accommodations</p><p>Each of the four bedrooms features red-hued hardwood floors, double sliding glass and louvre doors that open onto the terrace, en-suite bathrooms, fitted wardrobes and safety deposit boxes.</p><p>The ''Master Bedroom'' is furnished in a contemporary style, enhanced by a bell jar ceiling lantern, Indonesian artefacts and paintings by local artists. Louvre doors lead into a dressing room, fitted with a chunky marble washbasin and teak cabinets and adjacent to the bathroom, with its marble bathtub and shower. The glassless windows in the bathroom allow the cool breezes to permeate, and provide lovely views of the main garden area and swimming pool bordering the river valley.</p><p>The ''Red Room'' is characterised by red accessories such as the lamps and paintings; and the ‘Cinnamon Room'' by the spicy-scented cinnamon stick arrangement in the vase above the bed. Both of these bedrooms feature a private garden bathroom with a marble bathtub surrounded by walls and leafy shrubs.</p><p>A separate thatched pavilion houses the ''Garden Suite'', a cosy bedroom that also doubles as air-conditioned lounge containing shelves of DVDs and books. The Garden Suite features an en-suite garden bathroom with a canopied bathtub.</p><p>A fully-equipped kitchen is behind the Garden Suite and is accessible from the car-parking area. There is so much attention to detail; even the water tower is decorated with fanciful carved flowers, dragonflies and birds.</p><p>An arched gateway with rustic Balinese doors marks the entrance to the beautiful garden, accessed by a dramatic flight of seventeen stone steps leading down from the car-park level. The garden is shaded by verdant jungle foliage and filled with an abundance of brightly coloured, sweet-scented tropical flowers and plants. A gnarled frangipani tree overhangs the enticing swimming pool; the water appears to cascade over the curved infinity edge into the backdrop of banana plants, bamboo, and towering coconut palms. A large relaxation gazebo, known as a ''Bale Bengong'', is situated next to the pool and offers the comfort of cushioned daybeds. Sunloungers are positioned on the white Palimanan stone patio; hand-carved paras stone statues and garden lamps create a romantic ambience. The constant sound of the fast flowing Petanu River, as it carves its way through the steep gorge below, is accompanied by the melody of birdsong and cicadas.</p>', '<ul>	<li><strong>Villa manager</strong>&nbsp;is responsible for the overall operation of the villa. His role is to oversee and coordinate the staff and property and to assist guests during their stay.</li>	<li><strong>Chef</strong>&nbsp;will happily prepare anything from the Western, Asian, vegetarian and children’s suggestion menus. Local dishes are the chef’s specialties</li>	<li><strong>Butler </strong>is&nbsp;on hand daily to assist you with whatever you should need.</li>	<li><strong>Housekeepers&nbsp;</strong>attend to daily housekeeping and domestic duties and a lady from the local village also performs daily offerings throughout the villa in keeping with Balinese Hindu tradition.</li>	<li><strong>Gardener&nbsp;</strong>ensures the villa gardens are maintained on a daily basis.</li>	<li><strong>Pool Attendant</strong>&nbsp;is serviced daily by a pool attendant.</li>	<li><strong>Driver</strong>&nbsp;is on standby for up to eight hours per day.</li>	<li><strong>Security guards</strong>&nbsp;guard provides night-time security.</li></ul><dl></dl>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include Airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>F &amp; B system : grocery bills + 20%</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and <strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Late check-out subject to availability.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.28595200', '-8.52805780', 8, 4, 3, 10, NULL, 6, '2016-09-05 05:27:26', '2016-09-26 17:59:36', NULL),
(5, 1, 'Villa Bukit Naga', 'villa-bukit-naga', 4, 0, '<p><b>Villa Bukit Naga</b> is a dream home - a luxurious, contemporary dwelling that marries majestically Balinese form and function. Nestled amid two acres of brightly colored local flora, shady palms and frangipani trees, the complex features five buildings tailored to provide exceptional accommodations.</p><p>The interiors of each building have been fashioned carefully by local craftsmen using Balinese hardwoods, marble, and stone, and are furnished throughout with Chinese and Indonesian antiques, giving the property a distinct character and charm. No expense has been spared to offer guests every conceivable comfort and convenience, whilst ensuring that peace and privacy prevail.</p>', '<p>Villa Bukit Naga is situated on the outskirts of Banjar Selat - a quiet, traditional Balinese village approximately twenty minutes east of Ubud, the cultural and artistic capital of Bali. The estate overlooks a lush tropical valley in which the Sang Sang and Ayuverda rivers converge. It has views to the west of the slopes of three of Bali''s majestic volcanoes, and away to the East one can catch glimpses of the holy Mount Agung.</p><p>Bukit Naga is a perfect base from which to explore the many facets of this fabulous island. Expert guidance is always at hand to offer advice on all aspects of your holiday, from shopping and sightseeing to spiritualism and serenity. Ubud boasts many fine restaurants (amongst these ''Mozaic'' must rate as one of the finest eating establishments in the southern hemisphere) and also offers fantastic shopping, where jewellery, ceramics, paintings, traditional fabrics, and antique and reproduction Indonesian artifacts can be purchased at very reasonable prices.</p><p>To the East, the resort of Candi Dasa is a forty five-minute drive. An hour to the west lie the more popular sands of Legian or Canggu Beach and some very fine beachfront restaurants. For those wishing to explore further inland, the villa is ideally placed for trips to Kintamani and Lake Batur. Additionally the Bali Bird and Reptile Park is a thirty-minute drive away. White water rafting and an Elephant safari are also within easy reach of the villa.</p><p>Villa Bukit Naga sleeps a total of twelve guests in six spacious suites. There is a one-bedroom guest villa, a huge two-bedroom guesthouse, and the three-bedroom main house. All suites are fully air-conditioned and feature private dressing rooms and large marble bathrooms. Imposing hand-made two-meter square Balinese beds, luxurious cotton sheets, and fine denier mosquito nets ensure an excellent nights sleep. All bedrooms and bathrooms have telephone lines for IDD calls and in house calls.</p><p>In addition, Villa Bukit Naga is ideal for weddings, family gathering and friends reunion, business meeting when a quite exclusive retreat is required to meet the occassion.</p>', '<p><strong>Services&nbsp;</strong></p><ul>	<li>Airport transfer: pick up and drop off.</li>	<li>Chef prepares global or specialised cuisines&nbsp;Western dishes to local Asian delights.</li>	<li>Villa Manager will arrange shopping trips, art gallery and museum tours, and much more.</li>	<li>Private transport can be arranged to&nbsp;take enjoying tour (volcano hiking, surfing trips or relaxing on the sand as well as golfing, cycling or touring)</li>	<li>Cooking classes, yoga lessons, massages and other spa treatments can be arranged in the privacy (surcharge)</li>	<li>Villa Bukit Naga’s manager can help with all aspects of your planning&nbsp;for weddings, family gathering, friends reunion and business meeting.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: Infinity swimming pools, and&nbsp;Jacuzzi in private garden.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;Satellite TV,&nbsp;600+ DVD titles,&nbsp;iPod docks.</li>	<li>Communication: WiFi</li>	<li>Living areas: 7 bedrooms total with&nbsp;6 en suite bathrooms,&nbsp;4 private outdoor showers, fully air-conditioned.</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;Gym.</li></ul>', '<pre style="margin-left:46.2pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--></pre><ul>	<li>Villa Manager</li>	<li>Cook</li>	<li>Waiter</li>	<li>Housemaid</li>	<li>Security Guard</li>	<li>Gardener</li>	<li>Pool Attendant</li></ul><pre style="margin-left:46.2pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></pre>', '<ul>	<li>The above rates including airport transfers rountrip, tax and services.</li>	<li>A security deposit of $500 is required and will be returned within seven days of departure.</li>	<li>Food &amp; beverage not included but billed at cost from local market and prepared for an additional fee. Staff will stock the house with food &amp; drinks. Market list needed prior to arrival.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 11:00 AM</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.32507070', '-8.53716160', 13, 7, 3, 15, NULL, 6, '2016-09-07 10:56:19', '2016-09-23 11:08:16', NULL),
(6, 1, 'Villa Vajra', 'villa-vajra', 4, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Vajra</strong> is a luxury villa&nbsp;standing just 50 meters apart in the village of Sebali which is only a ten minute drive from the cultural hub of Ubud. Villa Vajra is perched dramatically on the edge of a deep river gorge, resourcefully integrated into the natural contours of the hill. A beautiful stroll garden has been created for our guests in our extensive grounds.&nbsp;</p><p>The&nbsp;romantic hideaway&nbsp;is&nbsp;classic&nbsp;of contemporary Balinese architecture with thatched roofs while open to the drama of their surrounding landscapes. Villa Vajra can comfortably accommodate 8 people. Each villa boasts its own private pool.</p>', '<p>Deep in the heart of Bali, perched on a venerated spur of land at the confluence of two rivers, is the stunning hideaway known as <strong>Villa Vajra</strong>. Designed by the internationally acclaimed architect, Guy Morgan, this modern, spacious villa sleeps up to seven guests and offers the ultimate in luxurious accommodation within a totally private and exclusive, close-to-nature setting.</p><p>The property and gardens are landscaped into the slopes of the steep valley, and the approach, via a raised wooden walkway through undisturbed rice fields, gives no clue to the remarkable design of the villa, or the breathtaking views of the jungle and river gorge.</p><p>Constructed with high quality local materials including ''alang alang'' thatch, Palimanan stone and teak wood; the property combines the very best of Balinese architectural elements with contemporary flair, elegant finishes and modern amenities. The villa presents a blend of outdoor living and air-conditioned comfort.</p><p>Villa Vajra is named after the quintessential symbol of Vajrayana Buddhism, a five-pronged ritual object often employed in conjunction with a bell. The Vajra is represented by a carving in a freestanding stone at the main entrance.</p><p>Every room and corner of the property has the effect of producing gasps of surprise and delight as guests view it for the first time. The villa is comprised of two buildings, linked on the upper level by a lotus pond and pergola. A serene Buddha statue stands within the lotus pond and white thunbergia cascades over the pergola-covered walkway leading to the Master Bedroom and Studio. The Master Bedroom is characterized by elegant furniture, teak floors, and glass on three sides to maximize the awesome views of the jungle and river valley. Sliding glass doors open on to a timber balcony, fringed by a food forest of fruit trees; the built-in bench seat is an ideal place to absorb the natural surroundings and listen to the ceaseless gurgle of the Ooz River as it coils its way through the deep gorge below. The en-suite garden bathroom is dominated by a large black terrazzo bathtub, creating a strong contrast against the white Palimanan stone floor. A black terrazzo wash stand supports a stylish chrome washbowl, and the shower is flanked by shelves and cabinets. Everything possible has been considered for the comfort of the guests; the luxurious open-air bathtub is sheltered by a thatched canopy, and privacy is maintained by a wall. Wooden shutters, like hatches within the wall, can be opened to reveal a view of the rice fields, and a larger hatch beside the bathtub offers the delightful alternative vista of the jungle. Tree ferns, birds'' nest ferns, and stepping stones across a star-grass lawn complete the natural decor of this charming garden bathroom.</p><p>Colourful local artwork adorns the walls of a passage way leading to the Studio on the same floor. Situated on the western side of the villa, this room boasts a panoramic view of the rice fields, and features a pitched roof, a cream terrazzo floor and more built-in cupboards and storage space. The Studio doubles as an additional bedroom and includes an en-suite toilet and shower room with a marble floor and black terrazzo washstand.</p><p>The adjacent building, across the lotus pond, holds the Study, with a flat screen satellite TV, DVD player and a quality sound system for the entertainment of the guests. This room also doubles as an additional bedroom with an en-suite shower room and a stone terrace that appears to almost float within the gently swaying fields of rice. Cushioned seating is built into the low wall encircling the terrace, thereby creating a comfortable place for relaxing with a book while enjoying a coffee or a cocktail at sunset. A cathedral window in the Study room overlooks the main living and dining area on the lower level, which is accessed by an external cantilevered staircase.</p><p>It is upon reaching this lower level that visitors will be able to fully appreciate the unique design of the villa. The gargantuan, 12 x 8 metre, living and dining pavilion extends the full height of the building and features a marble floor underneath a vaulted roof supported by coconut-wood pillars on stone plinths. Furnished with rattan chairs and sofas, pendulous steel globe lanterns and Buddhist welcome statues, this pavilion represents open living at its very best, and is a fantastic venue for parties, receptions and functions. A small aviary is situated to one side, and a large hatch links the dining area with the fully equipped kitchen, where the cook will prepare a range of delicious Indonesian and Western meals. Next door is a toilet and a shower, and the laundry and staff quarters are situated at the back. The adjoining semi-circular timber deck overhangs the lush river valley and provides an alternative romantic dining area. Living jackfruit trees grow through holes that have been cut in the floor of the deck, creating a solution that blends style with nature without threatening the environment. A further example of environmental conservation is the water recycling system that has been devised for the 8 x 3 metre infinity edge swimming pool, the outdoor Jacuzzi, and the graceful cascade flowing down from the lotus pond above. Another Buddha statue rests within an alcove behind the cascade.</p><p>The Guest Room is situated at pool level, within the building that houses the Master Bedroom and Studio. Furnished with a dreamy four-poster bed, the Guest Room features a Palimanan stone floor, windows with sliding doors facing the valley, a dressing room, and a garden bathroom with a black terrazzo tub, shower and toilet.<br />Rustic stone steps lead down from the swimming pool to the lowest level, past an outdoor shower, a bed of beautiful white peace lilies, and a small lotus pond contained within a stone pot. At this level there is an open terrace overlooking a grassy meadow within the valley. Another wooden deck juts out to one side and a narrow path leads down to the river past a small temple and a coconut grove. On one side is a secret sanctuary, a traditional open pavilion, known as a ''bale'', with a thatched roof and a raised teak floor scattered with cushions for relaxing. Even here, guests can enjoy music from the sound system, which boasts eight speakers directed towards every corner of the property. On the other side, a fully equipped gym provides the facility to maintain a daily fitness routine while appreciating the wonderful views.</p><p>The Master Bedroom, Guest Room, Studio and Study each feature individually controlled air-conditioning units and powerful ceiling fans to keep the rooms pleasantly cool. There are telephone lines for IDD calls and in-house calls in each room, and also safety deposit boxes. At night the villa takes on a different persona, with cleverly concealed lighting. Guests will appreciate the fresh cool air, and will be serenaded by a chorus of frog song to the accompaniment of ritual music from the village temples and the constant murmur of the river.</p><p>There is a barbeque terrace at the front of the villa beside the rice fields and parking space for up to six vehicles. Due to the steep hillside elevation, the villa is not recommended for disabled people or young children.</p><p>Villa Vajra is situated in the quiet traditional village of Sebali in the district of Kaliki, an hour and fifteen minutes'' drive from Ngurah Rai international airport, and about ten minutes'' drive from the cultural town of Ubud. This remarkable town is Bali''s centre for fine arts, dance and music, and the surrounding villages are home to Bali''s most accomplished painters, dancers, musicians and carvers. It is located 300 metres above sea level in the foothills of the central mountain range; this gives it a fresher, more pleasant climate than the southern coastal regions. The numerous art galleries in Ubud display traditional and modern work; the museums showcase the island''s rich history, and the shops and the market stalls sell handicrafts, jewellery, woodcarvings, textiles, paintings and antiques. There are many, well-presented, cultural performances staged in the town, in particular the Hindu epic, the Ramayana; also the Kecak Dance, the Fire Dance, the Monkey Dance and the Legong Dance. The countryside around Ubud is particularly beautiful, with an abundance of trails offering memorable walks through the peaceful rice fields. The location is convenient for tours all over the island and is only a forty-minute drive from the coast.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers round trip.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and basket fruits in room.</li>	<li>Daily checking &amp; replacing&nbsp;fine cotton sheets, down bedding and towels.</li>	<li>Serving Breakfast every day.</li>	<li>Complimentary&nbsp;shuttle service trip to Ubud.</li>	<li>24 hours Security service</li>	<li>Cooks offer an array of tempting Balinese and other Southeast Asian delicacies as well as traditional Western cuisines (special dietary requirements and dishes not on the menu are available on request).&nbsp;They teach&nbsp;cooking classes, too (extra cost).</li>	<li>Laundry services (surcharge).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pools: Private swimming pool 25,5 meters square;&nbsp;Jacuzzi.</li>	<li>Living areas: 3 air-conditioned Bedroom + 1 air-conditioned Study room (with single bed) along&nbsp;4 ensuite bathrooms;&nbsp;Fully equipped kitchen;&nbsp;Hair dryer;&nbsp;Safety deposit box in each bedroom.</li>	<li>Entertainments: TV, Satellite TV, DVD Player, Stereo system with CD at Study Room (bedroom 4);&nbsp;Book library;&nbsp;Board games.</li>	<li>Families: Baby cot;&nbsp;Baby high chair</li>	<li>Other facilities: Generator back-up during power failures;&nbsp;Sun loungers;&nbsp;Gym equipment.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>MANAGER: greets guests on their arrival, orients them to all that the villa has to offer, and helps them to plan their stay both on-site and by organizing exciting excursions around the island. He also will arrange for individual needs.</li>	<li>	<p>TWO VILLA ATTENDANTS: in charge of housekeeping and F&amp;B service.</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>TWO COOKS: trained in local cuisine as well as a wide range of international specialties. They do daily marketing and prepare meals to fit the guest’s dietary preferences.&nbsp;</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>FOUR SECURITY GUARDS: on-duty to ensure the safety and security of the guests and the premises.</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>TWO GARDEN &amp; POOL ATTENDANTS:&nbsp;work discreetly to maintain the landscaping and the pool without disturbing the guests.</p>	</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>Using shuttle bus only once daily (round trip)&nbsp;to Ubud.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>Charge service fee for cooking 30% + Bill for groceries.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14.00 pm</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : 50% one night seasonal rate if check-out until 16.00 PM and Full one night seasonal rate if check-out above 16.00 PM</li></ul>', NULL, '115.26040400', '-8.47731700', 6, 3, 5, 13, NULL, 6, '2016-09-07 12:14:49', '2016-09-23 11:09:00', NULL),
(7, 1, 'Villa Sati', 'villa-sati', 4, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Sati&nbsp;</strong>is a luxury villa&nbsp;standing just 50 meters apart in the village of Sebali which is only a ten minute drive from the cultural hub of Ubudappears, and to float upon its surrounding rice fields. This one bedroom plus hideaway, complete with plunge pool, takes its name from the Buddhist concept of "mindfulness". It can be rented independently or in conjunction with Villa Vajra.&nbsp;</p><p>The romantic villa&nbsp;hideaway&nbsp;is&nbsp;classic&nbsp;of contemporary Balinese architecture with thatched roofs while open to the drama of their surrounding landscapes.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Deep in rural Bali, yet only a ten minute drive from Ubud, the Island''s cultural centre, <strong>Villa Sati</strong> appears to float upon its surrounding rice fields. This one bedroom plus hideaway, complete with plunge pool, takes its name from the Buddhist concept of "mindfulness". It can be rented independently or in conjunction with Villa Vajra.</p><p>Villa Sati takes its name from the Buddhist word for&nbsp;‘mindfulness’. It is a magnificent hideaway. Its two thatched roof pavilions dramatically merge classical Balinese alang-alang (thatch) construction with soaring contemporary expanses of glass.&nbsp;It has been lovingly appointed with custom designed furnishings. It has its own plunge pool.<br /><br />An arch of giant bamboo and an elaborate, traditional Balinese gateway marks the entrance to Villa Sati. This private, walled enclave on the grounds of Vajra Villas is comprised of two thatched-roof pavilions bordering a courtyard, a small garden and a pool. The main two-storey pavilion is a jewel-like marriage of wood and glass offering stunning panoramic views of the rice fields, allows for an appreciation of the complexity and beauty of time-honoured practices of rice farming. The area is also a birdwatchers'' paradise, and in every direction lies an invitation to leisurely exploration. The caring staff provide a glimpse into the gentle Balinese spirit, fulfilling their duties with enthusiasm and ready smiles.</p><p>Between the two buildings on the upper level are a lotus pond and pergola. A serene Buddha statue dominates the lotus pond while white thunbergia flowers cascade over the covered walkway leading to the Master Bedroom, the small painting gallery and the Sawah bedroom. A plaza shaded by two white plumerias offers sunset viewing and a separate small thatched pavilion is the venue for rest, contemplation, meditation or yoga. There are areas designated for yoga, meditation, massage and gym workouts. There is parking space for six vehicles.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers round trip.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and basket fruits in room.</li>	<li>Daily checking &amp; replacing&nbsp;fine cotton sheets, down bedding and towels.</li>	<li>Serving Breakfast every day.</li>	<li>Complimentary&nbsp;shuttle service trip to Ubud.</li>	<li>24 hours Security service</li>	<li>Cooks offer an array of tempting Balinese and other Southeast Asian delicacies as well as traditional Western cuisines (special dietary requirements and dishes not on the menu are available on request).&nbsp;They teach&nbsp;cooking classes, too (extra cost).</li>	<li>Laundry services (surcharge).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pool: Swimming pool 6.2 m x 3.3 m,&nbsp;1.3 meters deep with own small water cascade.</li>	<li>Living areas: Air-conditioned bedroom with en-suite bathroom;&nbsp;Safe deposit box;&nbsp; Additional sleeping loft and bathroom; Kitchen with full equipped.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Entertainment: Satellite TV, DVD and CD player;&nbsp;DVD and CD library</li>	<li>Communications: Broadband internet connection (voucher system);&nbsp;IDD, Landline telephone (fax available)</li>	<li>Families: Baby cot and high chair</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;two sun beds;&nbsp;a table with four chairs;&nbsp;sheltered by a pergola is ideal for barbeques and alfresco dining.</li></ul>', '<p>MANAGER</p><p>greets guests on their arrival, orients them to all that the villa has to offer, and helps them to plan their stay both on-site and by organizing exciting excursions around the island. He also will arrange for individual needs.&nbsp;</p><p>TWO VILLA ATTENDANTS</p><p>in charge of housekeeping and F&amp;B service.&nbsp;</p><p>TWO COOKS</p><p>trained in local cuisine as well as a wide range of international specialties. They do daily marketing and prepare meals to fit the guest’s dietary preferences.&nbsp;</p><p>FOUR SECURITY GUARDS</p><p>on-duty to ensure the safety and security of the guests and the premises.&nbsp;</p><p>TWO GARDEN &amp; POOL ATTENDANTS</p><p>work discreetly to maintain the landscaping and the pool without disturbing the guests</p>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer, Complimentary daily breakfast ( 2 persons per room ), Internet connection, welcome fruit Basket.</li>	<li>Using shuttle bus only once daily (round trip)&nbsp;to Ubud.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>Charge service fee for cooking 20% + Bill for groceries.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14.00 pm</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : 50% one night seasonal rate if check-out until 16.00 PM and Full one night seasonal rate if check-out above 16.00 PM</li></ul>', NULL, '115.25821530', '-8.47731700', 2, 1, 5, 9, NULL, 6, '2016-09-07 16:55:51', '2016-09-23 11:09:39', NULL),
(8, 0, 'Villa Umah Cagaan', 'villa-umah-cagaan', 4, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Umah Cagaan</strong> boasts 4 spacious, air-conditioned en-suite bedrooms. Each bedroom with its individual soft and hard furnishings boasts a commitment to stated charm and harmony. King-size beds made of teak wood, parquet solid wood flooring and natural wood furnishings ensure comfort and style. The spacious Master Bedroom features a balcony and verandah where you can enjoy your afternoon tea and a good book. The master bedroom also includes satellite/cable TV and DVD player for your private entertainment options. Javanese bride and groom Loro Blonyo figures symbolize love, harmony, throughout the space. A private open shower in addition to the bathtub overlooks the greenery outside.</p>', '', '', '<p>Walking downstairs, you''ll find a cozy Media Room equipped with 60" wide screen plasma HD cable television, DVD player and an assorted collection of DVDs to choose from.</p><p>The adjacent Villa''s Spa Room offers various massages and beauty treatments, using natural spices and herbs of Bali. A gym is also available and accessible at any time.</p><p>The Villa''s dedicated Manager is on call 24-hours. Anything can easily be arranged for our guests. While your private chef can prepare meals to the guests'' specifications, our fully staffed team can fulfill any guests'' whim, 24 hours a day - looking after your every need, from daily housekeeping, to preparing a full range of fine cuisine from a simple breakfast to a formal dinner. Enjoy your meals cooked in the Villa''s beautifully large and fully equipped kitchen or create your own Teppanyaki outdoor grill or barbeque. Eat outdoors on the terraces, the lawn or at the pool side surrounded by frangipani trees, orchids, ferns, hanging heliconias, and at times, yellow butterflies.</p><p>Adjacent to the 16mx4m infinity swimming pool is the Bale or Sala decorated with local colors of beautiful traditional Balinese and Javanese furniture. This open living area is equipped with a collection of novels and is just the place for relaxing, enjoying yoga, an afternoon siesta, or just sipping your herbal scented tea.</p><p>Our traditional Bale Bengong is another opportunity not to be missed. Green rice paddy spread at your feet along with the soothing sounds of water flowing from the Pangkung streams are just there for your private enjoyment at Umah Cagaan.</p><p>Wide arrays of activities outside the Villa are only a stones throw away. Our Manager can arrange with ease: a visit to the Bali Bird Park, Blanco Renaissance Museum; a seat at the local Jazz club, Ubud restaurant reservations; fishing, cycling, rafting, horse riding, elephant trekking and others. Or, simply enjoy a walk in the early burst of the sun and chat with people of the village to gain an insight into their lives. Truly all is possible just ask!</p>', '', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer ( 1 x in &amp; 1 x out ), Welcoming drink, Exclusive use of the villa and all amenities, Daily American-style breakfast (2 persons per room), Fine cotton sheets; down bedding and towels, Ubud Shuttle provide at the villa start from 8 a.m to 8 p,m : one car only, Staffs</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5% service charge</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14.00 pm</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : 50% one night seasonal rate if check-out until 16.00 PM and Full one night seasonal rate if check-out above 16.00 PM</li></ul>', NULL, '115.29400000', '-8.50975000', 8, 4, 5, NULL, NULL, 6, '2016-09-08 08:30:55', '2016-09-20 10:59:17', NULL);
