s or estates, and some are subject to rules and regulations regarding their use. Therefore, it may not always be possible to grant permission for certain uses or activities due to these or other reasons beyond the control of Management&nbsp;and the Owner.</p><p>If Management&nbsp;has confirmed a booking which includes an event at the Guest’s chosen Property, in certain circumstances the Guest must then obtain permits from the police and the local community before the event can proceed. The Guest acknowledges and agrees that Management, the Owner and the Owner’s Representative cannot control the issue of these permits. If the police and/or the local community refuse to issue a permit for an event at the Property, the Owner or the Owner’s Representative will refund any event fee paid by the Guest to the Owner, however neither Management, the Owner nor the Owner’s Representative will be liable for any further refund or payment to the Guest.</p><h4><strong>Conduct and Due Care</strong></h4><p>Properties are generally located in quiet residential neighbourhoods. The Guest is asked to respect this, and ensure that all guests and visitors to the Property behave appropriately. Illegal or immoral activities including gambling, prostitution, prohibited drugs, possession or use of pyrotechnics or dangerous goods, and possession or use of firearms and other weapons are all strictly prohibited. Smoking is generally prohibited unless stated otherwise in the booking confirmation or reservation voucher.</p><p>The Guest is responsible for the behaviour of the guests staying at the Property, as well as visitors to the Property during the Rental Period. Should any guest(s) or visitor(s) not behave in a suitable manner, the Owner or Owner’s Representative may, in their absolute discretion, require the Guest, their party and/or visitor(s) to leave the premises and/or vacate the Property immediately, without compensation or refund</p><p>In the interests of safety, due care should be taken at the Property at all times, especially with children. Suitable supervision should be given around pools, beaches and roads, and when using all Property’s facilities.</p><h4><strong>Valuables and Security</strong></h4><p>Any Guest valuables or property left or used at the Property are at the Guest’s own risk. Neither Management, the Owner nor the Owner’s Representative accepts any responsibility for loss of or damage to Guest property. The Guest is responsible for the Property during the Rental Period, and must ensure that all windows and doors are locked securely when not on the premises. Any act or omission by the Guest, their party and/or visitors which may negate or prejudice the Property’s insurance policy and/or results in loss or damage is the Guest’s responsibility.</p><p><strong>Price Fluctuation</strong></p><p>Once the Guest’s booking is confirmed, the price of the Guest’s reservation is fully guaranteed, even if Management&nbsp;changes the price on its website after the Guest’s booking has been confirmed. In return for this commitment, no refunds will be made for any exchange rate fluctuations that would otherwise reduce the rental cost.</p><p>Management reserves the right to impose any taxes or other charges which may be implemented by any government or other regulatory body, which were unknown at the time of publishing. Management will tell the Guest promptly in the unlikely event that it becomes aware that any taxes or charges will apply to the Guest’s booking.</p><h4><strong>Cancellations</strong></h4><p>If the Guest wishes to cancel a confirmed booking, written notice of cancellation must be sent to Management. All cancellation notices received by Management will be acknowledged in writing. It is strongly recommended that the Guest and all members of the Guest’s party purchase trip cancellation insurance.</p><p>Cancellation of a booking includes but is not limited to:</p><ul>	<li>Cancellation of one or more days of a booking;</li>	<li>An amendment of a booking so that none of the dates of the booking once amended fall within the same dates that originally constituted the booking;</li>	<li>Failure of all Guests to provide the required documentation on arrival (eg. Passports or suitable identification); and</li>	<li>Attempt by the Guest, their party or visitors to hold an event at the Property in breach of these Terms and Conditions or breach of any rules applicable to the Guest’s chosen Property.</li></ul><p>In the event that the Guest cancels a confirmed booking, the following cancellation fees will generally apply:</p><ul>	<li>20% of the total rental amount will be forfeited if the cancellation is made more than 60 days before the start of the rental period</li>	<li>50% of the total rental amount will be forfeited if the cancellation is made between 30 and 60 days before the start of the rental period</li>	<li>100% of the total rental amount will be forfeited if the cancellation is made between 1 and 29 days before the start of the rental period.</li></ul><p>The applicable amount will be deducted from the deposit and moneys paid, and Management will refund any remaining balance to the Guest.</p><h4><strong>Amendments</strong></h4><p>Once a booking confirmation is issued by Management, a fee of USD 50 will apply to each amendment made. Management will do its best to accommodate any reasonable amendments, but the Guest should be aware that some changes may not be possible.</p><p>Please note that these amendment policies apply for regular booking periods. Special amendment terms may apply for peak/high seasons and will be stated in the Property description, booking confirmation or reservation voucher. If the information in any of these is inconsistent, the most recently issued terms will prevail.</p><p>In the unlikely event that Management is unable for any reason (including the sale of a property and force majeure) to provide the Guest with the Property booked by the Guest, Management reserves the right to transfer the Guest and their party to an alternative Property of the similar type and value, in consultation with the Guest. If the price of the substituted Property is less than the original booking, the difference will be reimbursed to the Guest. If the price of the substituted Property is higher than the original booking, the difference may be charged to the Guest. If, however, after considerable effort by Management, no alternative of similar type and value is available and / or no agreement can be reached between the Guest and Management, then either Management or the Guest may opt to cancel the booking and this Rental Contract. In that event, Management will refund the Guest all monies paid, without further compensation.</p><h4><strong>Complaints</strong></h4><p>Every attempt will be made for the Guest to have an enjoyable stay. If the Guest should have a problem during the Rental Period, please inform the Owner or Owner’s Representative immediately who will endeavour to put things right. Should the Owner or Owner’s Representative not address the Guest’s problem satisfactorily, please contact Management promptly. In order for the Guest’s complaint to be addressed, the Guest must communicate any problem whilst on location. If no complaint is reported during the Rental Period, Management and the Owner will assume that the Property was to the Guest’s satisfaction and no complaint will be entertained.</p><p><strong>Provisions</strong></p><p>Self-catering accommodations require that the Guest supply all provisions and consumables necessary for daily living. The staff at the Property may accommodate any reasonable requests to purchase provisions on the Guest’s behalf, and this will be charged to the Guest’s account.</p><p><strong>Management’s Responsibility</strong></p><p>The descriptions, assessments and/or ratings of Properties and surrounding locations that Management publishes or gives to the Guest are provided in good faith and in the belief that they are accurate based on the latest information received. However, Management cannot be held responsible for any modifications to the Properties or inaccuracies. Where Management publishes or refers to descriptions, assessments and/or ratings of the Property either by Management or by third parties, these ratings are for information purposes only and Management will not be held responsible for any reliance placed on these ratings.</p><p><strong>Disclaimers</strong></p><p>Neither Management, the Owner nor the Owner’s Representative accepts any responsibility or liability for:</p><ul>	<li>any physical injury, sickness, death, loss, damage, inconvenience or additional expenses incurred by the Guest, their party or visitors regardless of the cause;</li>	<li>any vehicle or the contents of any vehicle used, hired or engaged by the Guest or their party during the Rental Period;<br />	inability of the Guest or any member of the Guest’s party to enter the location of the Property or stay at the Property for all or part of the Rental Period as a result of failure to obtain appropriate travel or visa documentation, cancellation or amendments to travel arrangements or the missing of flights or travel connections; and/or</li>	<li>any delay or cancellation of the booking as a result of war, threat of war, riot or civil strife, strike, demonstration, terrorist activity (threatened or actual), natural disaster, fire, sickness, weather conditions, action at an airport or port by any government or public authority, technical problems relating to transport and airport regulations caused by technical, mechanical or electrical breakdowns, or any technical, structural, electrical, plumbing or other problems or difficulties with the Property which make it unsafe or unusable, or any other circumstances which amount to ‘force majeure’ or Acts of God, or other events beyond the Owner’s control.</li></ul><p>In no case will Management, the Owner or the Owner’s Representative individually or collectively be liable to make any payment or give any refund or compensation of any amount over and above the total rental amount paid.</p><h4><strong>Jurisdiction&nbsp;</strong></h4><p>This agreement will be governed by the laws of Hong Kong. In the event of controversy arising from the booking and Property rental that cannot be resolved amicably between the parties, both parties agree to exclusively refer the matter to the Singapore International Arbitration Centre to be resolved finally by arbitration in the English language.</p><p>By making its booking request, the Guest agrees that these terms and conditions have been read, understood and have been accepted and agreed to by the Guest without reservation and without exception.</p><p>If any of the conditions of this Rental Contract are or become or are deemed to be invalid, or if there is any omission from any terms and conditions, the remaining terms and conditions will remain valid and enforceable and cannot be contested.</p><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 2 Nights) : Jan 9th to June 30th, 16 sep - 19 Dec, excluded Easter period and Chinese New Year&nbsp;</li>	<li>High Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 5 Nights) : July 1st to September 15th, Easter period (30 March - 4 april 2013) and Chinese New Year (29 Jan - 4 Feb, 2013)</li>	<li>Peak Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 7 Nights) : December 20th to January 8th</li></ul>', NULL, '115.15333930', '-8.68310370', 8, 4, 2, NULL, NULL, 3, '2016-09-12 11:05:42', '2016-09-27 08:24:25', NULL),
(13, 1, 'Villa Ria Sayan', 'villa-ria-sayan', 4, 1, '<p>Welcome to <strong>Villa Ria Sayan</strong> where you can find little piece of heaven in Ubud, Bali. Located in a perfect secluded area in the town, our luxury accommodation comes with elegance and natural scene of this Thousand Temple Island. The moment you enter the villa is passing through antique gate and serene garden. Small fishpond in the entrance leads you to the main villa continuing the infinity pool. Rice field view and coconut trees under the clear blue sky let everybody’s eyes to admire. Also the view of volcanoes and Sayan Gorge makes the setting of the villa completely adorable.</p><p>Villa Ria Sayan is nestled into the natural hillside amongst fruit trees, tropical plants and flowers. You enter the walled villa compound from the parking area through an antique entrance gate, and follow a path through the garden, past the temple, down stone steps, and over a small fish pond at the main villa entrance. From here will experience one of the most spectacular views in all of Bali - the famous Sayan Gorge.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Ria Sayan</strong> is a privately owned, but professionally managed, luxury villa retreat that is available for rental when its owner is not in Bali. Villa Ria is located down a narrow, private drive in a traditional Balinese village, a few minute drive from Ubud. The private, walled compound is perched on the edge of the famous Sayan Ridge with spectacular views across the gorge to terraced rice fields, an active Balinese temple, and views to the volcanoes beyond. You will see the farmers planting, cultivating, and harvesting their rice crop and you will hear the haunting sounds of traditional chants and music drifting across the valley from the temple. You will find yourself surrounded by the peace, beauty, and magic of traditional Bali.</p><p>Villa Ria Sayan was built with Indonesian esthetic varying from antique furniture, traditional textile and Balinese crafts. All furniture was selected that purposed to give classy taste in the entire of the villa. The open-air concept brought in the living and dining pavilion presents spacious sensation overlooking magnificent Sayan Valley and the pool. The pool itself completed with pool loungers, bale and dining table, all fenced by beautiful bushes.</p><p>The villa consists of 2 master en-suite bedrooms furnished with four-poster king-sized beds, mosquito netting, air-con and fan. Gym equipment, Internet access, library with collection of books, TV and DVD player are there to entertain you. For perfect dining, our chef is available to serve you nice menu ranging from Western, Indonesian, Asian or other special selections. Having breakfast, lunch, dinner or snacks everyday with family in the poolside is a pleasant moment. In your relax time, you can ask for in villa yoga or massage that is at additional cost. If you need something, please tell our villa staffs to assist you. The owner of Villa Ria Sayan has succeeded in creating a luxury accommodation that not only gives comfort and privacy to each guest, but also simply brings the essence of Bali.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers roundtrip.</li>	<li>Welcome drink and towel, and welcome fruits basket.</li>	<li>Continental Breakfast service daily.</li>	<li>Highly trained Staffs are&nbsp;available to help with any questions, special requests or in case of an emergency, and helping for arranging transportation with negoitable price.</li>	<li>Private Dining Menu has been prepared by a chef of a five star resort who also trained the staff in safe food handling, preparation and presentation.</li>	<li>Laundry and Baby Sitting&nbsp;at extra charge.</li>	<li>Doctor on call.</li>	<li>Car and driver at additional charge.</li>	<li>In-house&nbsp;villa yoga, villa massage at additional cost.</li>	<li>Laundry and dry cleaning service at additional charge.</li>	<li>Night security service.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: infinity style swimming pool and pool terrace.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Living areas: AC;&nbsp;Ceiling / Wall Fan;&nbsp;Library;&nbsp;Safety Box;&nbsp;Study room;&nbsp;Hair dryers;&nbsp;Fire extinguishers;&nbsp;Smoke alarms;&nbsp;Guest safe</li>	<li>Sports:&nbsp;Gym.</li>	<li>Communications: Internet Connection;&nbsp;IDD Telephone access.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;TV;&nbsp;Cable TV, DVD players</li>	<li>Families: Baby cots on complimentary basis</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;Extra beds at additional charge;&nbsp;Car and driver;&nbsp;Traditional Bale;&nbsp;Tropical garden</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p>The villa is furnished with Indonesian antique furniture and artifacts, hand woven textiles and local Balinese crafts The entrance foyer''s stone stairs lead down to a spacious, open-air, traditional Balinese style living and dining pavilion with alang-alang roof. This main living area overlooks the natural stone tile, infinity style swimming pool and pool terrace. A separate, fully equipped staff kitchen is located adjacent to the dining area. Stone walls, fountains, and ponds surround the main pavilion. A few steps lead directly from the main pavilion to the swimming pool and patio area with umbrella shaded teakwood dining table, pool loungers, and poolside bale.</p><p>From the entrance foyer antique Balinese doors open to the villa''s two master guest bedrooms with garden style ensuite bathrooms. Each is furnished with four poster, king size bed with mosquito netting, ceiling fan, and air conditioner.</p><p>The upper level of the villa is reached by timber stairs from the entrance foyer. Here you will find a combination study/ guestroom and additional garden style bathroom. Floor to ceiling windows overlook the pool area, the rice fields and village temple on the far side of the valley. The wall of windows fold open for cool breezes or close for air conditioned sleeping. The study is furnished with a three quarter size antique Javanese bed, oversize desk, armchairs and entertainment center. Equipment includes a bar fridge, telephone/fax, satellite flat screen HD television, VCD and CD players; and a growing library of recent fiction, books on culture, local design, and guidebooks.</p>', '<p>The Ria Sayan Villa has&nbsp;24 hour staff includes senior staff member and excellent cook Nengah, as well as our housemaid Ketut. Both of whom speak excellent English. And, other staffs include&nbsp;gardener and pool attendant Wayan, and 2 guards, Made and Ketut who support the household staff and provide security.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Villa Ria Sayan is a non-smoking villa.</li>	<li>Rates include of Return airport transfer, daily continental breakfast (2 persons per room), welcome refreshment, WiFi Internet.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>Guests are charged only for ingredients used in meal preparation for private dining.</li>	<li>Check-in Time : 14:00 PM.</li>	<li>Check-out Time : 12:00 Noon.</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM.</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.23891600', '-8.51010700', 4, 2, 3, 7, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 07:09:38', '2016-09-23 11:13:07', NULL),
(14, 1, 'Villa Ahn', 'villa-ahn', 4, 0, '<p>Nestled in the rice fields of Ubud, Bali,&nbsp;<strong>Villa Ahn</strong>&nbsp;is a luxurious privately owned property that provides the perfect environment from which to discover the many delights of the beautiful "Island of Gods". Ubud is a 50 minute drive from the international airport at Denpasar.</p><p>The villa is a private home that blends elegantly into its surroundings, fusing Asian and Western influences harmoniously together. Traditional "alang-alang" thatched roofing, spacious living areas open to the elements, and inspiring views of the surrounding fields and mountains showcase the natural beauty of the location. Incorporating all the comforts of modern living, Villa Ahn is a place to unwind and relax, whilst its central location also makes it an ideal base from which to explore the rest of Bali, with a multitude of activities and amenities on the doorstep.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Ahn</strong> is well situated in Pejeng that is 15 minutes away from central Ubud, our Villa Ahn is presented to you with all pleasures of Bali. Surrounded by amazing rice fields and greeneries, it is giving fine impression to everybody who sees it. Ubud, as people know it, has been popular for its art, beautiful scenery, spa and adventurous sites to experience such as museums, Ubud Art Market, Monkey Forest or Elephant Cave. The villa itself gives perfect site to explore among privacy, amenities and style.</p><p>Build on nearly 4,500 square feet; Villa Ahn combined Balinese architecture with modernity to meet the idea of luxury accommodation in Bali. Shades of Asian and the Western are applied to provide harmonization that brings admiration. The villa has 3 en-suite bedrooms around exotic gardens; spending holiday at Villa Ahn is differently enjoyable than you''ve ever known. Each room furnished with queen-sized beds, bathtubs, showers and wardrobes, as well as air conditioners and fans. In order to give natural impression, decoration is put in soft colors but still gives luxurious look. The bedrooms are designed to bring the comfort so you can wake up the next morning with a happy feeling.</p><p>The infinity pool that is situated around the rice fields and verdant coconut plants invite anyone to immediately swim, sunbath or just relax in the bale with <em>alang-alang</em> thatched roof. Beautiful scenery can be enjoyed through the spacious living room, where you can spend all day to fully relax. The services provided will give satisfaction to the guests. Villa Ahn serves you from personal butler service, the villa manager and security; it is guaranteed to meet everything you need. Completed with fully equipped kitchen also allows you to create your own dining. In short, choosing Villa Ahn is a worth spending your holiday as you will get indulgences, everything in one package.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport Transfer round trip.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks on arrival with refresh towel.</li>	<li>Welcome Fruit Basket in the room.</li>	<li>Daily American-style breakfast for 2 persons per room.</li>	<li>Coffee and Tea at anytime during the stay,</li>	<li>Free of charge shuttle bus service within Ubud.</li>	<li>Personal Butler service and&nbsp;24h security.</li>	<li>Souvenir on check out time.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: infinity pool with pool bed.</li>	<li>Living areas: a 3 Air-conditioned and fan bedrooms with en-suite bathroom each room; Living area and dining;&nbsp;Fully equipped kitchen with full size fridge / freezer and coffee &amp; tea maker.</li>	<li>Entertainments: Flat TV and satellite chanels; DVD and CD players with sound system.</li>	<li>Communication: internet connection.</li>	<li>Additional facilities: Safety box; Mini Bar;&nbsp;finest Egyptian cotton bedding and towels; Drinking water.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Villa manager</li>	<li>Chef&nbsp;</li>	<li>Housekeeper</li>	<li>Gardener &amp;&nbsp;Pool Attendant</li>	<li>Driver</li>	<li>Security guards</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 21% government tax and service.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that early chek in and late check out is subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.28966900', '-8.51477450', 6, 3, 5, 6, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 07:35:10', '2016-09-23 11:12:24', NULL),
(15, 1, 'Villa Bayad', 'villa-bayad', 4, 1, '<p><b>Villa Bayad</b> is a spacious, luxurious 4 bedrooms villa, designed by Popo Danes, one of the most renowned architects in Southeast Asia. The villa is traditionally laid out as a compound, the 4 bedrooms being separate houses beside the main house, all connected by flower-covered pergolas. From every room there is a beautiful view across the surrounding rice terraces to Bali''s sacred volcano in the horizon.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Bayad </strong>is Fifteen minutes north of Ubud – in the middle of lush green ricepaddies, with a magnificent view of Bali’s mighty Mount Agung, lies Villa Bayad – a private luxurious 4 bedrooms villa with two swimming pools, surrounded by a 8000 m2 garden of sweet smelling flowers, lotus-ponds and waterfalls,&nbsp;laid out as sloping terraces and bordered by a small river, you will constantly experience the amazing touch of un-disturbed nature. Moving through jungle-like vegetation, you will arrive at the traditional gate and lobby, where the magnificent view of the garden and the rice fields awaits you. In the garden there are numerous coconut palms and fruit trees, and the organically grown vegetable&nbsp;and herb-gardens supply the villa''s household.</p><p>Staying here is your chance of experiencing the real Bali aesthetic from the inside and at the same time enjoying the tranquility of nature and the local countryside, while your friendly staff will be right there to cater to your every need.</p><p>And with Ubud – Bali’s cultural center – just 15 minutes away, you will be conveniently close to shops, restaurants and galleries.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfer roundtrip.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast in villa.</li>	<li>Free of charge Ubud Shuttle.</li>	<li>Staffs could prepare lunches and dinners on request.</li>	<li>Arranging on request &nbsp;in-house&nbsp;massaseu,&nbsp;yoga lessons and cooking class,&nbsp;excursion tours,&nbsp;Balinese dance evenings,&nbsp;visit to local artists and galleries,&nbsp;trekking tours (extra charge).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilties</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: main pool&nbsp;18 by 5 meter&nbsp;springwater pool with&nbsp;sunbeds and sunshades, and the plung pool.</li>	<li>Living areas: a 4 air-conditioned bedrooms in different house; equipped kitchen;&nbsp;furnished veranda and bathroom complete with shower cabin and a small walled garden with outdoor shower.</li>	<li>Entertainments: cable TV; DVD Player; high quality audio and video experience;&nbsp;</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi</li>	<li>Sports: Mountain bicycle (4 units);&nbsp;Gym, Yoga&nbsp;mats &amp;&nbsp;cushions.</li>	<li>Other facilities: The Sunrise Bridge, Bale.</li>	<li>The Teriyaki Grill Cafe</li>	<li>The Spa</li>	<li>Huge Garden</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Main House</strong></p><p>The spacious living and dining area opens to a large veranda, surrounded by flower covered, multi-level fishponds and flanked by two comfortable bales, where you can relax, listening to the sprinkling water and enjoying the beautiful view. An open, fully equipped kitchen is ready for the staff to prepare your meals on your request or feel free to use kitchen by yourself, if you prefer to cook your own meals.Just couple steps upstairs in the main house you will find an air-conditioned media room with mini library and hi-quality audio- and video experience.</p><p>It is furnished with spacious sitting areas, a 10 seat dining table and multiple artwork. The rooms open through folding doors towards a spacious natural stone floored veranda, all surrounded by water lily-covered, terrassed fishponds and with two flanking traditional bales offering breezy, shady relaxation.&nbsp;A tastefully decorated guest powderroom is also located in the main house.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The bedrooms</strong></p><p><b>The Tenganan House</b><br />This is the largest bedroom, tile thatched, styled and named after the the pictoresque Bali Aga village near the east Bali coast. Standing on columns, overlooking the main pool, it is right on the brink of the lower garden area. The breezy high perched veranda offers a close view over the rice paddies to the mountain in the distance. This house has a large queensize bed and a spacious walk-in closet. It is possible to supply with an extra bed if needed. The parltly open bathroom, floored with natural stone tiles, offers two washbasins, WC and shower cabin.</p><p>Directly connected is a beautiful open, walled spa-area, covered by a traditional bale in the middle of a reflecting Koi-pond.</p><p><b>The Klung Kung House</b><br />This house is styled and named after the old royal town in the center of east Bali. It is located closest to the main house, and it has the loveliest view to the ricefields from the relaxing bale right in the center of a small private water garden. The bedroom has a hardwood floor and is fitted with a queen size bed (with dividable mattresses if needed), a walk in closet and a TV with DVD-player. It is possible to supply with an extra bed if needed.</p><p>The partly open bathroom, floored with natural stone tiles, offers two washbasins, WC and shower cabin.</p><p>This house is also connected to the spa area.</p><p><b>The Ubud House</b><br />This house is styled and named after the nearby town - Bali’s cultural center.<br />The bedroom has a hardwood floor and is fitted with a queen size bed (with dividable mattresses if needed), and a TV with DVD-player. It is possible to supply with an extra bed if needed. The bathroom, floored with natural stone tiles, offers two washbasins, WC and shower cabin. In addition, it has a small walled garden with an open air shower.</p><p><b>The Singaraja House</b><br />This house is styled and named after the former capital and trading town on Bali’s north coast. The bedroom has a hardwood floor and is fitted with a queen size bed (with dividabe mattresses if needed), and a TV with DVD-player. It is possible to supply with an extra bed if needed. The bathroom, floored with turquise coloured terazzo, offers two washbasins, WC and shower cabin, as well as a small walled garden with an open air shower.</p><p>The Ubud&nbsp;and the Singaraja Houses share a private open air fully equipped kitchen&nbsp;and dining-bale, as well as a private spring-water fed plunge pool and pool-deck.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Spa</strong></p><p>The spa area is connecting two of the bungalows. It is a beautiful open, walled court,<br />covered by a traditional bale in the middle of a reflecting pond, where colourful koi are swimming. Here is a natural stone bathtub and an open air waterfall styled shower and a massage bed.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Pool</strong></p><p><b>The main pool</b><br />The huge 18 by 5 meter pool is springwater fed and flanked by a spacious ironwood pooldeck furnished with sunbeds and sunshades. Protruding into the pool is a traditional bale, where you can relax in the shade.</p><p><b>The plunge pool</b><br />The plunge pool connected to the two smaller bungalows, is also springwater fed, and is flanked by a small stone floored pooldeck with sunchairs and sunshade.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Sunrise bridge</strong></p><p>Spanning a small canyon of rocks, lily ponds and waterfalls, the Sunrise Bridge offers you a beautiful breezy spot for dining or relaxing - or to receive yoga lessons.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Teriyaki Grill</strong></p><p>Connecting to the pooldeck is the teriyaki kitchen with cafe-tables and chairs. Here you can enjoy your drinks, snacks or poolside-meals from the genuine teriyaki grill.</p><p><strong>Villa Bayad - The Gym</strong></p><p>If you want to keep fit during your stay, an airconditioned, well equipped gym is at your free disposal.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Villa manager&nbsp;</li>	<li>House manager&nbsp;</li>	<li>Cooks&nbsp;</li>	<li>Housekeepers&nbsp;</li>	<li>Gardener</li>	<li>Pool Attendants</li>	<li>Driver</li>	<li>Securities.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Rates, Checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include Airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10.5% VAT and 5% service charge.</li>	<li>Grocery bills plus 20% handling fee.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low: Jan 9 – June 30, Sept 16 – Dec 19.</li>	<li>High: July 1 – July 31, Sept 1 – Sept 15 (Including all the Chinese and Easter Periods).</li>	<li>Peak: Aug 1 – Aug 31, Dec 20 – Jan 8.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.24413180', '-8.44773960', 8, 4, 3, 14, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 07:55:56', '2016-09-23 11:14:51', NULL);
INSERT INTO `villas` (`id`, `status`, `title`, `slug`, `area_id`, `featured`, `intro`, `description`, `services`, `facilities`, `staff_detail`, `term_condition`, `other`, `longitude`, `latitude`, `occupied_max`, `bedrooms_no`, `environment_id`, `staff_no`, `position`, `created_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`) VALUES
(16, 1, 'Villa Sebali', 'villa-sebali', 4, 0, '<p>This beautiful, very spacious villa on the edge of Sebali, a pretty village just outside Ubud, is a luxurious haven from which to enjoy both the peace and the delights of Bali. The views from the house are of typical rice terraces and, in the distance, spectacular Mt Agung and the dramatic mountains towards the north of the island. We have been careful to be environmentally sensitive – green – with many eco-features including solar power and water heating, and a beautiful garden with organically grown fruit trees.&nbsp;It also has beautiful setting of green rice paddies that brings you to the real village panorama. Villa Sebali is just 15 minute’s drive from Ubud center, so it can be sure that you will have all those experiences if you stay in here.</p><p>A pleasant hideaway holiday home – but also, green, quiet, fragrant&nbsp;<strong>Villa Sebali</strong>&nbsp;is a wonderful place just to be.</p>', '<p>This beautiful, very spacious villa on the edge of Sebali Village, a pretty village just outside Ubud.&nbsp;Ubud, located in the center of Bali, is well known for its art and culture where you can find numbers of art shops, museums or souvenirs shop in Ubud or Sukawati Market. It&nbsp;is a luxurious haven from which to enjoy both the peace and the delights of Bali.&nbsp;</p><p>Built on almost 3000 square meter of land, Villa Sebali has 5 main bedrooms with different views. First one is Sky Bedroom Suite; facilitated with modern amenities, this bedroom has cathedral ceiling to allow the guest enjoying the sky view. Second bedroom is Forest Bedroom Suite that charms you with its beautiful forest view. Also completed with high standard hotel features, this suite is completely comforting. Sunrise and Sunset Bedroom Suites are other bedrooms that both have stunning ceiling. Sunrise Bedroom Suite is toward Mount Agung and will be nice option for honeymooners. The last room is library where you can spend time by reading, watching TV, playing games or just relaxing on the comfortable settee.</p><p>To indulge the entire guest, Villa Sebali is comprised with magnificent infinity pool and sitting area by the poolside for totally relaxing time. Fully equipped kitchen and dining area with 12 seats to allow you having fine dining with all family members also opened living area that is exquisitely accomplished. At last but not least, full time villa staffs are available to assist you including cook, security guard, gardeners and house staff to prepare all your need during your stay.</p><p>To realize your dream of holiday in Bali that is fully pleasurable and comfortable, we suggest you to choose home stay that does not only have sufficient facilities and features but also caring ambiance to your holiday destination.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Welcome drink on arrival with cake/Balinese cake and in-room fruits basket.</li>	<li>Daily serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>House manager will assist what guests need as part of villa service.</li>	<li>Cooks will prepare lunches and dinners in privately&nbsp;with reasonable price.</li>	<li>Serving daily American-style breakfast.</li>	<li>Complementary tea and coffee are available all day.</li>	<li>Free Ubud Shuttle</li>	<li>24h security.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool:&nbsp;infinity swimming pool is 12m. x 4m.</li>	<li>Spacious parking car (up to 4 cars).</li>	<li>Living areas: 4 Air-conditioned bedrooms with different type, size and separate WC and shower; Living and spacious Dining area; Fully equipped Kitchen; Library room.</li>	<li>A locally usable mobile phone will be supplied.</li>	<li>Cotton sheets, down bedding and towels</li>	<li>Filtered drinking water is supplied.</li>	<li>Hair driers and an iron are supplied</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities&nbsp;Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Accommodation</strong></p><p>The house is approached by a tree fern-shaded path leading from the front courtyard with space for three or four cars, over an ornamental pool and into the main building.</p><ul>	<li><b>Dining area</b> - spacious and equipped for up to 12 at table. It is open to the garden at one side and has two steps down to the living area. At the side is the</li>	<li><b>Kitchen</b> - fully equipped with large fridge-freezer and permanent chilled drinking water.</li>	<li><b>Living area</b> - an enormous room open to the garden with ample seating and many art works</li></ul><p>All the above areas have rich terra-cotta coloured floor tiles, a lovely combination of warmth for the eye and coolness for the room.</p><p><strong>Villa Sebali - Bedrooms</strong></p><ul>	<li><b>Sky bedroom suite</b> - vast, with a fantastic cathedral ceiling and flower-edged terraces facing all four points of the compass with views to die for!. A large dressing area leads to the bathroom which is partly open air with wash basin, WC, bath, separate shower. One of its four terraces is covered and has seating for relaxing and admiring the garden and view.</li>	<li><b>Forest bedroom suite</b> - equipped with twin beds which can also be joined to make one king size bed. The dressing area leads to the shower room with wash basin and separate WC. A door leads through to the</li>	<li><b>Library</b> - an enchanting rotunda which can also be reached directly by steps from the garden. Equipped with flat screen TV, books, games and comfortable seating, this room can either be used as a sitting room for the Forest Bedroom, or as a communal room for all guests.</li>	<li><b>Sunset bedroom suite</b> - This is another generous room with cathedral ceiling and a queen sized bed. The spacious dressing area leads through to the bathroom with basin, WC, shower and garden. It has its own pretty patio.</li>	<li><b>Sunrise bedroom suite</b> - As the name suggests, this huge room with its magnificent ceiling and king size bed faces east, towards Mt Agung, and has double doors opening onto a raised deck shaded by a flower-festooned pergola. Steps lead down to the pool and courtyard. There is a big dressing area leading through to the biggest bathroom of all which, again, is partly open to the sky and has its own garden. It is equipped with bath, basin, shower and separate WC.</li></ul><p>All the bedrooms have mosquito nets and full air-conditioning, though the house is designed to optimise cooling: all the rooms are shaded by the deep eaves of the alang-alang roofs, and big windows allow refreshing air to flow through freely. There are ceiling fans in all rooms including the living areas.</p><p>Additional beds can be supplied, and there is also a very large comfortable daybed in the living area which would make an excellent extra bed. Guests who like the idea of sleeping under the stars could even sleep on the bale!</p><p>The villa is built on almost 3000sq.m. (3/4 acre) so the gardens are generous and have been beautifully planted by a top professional and are maintained on organic principles. Beyond the courtyard and pool, a series of voluptuous ponds echoing the neighbouring rice fields and planted with lotus and water lilies cascades down to the orchard, and pretty paths wind between them. The orchard is planted with, among other fruits: avocados, pineapples, mangoes, papayas, bananas, jack fruit, durian, nutmeg, lemons and limes. There is also a herb garden for keen cooks.</p><p>The infinity swimming pool is 12m. x 4m. plus a side sitting area. For relaxing there are garden reclining chairs and big sunshades as well as the pretty bal. There is a built-in barbeque adjacent to the bale for al fresco cooking and dining.&nbsp;</p>', '<header class="entry-header"><p class="entry-title">Villa Sebali’s overall manager is Rita Dewi, a renowned Balinese dancer. She has excellent English and can help with any problems and special requests. She will be sure to come to the villa to meet you and ensure that all is well.</p></header><div class="entry-content"><div id="pl-163"><div class="panel-grid" id="pg-163-0"><div class="panel-grid-cell" id="pgc-163-0-0"><div class="so-panel widget widget_text panel-first-child panel-last-child" data-index="0" id="panel-163-0-0-0"><div class="textwidget"><p>Our house manager is Ketut Muliarta. He is a well educated man who also has very good English. As well as having considerable hotel experience, he is also a good driver and can act as tour guide on request at a reasonable rate. He will ensure your stay at Villa Sebali is comfortable and trouble-free, respond to your requests promptly and make sure you have a good time.</p><p>Also in the house are Ayu and Ketut, who are both excellent cooks (Indonesian and Western). All the staff are very good with children. If your party is very large we can employ extra staff from the village. Babysitting can be arranged.</p><p>Ketut and Ayu will prepare delicious lunches, dinners and snack menus, all at very reasonable prices. Equally, we can advise on restaurants which can deliver, though our food is so good you are unlikely to use them except for very special requests. And there are dozens – maybe hundreds – of cafes and restaurants within a 20 minute drive of Villa Sebali, from the very modest to top level.</p><p>The housekeepers are Ngurah and Wayan (Ngurah is from our village, Sebali). They are hard-working and responsible. They will make sure all the rooms and every corner of the villa are clean and tidy. They have limited English but they are very friendly and warm, so it is a pleasure to have them around. Wayan is also a good driver and will sometimes be available to drive you into Ubud.</p><p>The gardeners are Nyoman and Kawi who are also from our village. They are responsible for keeping the lovely gardens clean, tidy and beautiful. The gardens are special, part of the attraction of the villa. As well as tending the many flowers and trees. Nyoman and Kawi grow some vegetables and fruit for the villa in our kitchen garden and orchard.</p><p>Gusti is in charge of security. A lovely, friendly man, he will make sure the villa is secure day and night. There is always someone on duty at the villa at night, patrolling the gardens and keeping everyone and everything safe.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>', '<p><strong>Rental Rates checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates are subject to change without prior notice.</li>	<li>Rates include Airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>Rates do not include baggage handling, gratuities, telephone and services extra charge&nbsp;on requests.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Payment</strong><br />To secure the villa, 50% non-refundable deposit is required once the booking is confirmed and the balance will be due 30 days prior to guest arrival. Incidental costs should be settled by the guests in local currency on check-out.</p><p><strong>Inventory</strong><br />Inventory will be agreed on arrival and departure.</p><p><strong>Family Plan</strong><br />Children under 12 years old sharing a room with parents with no extra bed are free of charge.<br />No adult triple share is permitted.</p><p><strong>Child policy</strong><br />We welcome children under the age of 18 as long as they accompanied by an adult guardian, but cannot assume any responsibility for their safety whilst on the property.</p><p><strong>Cancellation</strong><br />Cancellation of a booking at any time may result in forfeiture of deposits. Deposit will be refunded for a cancellation if we can re-booked the villa for the period of the initial booking. If only a portion of the rental time is re-booked, a pro-rated refund will be made. Any rental payments which qualify for a refund, whether in whole or pro-rated, will be subject to a deduction of a 20% administration fee.</p><p><strong>Travel Insurance</strong><br />With potential medical, liability, cancellation risks involved in holidays, travel insurance is important, as deposits and rental payments are not refundable after a reservation has been confirmed. We highly recommend to buy an all-inclusive travel insurance package which covers all your expenses if you need to cancel your holiday due to personal reasons or a world event.</p><p><strong>Liability</strong><br />The owners cannot accept any liability for any loss, expense, damage, claim or injury either directly or indirectly, consequential or otherwise whatsoever, however caused or incurred, whether arising in contract or otherwise in law or equity as a result of rendering of the services or accommodations as described or substituted, or by reason of terrorist or military action, riots, revolution, insurgency, civil war, adverse government action or inaction or acts of God, or by any agents, employees, subcontractors, servants or third parties whatsoever supplying any of the services or accommodations herein or as substituted.</p>', NULL, '115.26036900', '-8.47059500', 8, 4, 5, 9, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 07:59:36', '2016-09-23 11:16:08', NULL),
(17, 1, 'Villa Shamballa', 'villa-shamballa', 4, 0, '<p>For super romantic honeymoon ever, <strong>Villa Shamballa</strong> has everything what each couple may need. This is a perfect hideout to spend your passionate moment with the loved one. Situated in Payogan Village in Ubud, which is also known as place to do yoga, Villa Shamballa offers five-star hotel amenities blessed with the beauty of Ubud. Only takes one hour and fifteen minutes from Ngurah Rai Airport, it is not going to be long drive to reach this gorgeous place. Stunningly set in the middle of tropical forest, staying at Villa Shamballa offers the guest full romantic activities especially with the loved one.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Shamballa</strong> comes with unique architecture that you won’t fine at other villas. The one-bedroom villa gives you not just privacy but also makes you like king and queen in your own kingdom. The house villa is fully facilitated with fashionable comforts; the staffs are offered to cater all your needs and the convenience is in your hands.</p><p>There are two main parts in the villa: Ground Floor where you can spend nights in indoor living room equipped with TV and DVD/CD player, outdoor dining area by the infinity pool and the exclusive main bathroom featuring indoor bath and outdoor shower; and Upstairs that has superb view of Ubud jungle. Comes with spacious en-suite bedroom, living and dressing area, upstairs of Villa Shamballa could be your favorite spot to spend special moment during holiday. The bedroom is light and equipped with the finest furniture to support your sleep time. Best of this is that you can feel sunshine on your face when you wake up.</p><p>To satisfy the guests; then in Villa Shamballa there is also massage and spa service for 100% indulgent. Imagine relaxing by the poolside with fresh air blowing. For your entertainment, they can arrange Balinese music or dance in your dining time. Also enjoy the Balinese cooking lesson with their seasoned chef for different culinary experience during your vacation.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers roundtrip.</li>	<li>Welcome drink/chilled towel.</li>	<li>Welcome fruit basket.</li>	<li>Fresh tropical flower arrangements.</li>	<li>Complimentary breakfast daily.</li>	<li>Afternoon Tea with Balinese sweets daily.</li>	<li>Daily housekeeping and turn-down service.</li>	<li>The villa staff will arrange transport for tour to other areas for sightseeing with&nbsp;reliable contract drivers.</li>	<li>The villa provides in-house dining (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner).</li>	<li>Balinese masseuses are available for massage at the villa (surcharge).</li>	<li>Arrange traditional Balinese music and/or dance during dinner (extra cost).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: Private infinity swimming pool</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;Large bedroom (King Koil mattress size bed), 2 Indoor living rooms;&nbsp;Outdoor dining area;&nbsp;Wooden Deck;&nbsp;2 Bathrooms; Equipped Kitchen.</li>	<li>Entertainments: Flat screen TV and&nbsp;Satellite TV Channels;&nbsp;DVD player;&nbsp;CD player and Bose System; Bluetooth iPod dock.</li>	<li>Communications:&nbsp;Free WIFI</li>	<li>Espresso machine</li>	<li>&nbsp;Other facilities: Umbrellas;&nbsp;Handmade Batik cushions;&nbsp;Safety deposit box;&nbsp;Safety deposit box;&nbsp;Fine cotton bed linen;&nbsp;Yoga mats;&nbsp;extra bed on request.</li></ul><p><strong>Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Upstairs</strong></p><p>Overlooking the stunning jungle valley is a huge airy bedroom, living area, dressing room and ensuite. The bedroom and living area is the ideal place to relax and chill out. Enjoy reading over a cup of refreshing ginger tea and Balinese cake that our staff will gladly prepare for you. Surrounded by many tropical trees you have the sense of living in a tree house.</p><p>For your ultimate comfort the four-poster king size bed consists of top of the range mattress and pillows covered with crisp Egyptian cotton sheets. Chinese lamps and mosquito net create an exotic and colonial atmosphere respecting the fusion of beauty and classic charm with the subtleness of modern sophistication.</p><p>From this exclusive location, view the vista of the sunrise over the valley each morning as you wake.</p><p>The upstairs living area is furnished with a teak day bed, two sofas, a single chair with ottoman and a coffee table. Enjoy lounging back amongst the traditional batik cushions or use as an extra bedroom. Along with Coffee and Tea making facilities, Mini Fridge and Bluetooth iPod Dock for your comfort and convenience.</p><p><strong>Ground Floor</strong></p><p>An indoor living room equipped with a flat screen TV, DVD, Bose Bluetooth Speaker and CD player for your entertainment, outdoor dining area, wooden deck area by the infinity pool plus the main bathroom featuring outdoor bath and shower.</p><p>The outdoor dining area is the perfect spot for breakfast whilst enjoying the fresh morning air and dappled sunlight. In the evening indulge in a romantic candlelit dinner by the pool and listen for the traditional gamelan music that might travel across the valley.</p><p>The main bathroom is for pampering. Imagine soaking in a large terrazzo bathtub surrounded by candles, millions of stars shining above and the sound of bamboo leaves rustling in the balmy breeze. Luxuriate with our natural aromatherapy products and thick plush towels.</p>', '<h3><strong>Staffs Villa</strong></h3><p>The villa team consists of three full time staff members who will take care of food and beverage service, arrangements for tour and restaurant bookings, housekeeping and laundry requirements plus security.</p>', '<p><strong>Booking &amp; Reservations</strong></p><p>Reservations are subject to availability and confirmation by email.</p><p><strong>Rates, checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers, breakfast,&nbsp;other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>Rates are subjects 10% government tax, and 5.5% services.</li>	<li>Check-in time: 02:00 pm</li>	<li>Check-out time: 12:00 noon</li>	<li>Late check-out can be arranged at an additional cost of 30% of the normal room rate to secure the villa.</li></ul><p><strong>Villa Capacity</strong></p><p>Our nightly rate is for two guests.<br />However, we can accommodate a maximum of three adults or two adults and one child.<br />The villa provides one king size bed with an extra bed available upon request (US$45.00/night including breakfast)</p><p><strong>Payments</strong></p><p>To secure a booking a deposit of&nbsp;<u>50%</u>&nbsp;of the total rental amount must be received within&nbsp;<u>7 days</u>&nbsp;of the booking request.<br />Upon receiving the deposit, the management will issue a formal booking confirmation receipt.<br />If a deposit is not received within this time the booking will be cancelled.</p><p>Final payment of the balance shall be either paid 30 days prior to check-in or in cash at the villa on arrival.<br />All payments must be in USD.</p><p>Payment for a 50% deposit&nbsp; can be made by&nbsp;<u>bank deposit or Paypal.</u><br />(Bank details will be given after a booking is made)</p><p>*Payments by traveller’s cheque, credit card, other currencies are not accepted.<br />*US dollar notes 2003y , newer notes only)</p><p>In the case of last minute bookings, we can accept cash at the villa in full amount upon arrival at the villa. (No deposit needed due to the time constraint).</p><p><strong>Cancellation</strong></p><p>If the booking is cancelled&nbsp;<u>within 30 days</u>&nbsp;of the check-in date full payment will be non-refundable.<br />For cancellations made 31 days or more before the check-in date a full refund of the deposit will be made less $100 administration fee.</p><p><strong>Damage or Loss</strong></p><p>The villa management highly recommends our guests leave the property in good order. We shall charge our guests for any damages or losses incurred by any guest during their occupancy.</p><p><strong>Liability/Disclaimers</strong></p><p>The villa management highly recommends all of our guests take out a comprehensive travel insurance. We will not accept any responsibility for any injury, sickness, loss, damage and additional expense caused by the use of the property. Further, no responsibility is accepted for personal belongings. However, the villa management and staff will do our best to assist our guests as the safety of our guests is of utmost importance to us.</p><p><strong>Food &amp; Beverage Charges</strong></p><p>Your invoice for the expenses will be given when you check out. Please pay your Food &amp; Beverage and other expenses such as laundry in&nbsp;<u>IDR (Indonesian Rupiah).</u></p>', NULL, '115.25522850', '-8.47920620', 2, 1, 3, 3, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 08:04:57', '2016-09-24 14:57:36', NULL),
(18, 1, 'Villa Pantulan', 'villa-pantulan', 4, 1, '<p>In the quiet, unspoiled village of Lodtunduh, three kilometers south of Ubud, <strong>Villa Pantulan</strong> overlooks verdant rice fields and Mount Batukaru. From the moment our gates are opened, you enter a world of enchantment, seclusion and tranquility, far from the noisy, crowded beach hotels and busy roads of Bali.</p><p>The open environment of Villa Pantulan is an ever-changing scene depending on the season. The rice fields glimmer in shades of green and brown, and at sunset, when the sun descends behind the tree line, the frogs and crickets begin their nightly symphony and the mountain air brings a cool breeze.</p>', '<p>Pantulan means reflection in Indonesian.&nbsp;Villa Pantulan comprises four pavilions, an artists studio and a meditation/massage bale. All buildings have traditional alang alang roofs (thatched), wood and terrazzo floors. The five bedrooms, which sleep ten comfortably, have sliding louvered and glass doors that open up completely to allow the cool mountain air to circulate and all rooms have ceiling fans.</p><p>The villa is built around several water features including a reflecting pond, lily pond, swimming pool and a small bamboo forest waterfall. It is well suited for small weddings, a health/yoga retreat, or a corporate team seeking privacy and luxury.</p><p>We take great pride in the beauty of our home and have furnished it with many exquisite works of art both modern and antique. Great care has been taken to provide our guests with as many amenities as possible. Beautiful Balinese cotton kimonos and slippers are available for your comfort and to take home as a souvenir of Villa Pantulan.</p><p>Villa Pantulan is eco-friendly property. Our water is pumped from and underground well, which guarantess purity. All waste water an underground filtration system and all outdoor water features are recycled. The pool is salt-water treated&nbsp; and chlorination is kept to a minimum. we use only biodegradeable soaps and compost all our organic wastes. Each week all glass, plastic, metal and paper is recycled through a local recycling program&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Daily Breakfast and afternoon coffee or tea.</li>	<li>Daily shuttle bus to Ubud centre.</li>	<li>Consulting menus on request to&nbsp;a fully staffed kitchen who are trained in both Western and Asian cuisines, dietary menu as well in-house dining.</li>	<li>Assisting to cater to small wedding parties.</li></ul><p><strong>Optional Services</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>--- Applied cost ---</p><ul>	<li>Lunch &amp; Dinner, as well as cocktails, beer and wine at market price.</li>	<li>Sightseeing tours</li>	<li>Massage treatments</li>	<li>Cooking classes</li>	<li>Batik classes</li>	<li>Dance Events</li>	<li>Restaurant booking</li>	<li>Visit to coffee plantation</li>	<li>Visit to Balinese compound</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pool: 25m Swimming Pool.</li>	<li>Living areas: Five distinct bedrooms with air-conditioning and fan in three pavilions with&nbsp;five unique bathrooms;&nbsp;Living room with open views to swimming pool and rice fields;&nbsp;Sitting room with illuminated carved wall and views;&nbsp;Dining room adjacent to Buddha waterfall and garden;&nbsp;Fully equipped gourmet kitchen;&nbsp;Open office and library overlooking living area;&nbsp;Entertainment room.</li>	<li>Entertainments: Satellite TV;&nbsp;DVD, a Playstation;&nbsp;music system with&nbsp;200 DVDs, and CDs.</li>	<li>Communication:&nbsp;WiFi.</li>	<li>Other facilities: Pantulan Spa;&nbsp;Open&nbsp;secluded and eranquil Environment;&nbsp;Lotus pond with Koi fish;&nbsp;Reflecting pond with serene Buddha.</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p>The Pantulan Pavilion includes a living room, dining room, gourmet kitchen, library, entertainment room and bathroom. All spaces are connected by a soaring alang alang roof and walkways to each separate pavilion offering panoramic views to the rest of the house and the rice fields beyond.</p><p>Our gourmet kitchen is fully equipped to allow our staff to create memorable meals for your pleasure, offering both European and Balinese meals upon request. We also offer fine Australian wines, as well as a selection of beers and soft drinks. Breakfast is included in your package.</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - Dining Room</strong></p><p>The dining room is an extension of the kitchen dominated by a five meter mirbau wood table. Seating sixteen people comfortably, it overlooks the reflecting pond on one side and the bamboo waterfall on the other.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - Living Room</strong></p><p>The living room is open to the rice fields and the lotus pond. The comfortable terrazzo seating is covered in cushions decorated in navy and gray Balinese cotton. A small table situated on the rice field side gives splendid views in the morning while taking breakfast, or for playing games on a hot afternoon. Beside the table, a beautiful Javanese marriage bull and cart looks as if it were arriving from the sawah. Dominating the center wall is a stunning painting by local Bali resident Wolfgang Widmoser.</p><p>Above the living room, the library contains a PC and printer for your convenience. As of now, there is no internet connection available at Villa Pantulan. However, there are many excellent connections in Ubud, ten minutes away. It is also a comfortable place to read in privacy.</p><p>Our entertainment room includes a satellite television, DVD, music system and a Playstation. There are over 200 DVDs, as well as many CDs for your entertainment. Comfortably decorated in shades of green, the surround seating and futon mattress make it hard to leave this comfortable viewing room.</p><p>The bathroom conveniently situated next to the entertainment room is also used as a pool bathroom. Like all the bathrooms at Villa Pantulan, it has its own exterior garden.</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - The Lotus Pavilion</strong></p><p>The Lotus Pavilion is a two-story structure comprising sitting room, bedroom and bathroom. On the ground floor, a stunning wall carving depicting village life adorns the back wall. A small sofa, two chairs, a coffee table and a sofa table are covered in brown Balinese cotton. On the table and long benches are fine examples of Balinese glass and traditional wooden boat.</p><p>Upstairs, a large bedroom overlooks the rice field and swimming pool. A beautiful white stone Buddha head decorates the back of the bed, and delicate colored organza is lit from behind to cast a beautiful light on the bed at night. This is a truly romantic bedroom and as the sun sets, there is a magnificent view from this bedroom.</p><p>The bathroom includes a waterfall and a koi fish pond next to the outdoor shower. Two porcelain bowls sit on top of terrazzo counters and are well-lit by Italian light fixtures. A high wall, covered in fern and flowering plants, gives you complete privacy.</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - The Temple Garden Pavilion</strong></p><p>The Temple Garden Pavilion has two bedrooms, both decorated in shades of tropical green and deep sea blue. In each room, a queen size bed is surrounded by a white mosquito net emphasizing the dramatic bed linens, cushions and curtains made from Balinese cotton. The lower bedroom extends out to the Temple garden, koi pond and orchid garden. The upper bedroom offers splendid views of the rice field and an overall view of the house and orchid garden below.</p><p>The bathroom on the ground floor is a striking bamboo and white pebble garden designed around the outdoor shower. Two porcelain bowls set on terrazzo counters and Italian lighting fixtures make this a stunning bathroom.</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - The Rice Field Pavilion</strong></p><p>Behind the Lotus Pavilion, tucked away discretely behind the wall, is the Rice Field Pavilion. A two bedrooms structure decorated in shades of Irish green, Balinese red and black add dramatic flair to an already dramatic setting.</p><p>Each bedroom opens out onto a different view from a small wooden deck, on one side the Temple Garden and on the other, the rice fields. Each bedroom has a queen sized bed canopied in white mosquito net and a beautiful Balinese Ikat design. All beds are carefully lit from inside by beautiful Italian lamps. A small table and chair for writing postcards or letters and a mirror complete this room. On the walls, are drawings and paintings by local artists.</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - Artist Studio</strong></p><p>At the north end of the swimming pool is our Artists studio. A two level pavilion designed by Tony Gwilliam. Built on water, it is an ideal place to take tea and admire the rice fields on your doorstep. A small table rises from the middle of the floor Japanese style, enabling you to put your feet in the water on hot afternoons. Upstairs is an office space with a magnificent view of the mountains in the distance.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - Massage Bale</strong></p><p>At the south end of the pool is a massage/meditation bale. A single storey structure decorated with fine white cotton curtains for privacy. All massage therapists can be booked through our villa manager.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Villa Pantulan - Swimming Pool</strong></p><p>Beyond Pantulan Pavilion is the swimming pool. Built for laps, it is twenty-five meters long with an infinity edge flowing towards the rice fields.</p>', '<p>Villa Pantulan is a fully equipped, and fully staffed villa including housekeepers, cooks, gardeners, driver and security.</p>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of airport tranfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>Rates include&nbsp;subjects&nbsp;10% Government tax and 5.5% service charge.</li>	<li>Check-in time : 14.00 PM</li>	<li>Check-out time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Late Check Out is subject to availability&nbsp;</li>	<li>Charge for late check-out : 50% of room rate until 18.00 PM, One night of room rate after 18.00 PM</li>	<li>Villa Pantulan is not a self-catering villa.</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low season&nbsp;(min. stay 3 nights) : January 9th - June&nbsp;30th, September 16th - December 19th</li>	<li>High season&nbsp;(min. stay 7 nights) : July 1st - September 15th, December 20th - January 8th, CNY and Easter Week.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.26069600', '-8.53484200', 10, 5, 5, 10, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 08:09:11', '2016-09-22 16:36:09', NULL),
(19, 1, 'Villa Griya Aditi', 'villa-griya-aditi', 4, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Griya Aditi</strong>&nbsp;located in the friendly village of Tengkulak Kelod, near Ubud. Tengkulak is known for its craft of sculpted and painted ducks and other birds.&nbsp;Overlooking a landscape of rice fields and forest, you will find calm and relaxation, while you are only a short drive away from the cultural and artistic experience of Ubud and nearby villages.The Villa has been designed, built and is managed with the single purpose of your enjoying a wonderful and trouble free stay.&nbsp;</p><p>During the Villa opening ceremony held in December 2009. More than 200 members of the community participated in the ceremony in various roles. All the performers were from the local village. With Ubud lifestyle almost at your doorstep, you can enjoy the dances, arts, crafts, restaurants and nightlife. Tengkulak Kelod is an exceptional community, which can be branded as "Bali as it once was".</p><p>The Villas face more than 1 km uninterrupted rice fields, with a small temple on the right side. The only sounds you can hear are the ones of nature, traditional agricultural activities and the laughter of children.&nbsp;From time to time, you will be entertained by a procession of ducks going through the rice fields or by a flock of white birds.</p>', '<p>The owners are a French-Indonesian couple, an Indonesian woman.&nbsp;The mandate to the architects (<strong>Rick McBride</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Jeffrey Loh</strong>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<strong>Cita Duta Artistry</strong>&nbsp;in Jakarta and Bali) was to design a complex of 2 villas and a common facilities center, with modern traits which could become a part of the landscape and perfectly blend in its natural surroundings. They matched expectations and more.</p><p>The result is a combination of contemporary facilities and technology with touches of Bali''s traditions, arts and crafts present in every detail.Particular attention to material and colors - with extensive usage of Indonesia''s wood and natural stones. The color scheme was designed to give a sense of fusion with the surrounding landscape.</p><p>The Villa has been designed, built and is managed with the single purpose of your enjoying a wonderful and trouble free stay.&nbsp;</p><p>The villa manager will welcome you upon arrival. She will visit you during your stay to check whether everything goes fine. You also call on her in case of a difficulty or to arrange activities.</p><p>The villas are fitted with modern facilities, telephone connection to all rooms as well as to kitchens, the office and security post, wired and wireless broadband internet and cable TV.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast.</li>	<li>In-house laundry (dry clean at cost).</li>	<li>Free of charge using&nbsp;of 6-seats car with driver for 10 hours/day (exclude petrol).</li>	<li>Routine checking by Villa Manager and&nbsp;freely to contact&nbsp;by&nbsp;calling in case of a difficulty or to arrange activities.</li>	<li>24h stand by security.</li>	<li>English and French speaking guide can be arranged upon request (surcharge).</li>	<li>At the villa Bale private massage on call (extra charge).</li>	<li>Dance performances by local village troop can be arranged at a fee depending upon the type of performance requested by the guests (applied cost).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: tiled with natural stone.</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;an Air-conditioned 3 bedrooms villa with indoor showers/bathtub&nbsp;and outdoor shower at Master bedroom;&nbsp;living and dining area with fully equipped kitchen; and separate third building for office management plus garage.</li>	<li>Communications: Wireless Internet access; Telephone connection to all rooms as well as to kitchens, the office and security post.</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;&nbsp;a 30 kVA generator;&nbsp;The Bale Bengong.</li></ul><p><strong>Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Griya Aditi - The Villas</strong></p><p>Griya Aditi is a 3 bedrooms villa. The goddess Aditi is the goddess of wisdom and consciousness.</p><p>In Griya Aditi, you will find the dominant theme to be the story of the Ramayana, Sculptures and carvings depict several key figures and events in the Ramayana.</p><p><strong>Villa Griya Aditi - The Bedrooms</strong></p><p>Master bedroom faces the rice fields with the infinity swimming pool on the side. It has ensuite bathtub and outdoor shower. It also has a private garden area with a daybed. The 2 other bedrooms on ground floor face the swimming pool. Both have indoor showers</p><p><strong>Villa Griya Aditi - The Dining and Living Area</strong></p><p>The dining / living room (60 sq meters) faces south towards the swimming pool and rice fields. A family room (with TV) and games faces the back of the property.</p><p>All rooms have air conditioning and fan</p><p>The kitchen is used for final preparation of the dishes before serving. It has a refrigerator, a microwave oven, and a water dispenser.</p><p><strong>Others Facilities</strong></p><p>Bale is used for giving massages, thanks to an agreement with one group of traditional massage ladies</p><p>The third building houses a garage for 2 cars, the main kitchen, used for initial preparation of dishes, a separate area for storage of food, the laundry, an office for the villa manager and a bedroom used for staff, if they need to stay overnight. It is sometimes called "back of the house", in our case it is more like the "center of the house" The villas are fitted with modern facilities, telephone interconnection to all rooms as well as to kitchens, the office and security post, wireless broadband internet and cable TV.</p><p>We have ample electrical power to feed all the above and to keep the villas cool, and a 30 kVA generator for the occasional power cuts, which are part of the life, here.</p><p>Through an agreement with a local group of drivers, the villa provides 1 car per villa for the entire duration of the guests'' stay. Their cars are new generation Kijangs, comfortably seating up to 6 adults. Their knowledge of Bali, including the most remote and "off the beaten track" roads is exceptional.</p><p>Note about broadband internet : please remember that you are in Bali and nothing goes at light speed here, internet connection is not an exception. It is good enough to be on e-mail, browse the net or even do a video call through Skype, however, please do not expect to be able to play live video game over the net.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The villas'' staff consists of 11 people, they are 1 cook, 6 waiters and room attendants, 1 pool attendant and maintenance man, 1 gardener, and&nbsp;2 persons night watchmen.&nbsp;All recruited in the neighboring villages.</p>', '<p><b>Booking Terms</b></p><ul>	<li>Bookings more than 30 days before the commencement of the stay	<ul>		<li>Confirmation of booking : Down Payment 50 % of the amount for the whole stay.</li>		<li>Balance to be paid at the latest 21 days before the commencement of the stay. Failure to pay the balance when due may result in cancellation of the booking and forfeit of the down payment.</li>	</ul>	</li>	<li>Bookings less than 30 days before the commencement of the stay	<ul>		<li>Confirmation of booking : Full Payment 100 % of the amount for the whole stay.</li>	</ul>	</li></ul><p><strong>Rates, other Conditions, Checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary return airport transfer roundtrip), daily breakfast ( 2 persons per room), in-house laundry (dry clean at cost), free use of 6-seats car with driver (10 hours / day, 1 car per villa, exclude petrol) and using other villa facilities.</li>	<li>All rates are subject to 10% government tax and 5.5% service charge.</li>	<li>Cash payment in a currency other than Indonesian Rupiah will be at the rate published by Bank Internasional Indonesia.</li>	<li>Food for meals other than breakfast, prepared by our cook. Actual expenses charged plus a handling fee of 20%</li>	<li>Telephone calls (long distance) made from the villas will be charged as per Telkom fees plus 20% handling fee.</li>	<li>Outside services, including special laundry requests and dry cleaning, charged at cost +20% handling fee</li>	<li>Every villa deserves a 6-seats car with driver for up to&nbsp;10 hours/day,&nbsp;exclude petrol.</li>	<li>Additional car(s) with driver, charged at USD 70 / day, for 10 hours per day, inclusive of fuel</li>	<li>Check-in time : 14.00PM</li>	<li>Check-out time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check-out : 50% of room rate until 18.00hrs, One night of room rate after 18.00hrs</li>	<li>Late check-out subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>From 1st September till 16th December 2016 - Low Season</li>	<li>From 17th December 2016 till 4th January 2017 - High Season</li>	<li>From 5th January till 26th January 2017 - Low Season</li>	<li>From 27th January till 3rd February 2017 - High Season</li>	<li>From 4th February till 30th June 2017 - Low Season</li>	<li>From 1st July till 31st August 2017 - High Season</li></ul>', NULL, '115.28277040', '-8.54057860', 6, 3, 5, 11, NULL, 6, '2016-09-13 08:31:19', '2016-09-23 11:10:26', NULL);
