resolved finally by arbitration in the English language.</p><p>By making its booking request, the Guest agrees that these terms and conditions have been read, understood and have been accepted and agreed to by the Guest without reservation and without exception.</p><p>If any of the conditions of this Rental Contract are or become or are deemed to be invalid, or if there is any omission from any terms and conditions, the remaining terms and conditions will remain valid and enforceable and cannot be contested.</p><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 2 Nights) : Jan 9th to June 30th, 16 sep - 19 Dec, excluded Easter period and Chinese New Year&nbsp;</li>	<li>High Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 5 Nights) : July 1st to September 15th, Easter period (30 March - 4 april 2013) and Chinese New Year (29 Jan - 4 Feb, 2013)</li>	<li>Peak Season&nbsp;(Min. Stay 7 Nights) : December 20th to January 8th</li></ul>', NULL, '115.15288130', '-8.68544870', 8, 4, 2, NULL, NULL, 3, '2016-09-14 11:16:50', '2016-09-27 08:33:52', NULL),
(27, 1, 'Villa Karang Kembar 3', 'villa-karang-kembar-3', 6, 1, '<p><strong>Villa Karang Kembar 3</strong>&nbsp;is a home with a view that you will never forget. A home to where you will always look forward to returning. Lose yourself in the tranquil and soothing character of our cliff top Villa, set in a secluded but prestigious area near the traditional Balinese village of Kutuh, Ungasan. Enjoy the warm sea breezes, breathtaking sunrises and, quite simply, one of Bali''s most spectacular panoramic ocean views.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Karang Kembar 3</strong> is located in the Karang Kembar Estate, an exclusive gated community within a 30-minute drive from Bali''s international airport. Secluded yet accessible means our Villa is the perfect location for anyone looking for a get-away-from-it-all, luxurious private sanctuary but still wants to enjoy Bali''s many attractions, entertainment and dining options.</p><p>The elegant two-storey, four-bedroom Villa has been created to maximize the stunning ocean views from almost every available angle. The architectural and interior design of the Villa is a contemporary Balinese style and features a traditional roof design and construction. It is decorated with high quality furnishings, art, and artefacts made in Bali by local artists and craftsmen. However, the Villa also features state-of-the-art technology including a Nakamichi Hi-Fi system with iPhone/iPod input, BOSE home entertainment centre, Sony PlayStation, more than 100 channels satellite TV and wireless broadband connectivity throughout the property.</p><p>Karang Kembar 3 guests have access to a private Beach Club on the unspoiled Kutuh Beach, a 5-minute drive from the Villa, where guests can to take full advantages of the Club''s facilities, including a private plunge pool overlooking the beach. Karang Kembar 3 is perfect for special events; weddings, reunions, birthday parties, private barbeques or just a relaxing place to meet with friends. Whatever the occasion, Karang Kembar 3 is your private sanctuary on the Island of the Gods.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Airport transfer: pick up and drop off</li>	<li>Welcome drink and cold towel upon arrival</li>	<li>Welcome fruit basket upon arrival</li>	<li>Serving&nbsp;daily breakfast</li>	<li>24 hour security</li>	<li>Chef provides service on request for lunchies and dinners.</li>	<li>In-house laundry (dry-clean can be arranged).</li>	<li>Baby sitting service on request (additional fee).</li>	<li>Daily housekeeping.</li>	<li>In-villa spa treatments (surcharge).</li>	<li>Fully attending staff from 7 am to 10 pm.</li>	<li>A seven-seater car and driver for 8 consecutive hours per day per each night stay (not including petrol, entrance fee and parking fee). The car will have a full tank of petrol on arrival, and the guest is required to refill during the stay. Thereafter the car will be charged with extra cost.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: 15 metre T-shape infinity pool and sun deck.</li>	<li>Living areas: Fully air-conditioned bedrooms with individual temperature control;&nbsp;Extensive open living and dining areas;&nbsp;Fully equipped kitchen (gas stove, refrigerator, oven, cooker hood, microwave, coffee maker, juicer, toaster, blender, water dispenser, etc).</li>	<li>Communication:&nbsp;WI-FI internet connection</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;LCD multi-channel TV;&nbsp;BOSE AV 321 II GSX media center;&nbsp;Hi-Fi system with&nbsp;iPhone/iPod input;&nbsp;Sony PlayStation game console.</li>	<li>Other facilities: Safe deposit box in each room;&nbsp;Barbeque facilities; Day gazebo on the edge of the cliff overlooking the Indian Ocean;&nbsp;Extra beds (extra&nbsp;cost).&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Accommodation - Bali Seaview Villa</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Karang Kembar&nbsp;</strong>located in Jimbaran Hills, has four bedrooms that sleep up to eight people, all with private bathrooms and panoramic ocean views. The Villa features a family living/media room, private massage facilities, spacious public living and dining areas, an infinity edge swimming pool (T-Shape Pool) overlooking the Indian Ocean, day gazebo and a fully-equipped, contemporary western kitchen, all supported by state-of-the-art fixtures, fittings and appliances. Smoking is not allowed in any of the villa''s rooms.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Master Bedroom 1</strong></p><p>This spacious Master Bedroom is located on the Ground Floor. It overlooks the ocean and faces the infinity-edge swimming pool allowing guests to embrace the sunrise and ocean breezes from the moment they wake. The room features a large en-suite bathroom; walk-in closet and private outside massage and shower area.&nbsp;<br />As with all the bedrooms, the contemporary interior design is complimented by elegant furniture, furnishings and art that result in a warm, enticing and extremely stylish feel to the room. The spacious en-suite bathroom features a deep oval shaped soaking tub and indoor and outdoor showers.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Massage Terrace</strong></p><p>The Villa’s ambiance makes it the perfect place to experience the traditional spa and massage treatments for which Bali is renowned. The Massage Terrace, adjacent to the ground floor Master Bedroom offers a perfect sanctuary to indulge and pamper yourself. A trained therapist will assist you to select from a range of massages or treatments.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Master Bedroom 2</strong></p><p>Positioned on the First Floor, the second Master Bedroom is the perfect space for couples. The room is reached from one of the Villa''s architectural features, a spiraling ramp that replaces a traditional staircase to reach the split-level second floor.The room features large glass doors and windows on 2 sides that provide access to a wrap around balcony and offers outstanding, uninterrupted views of the Indian Ocean, the rugged seascape and the Villas lush tropical gardens. A sunrise seen from this room is an experience that you are unlikely to forget.&nbsp;<br />The essence of this room is Balinese minimalist-elegance. It is well appointed and fully equipped with a walk-in closet and en-suite bathroom featuring an oversized soaking bathtub and rain shower. The art in the room, which adds to its sense of style, includes a seascape of local fishermen on the beach that can be seen from the balcony.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Guest Bedroom 3</strong></p><p>Located on the upper level of the First Floor, this bedroom and private bathroom is designed to create a warm and relaxing ambience and features contemporary décor in a rustic style, complimented by original paintings by local artists and high quality finishings. The floor-to-ceiling windows offer great views of the Indian Ocean, the Villa and its surroundings.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Guest Bedroom 4</strong></p><p>Designed with kids in mind, this room can either be set up with twin beds or a king-sized double bed. Like all the Villa’s bedrooms, the floor-to-ceiling windows offer great views of the Indian Ocean, the Villa and its surroundings but all doors and windows can be locked for added safety. The room and its private bathroom has a fun and relaxed feel to it but as it is elegantly appointed with quality furnishings, it is the perfect home-from-home for the young, young at heart or anyone else for that matter.</p><p><strong>Family Living/Media Room</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Karang Kembar</strong>&nbsp;is the best&nbsp;<strong>family accommodation in Jimbaran</strong>, because the facilities in this Villa is suitable for family activities. The Family Living/Media Roomis a perfect space for reading, playing or just hanging out together. A home entertainment centre, video game console, LCD multi-channel TV and a selection of traditional board games make this comfortable room the Villa’s entertainment hub. A wide array of video games, DVD movies, and books are available for your enjoyment.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Central Pavilion</strong></p><p>The formal dining area and the main Living Room are located in the Central Pavilion. This large room with direct access to the pool features a high traditional roof and spectacular Nusa Dua seaview. The villa''s room is adjacent to the modern, western style kitchen that provides all mod cons, including a built-in coffee/espresso maker, breakfast bar and a covered alfresco dining area. A Chef is available to prepare a selection of local and international dishes from the available menu for breakfast, lunch or dinner, including a number of kid’s favourites.&nbsp;<br /><br />Meals can be enjoyed indoors and outdoors, formal or relaxed by the pool or in the day gazebo. The choice is yours. A romantic candle light dinner by the pool and under the moonlight and stars in the southern sky can also be arranged. All you need to do is ask</p>', '<p>The Villa staffs are friendly, they speak English and are trained in providing personalized service to discerning guests. The Villa Manager and the team are available as little or as much as you need them. If you cannot find what you are looking for in Bali, you can be sure that they can.&nbsp;</p><p>The team consists of&nbsp;a villa manager, a chef, a gardener/pool attendant, a housekeeper, a security and a driver.</p>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers roundtrip, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The Villa sleeps up to eight persons.</li>	<li>Grocery bills pay market price by guests plus 20% handling fee.</li>	<li>Check-in time is after 2:00 p.m., with checkout by 12 noon on the day of departure.</li>	<li>Late checkout is possible at extra cost, depending on availability.</li>	<li>Rates include the cost of electricity, water, and supplies of cleaning, gardening and toiletries.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Rates do not include gratuities for staff.</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low Season&nbsp;(min. stay 3 nights) : 16 January - 30 June (excluding Easter and Chinese New Year weeks), 16 September - 19 December</li>	<li>High Season&nbsp;(min. stay 5 nights) : 6st - 13th February (Chinese New Year), 23rd March - 7 April (Easter week), 1st – 31st July and 1st – 15th September</li>	<li>Peak Season&nbsp;(min. stay 7 nights) : 1st – 31st August, 20th December – 15th January</li></ul><p><strong>Payment</strong></p><ul>	<li>A deposit of 50% of the full rental must be received into the account stated on the invoice within five working days of the invoice date. If the deposit is not received in a timely basis, the booking may be cancelled at the owner''s discretion</li>	<li>Final payment is required 45 days prior to arrival (60 days for Peak Season reservations) or together with the reservation form and deposit if booked less than 45 days prior to arrival (60 days for Peak Season reservations)</li>	<li>Payments are to be made by bank transfer and all bank charges are to be borne by the renter</li>	<li>Failure to receive the final payment on a timely basis may result in the reservation being cancelled at the owner''s discretion</li>	<li><em><strong>All deposits and final payments are non-refundable.</strong></em>&nbsp;A guest may request a change of date after having paid the deposit but the new dates must be in the same calendar year as the original booking. Any amendments to a<i>&nbsp;</i>reservation&nbsp;will be subject to availability and at the owners discretion&nbsp;</li>	<li>All incidental charges such as food and beverages, in-house spa treatments, extra car hire, etc., must be paid on check out in Indonesian Rupiah</li></ul><p><strong>Insurance</strong></p><p>The Villa’s insurance expressly does not cover the personal effects of guests or ill health or injuries sustained while staying at the Villa. Guests are responsible for any insurance that they might require while staying at the Villa or while holidaying in Bali.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Responsibility</strong></p><p>The owner is not responsible for any injury, illness, loss, damage, extra cost,&nbsp;or any inconvenience caused while staying at Karang Kembar 3 or while using the facilities provided, including the Beach Club and provided transportation, and will not be responsible for any cost arising from loss or damage to private belongings, vehicles, or other property brought into the Villa by guests.</p><p><strong>Damage and Losses</strong></p><p>On departing Karang Kembar 3, guests are expected to leave it in the condition in which they found it. The owner reserves the right to charge for any damage caused to the Villa, or any fixtures, fittings, furnishings or art, which arises during a stay that is a consequence of a guest’s actions or for any loss that is incurred as a result of such actions.&nbsp;The Villa owner has the right to immediately reclaim the property if guests causes extreme damage, annoyance or undertakes any activity or action that is inconsistent with the laws of the Republic of Indonesia.</p>', NULL, '115.18197840', '-8.84290470', 8, 4, 4, 6, NULL, 5, '2016-09-14 13:39:31', '2016-09-22 21:17:48', NULL);
