(31, 1, 'Villa Ambra at Pantai Lima', 'villa-ambra-at-pantai-lima', 2, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Ambra</strong>&nbsp;is an ideal mix of Antique Java and Modern styles. Adding to its appeal is 45 metres of private beachfront. Villa Ambra is a luxury villa right on the beach at Pererenan, a small Balinese community about approx 20 minutes drive from Seminyak, the entre of Bali''s sophisticated shopping, restaurants and nightlife. The world famous Nirwana Golf Course at Tanah Lot is 3.5km to the north west. Villa Ambra is one of five individually architecturally designed, 5- and 6-bedroom&nbsp;<strong>villas in the Pantai Lima estate</strong>. Each villa offers complete privacy and serenity, is truly spacious, and has vast tropical gardens. All of Villa Ambra''s five bedrooms have sea views.</p><p>The farming families who plant, nurture, and harvest the ricefields, and the fishermen who take to the sea according to the wind and the currents are part of the Villa Ambra experience. They often perform religious ceremonies on the beach in front of the villa.</p><p>Coming and going to the villa, you will see the current phase in rice cultivation, and if you walk up the beach a couple of hundred metres, you can enjoy watching the fishermen putting to sea, or returning with their catch.<br />Guests quickly respond to the natural rhythms of dawn and dusk, and the ebb and flow of the tides. The cares and pressures of city life seem to melt away and are swiftly replaced with serene relaxation. A welcome opportunity to recharge and renew body and spirit.</p>', '<section id="main"><article id="theContent"><p>Villa Ambra has 45 metres of beach frontage, and each of its five bedrooms has expansive and unimpeded sea views. A unique ambience that combines total relaxation with utter luxury and &nbsp;comfort.</p><p>Living areas are beautifully aligned to the beach, the sea and the sky. There really is room to move and to breath in the sea air, and the fantastic staff ensure that our guests lack nothing</p><p>All five bedrooms have ocean views and are each completely different in design and ambience. Each has its own en-suite bathroom, individually designed and furnished. There is a large sitting room on the ground floor and another upstairs. Both are open to sea breezes. The dining room, which seats ten, is air-conditioned, but has French doors which can be flung open instead. There is a home cinema with high definition projector and wide screen. Expansive gardens and lawn extend right to the beach.</p><p>The beach frontage is 45 metres.&nbsp;You simply step off the grass and on to the sand.&nbsp;There are two interconnected pools.&nbsp;The larger infinity pool totals 100 square metres, while the children’s pool is 21 square metres and only 60 cm deep. You can enjoy the garden jacuzzi which is large enough for eight adults. There are very comfortable lounging and dining areas right at the edge of the beach, as well as a shady bale to relax in. Both provide unobstructed ocean and sunset views.</p></article><nav>&nbsp;</nav></section><footer id="mainFooter">&nbsp;</footer>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Airport transfers: pick up and drop off.</li>	<li>Welcome drink and chilled towel upon arrival.</li>	<li>Complimentary use of a car and driver for up to 10 consecutive hours a day for 6 days/week&nbsp;(exclude fuel).</li>	<li>Butler service, who acts as major domo and concierge, also manages villa&nbsp;household staff.</li>	<li>Staffs are unobtrusive and discreet, but ever friendly and helpful.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Reasonable laundry requirements are handled free of charge. Fine items and dry cleaning are sent out and charged at cost.</li>	<li>French executive chef helps you choose your menus, and oversees your own sous chefs and kitchen staff.</li>	<li>Local Balinese nannies are excellent and can be sourced at cost.</li>	<li>Spa – excellent practitioners can be brought in at cost to provide a full range of services at a fraction of what would be charged in a 5-star hotel.</li>	<li>Arranging in-house&nbsp;Yoga teacher (surcharge).</li>	<li>Serving and arranging events for weddings, friends reunions, family gatherings and etc.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools: an&nbsp;infinity pool&nbsp;20m x 5m (100 square metres);&nbsp;a children pool 21 m2 with&nbsp;60 cm deepth; Jacuzzi (for 8 adults).</li>	<li>Living areas: a 5 air-conditioned double bedrooms ocean view with&nbsp;king- and queen-sized beds, and ensuite bathroom with&nbsp;bathtubs/showers; living and dining area along fully equipped kitchen.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;37 inch LCD television screen with satellite tv programming;&nbsp;DVD and Bose sound system;&nbsp;iPod dock (connected to speakers throughout the villa and the garden);&nbsp;Private cinema with large selection of DVDs;&nbsp;Library well stocked with books, games, and jigsaw puzzles;&nbsp;kites;&nbsp;fishing rods.</li>	<li>Communications:&nbsp;unlimited WiFi satellite broadband (up to 6 Mbps); ISD capable telephone;&nbsp;iMac with printer.</li>	<li>Sports: Gym; Mountain bikes;&nbsp;Tennis court (shared).</li>	<li>Other facilities: drinkable filtered tap water &amp; sparkling mineral water; generator;&nbsp;</li>	<li>2<em>&nbsp;</em>personal 8-seater MPVs (purchased new in 2013 and 2014 with electric sliding doors), and drivers for up to 10 continuous hours six days a week each (exclude petrol).</li>	<li>Spacious rooms and gardens are&nbsp;an ideal venue for that special event - a wedding, an anniversary, a birthday celebration, or just a great party.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Staffs</strong></p><p>Villa Ambra has 19 wonderful staff, with 365/24 attendance, including a Villa Manager, Head and Under-Butlers, Cooks, Helpers, Engineers etc.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checking in &nbsp;and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer</li>	<li>All rates are subject to an additional 10.5% government tax and 5% service charge.&nbsp;Rates are subject to change without notice, but changes will not be applied to bookings already made.</li>	<li>Food and beverages are charged at cost, with the addition of a 15% handling fee.</li>	<li>Additional hours and/or complimentary&nbsp;vehicles can be arranged at pre-agreed cost.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : check-out time is noon unless a variation has been agreed, which may incur a further charge.</li>	<li>Villa Ambra cannot change the beds or supply extra beds, except insofar as a cot for an infant can be placed in one of the bedrooms.</li>	<li>There is no pre-determined limit on the number of children within the party, and consider rental requests on an individual basis.</li>	<li>There is no lifeguard, nor are they fenced, and use of the pools, and indeed all villa facilities, is entirely at guests’ own risk and responsibility.</li>	<li>A deposit of 50% of the rental due must be received by Villa Ambra within seven working days after confirmation of the reservation, except that, if there are less than 31 days before the rental start date, full payment is required.</li>	<li>For last minute bookings within seven working days of the rental start date, full payment on arrival is acceptable.</li>	<li>In the event of cancellation 31 days or more prior to the rental start date, a refund of the deposit will be granted net of any agent’s commission and a cancellation charge of 20% of the total rental value.&nbsp; In the event of a cancellation 30 days or less prior to the rental start date, no refund will be granted. Guests are reminded to check that they have adequate cancellation insurance.</li>	<li>Subject to availability, we will be happy to make changes without charge, if the total rental value is not reduced.</li>	<li>Special permission is required for functions where the number of guests exceeds 15. A function fee may be applicable in addition to a local community (“Banjar”) fee and security deposit. We can recommend an excellent European party planner. Since our roofs are thatched,&nbsp;<em>no fireworks are permitted</em>.</li>	<li>Guests are expected to respect the peace of their neighbours at all times. No outdoor, or loud indoor, music is permitted after midnight. This stricture has been agreed with the local Balinese communities and is not open to negotiation.</li>	<li>Guests should be aware that Villa Ambra is furnished and equipped to a high standard and seemingly minor damages may prove surprisingly expensive. The renter is responsible for, and undertakes to reimburse, any and all damages or losses incurred during his occupation of the villa. The Villa Manager reserves the right to eject the occupants in the event of excessive damage or unruly behaviour.</li>	<li>The number of persons occupying the villa must not exceed the maximum number stated in the booking confirmation and the villa owner reserves the right to refuse any booking which he considers unsuitable.</li>	<li>The villa owner will not accept any responsibility for any injury, sickness, loss, damage, additional expense or inconvenience caused directly or indirectly by or arising from the use of the villa, plumbing, gas, electrical or otherwise, or weather conditions or other natural events. The villa owner will not accept any responsibility for any missed travel connections, however caused, nor is any responsibility accepted for any loss of or damage to the personal property of the renter or any member of the party, however caused.</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low season 2016: 1 Sep - 19 Dec</li>	<li>Peak season 2016 - 2017: 20 Dec - 8 Jan</li>	<li>Low season 2017: 9&nbsp;Jan - 26 Jan</li>	<li>High season 2017: 27 Jan - 2 Feb</li>	<li>Low season 2017: 3 Feb - 14 Apr</li>	<li>High season 2017: 15 Apr - 22 Apr</li>	<li>Low season 2017: 23 Apr - 15 Jun</li>	<li>High season 2017: 16 Jun - 31 Jul</li>	<li>Peak season 2017: 1 - 31 Aug</li></ul>', NULL, '115.11797270', '-8.64904600', 10, 5, 1, 19, NULL, 7, '2016-09-14 20:20:58', '2016-09-23 11:20:33', NULL),
(32, 1, 'Villa Melissa at Pantai Lima', 'villa-melissa-at-pantai-lima', 2, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Melissa</strong>&nbsp;is part of Pantai Lima complex villas, a luxury villa right on the beach at Pererenan, a small Balinese community about approx 20 minutes drive from Seminyak, the centre of Bali''s sophisticated shopping, restaurants and nightlife. The world famous Nirwana Golf Course at Tanah Lot is 3.5km to the north west. Villa Melissa is one of five individually architecturally designed, 5- and 6-bedroom villas in the Pantai Lima estate. Each villa offers complete privacy and serenity, is truly spacious, and has vast tropical gardens. Three of Villa Melissa''s five bedrooms have ocean views.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Melisa</strong> at Pantai Lima has located on the volcanic beach of Pererenan on the south west coast of Bali, Villa Melissa is conveniently located for those who want to experience the many facets of Bali. Only 25 minutes away from the shopping, world class restaurants and nightlife of Seminyak, an hour from the cultural capital and the jungles of Ubud and only 15 minutes away from the sunset splendour of Tanah Lot temple.</p><p>Bali’s Pantai Lima estate comprises five super-luxury, completely private villas. Four have five double bedrooms, the other has six. The property is truly spacious, extending over 1.6 hectares, or four acres. That’s about the size of two football fields. Individual gardens range from 2250 to 3270 square metres (24,220 to 35,200 square feet) and the villas themselves all exceed 800 square metres of floor area (8,600 square feet.) Four of the villas are right on the water’s edge, while the fifth is set back against the rice fields with the river at its side and a short boardwalk to the beach.</p><p>Villa Melissa, with its spacious rooms and gardens is an ideal venue for that special event - a wedding, an anniversary, a birthday celebration, or just a great party.&nbsp;There''s more than enough room to seat up to 60 guests for a sit-down dinner. Up to 200 can enjoy cocktails and canapes.&nbsp;</p><p>For corporate events, such as a weekend off-site or MICE for top-performers, Villa Melissa makes sense.&nbsp;Because of Villa Melissa''s relationship with Pantai Lima, an estate of adjoining super luxury villas, there are a total of 26 double bedrooms available, as well as a large seminar room with the very latest in High Definition projector systems.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Airport Transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and towel refreshment once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast.</li>	<li>Complimentary a car &amp; driver for 10&nbsp;continuous hours a day &amp; 6 days/week, exclusive of petrol.</li>	<li>A group 5 star chefs&nbsp;provide an eclectic menu selection melding classic cooking, nouvelle cuisine, as well as Indonesian/Asian fusion food.</li>	<li>Friendly and helpful staffs.</li>	<li>Butler, who acts as major domo and concierge, also manages your household staff.</li>	<li>Highly-trained and unobtrusive security guards on duty round the clock.</li>	<li>A full laundry service is provided&nbsp;(dry cleaning extra cost).</li>	<li>Kecak dance performs 300 dancers&nbsp;(once upon request - at price)</li>	<li>Therapist by call (surcharge)</li>	<li>Personal Traineer &amp; Yoga teacher (applied&nbsp;cost)</li>	<li>Surf instructors (fee negoitable directly)</li>	<li>Serving and arranging events&nbsp;to seat up to 60 guests for a sit-down dinner, or&nbsp;up to 200 attendees&nbsp;can enjoy cocktails and canapes.</li></ul>', '<article id="post-43"><article id="post-45"><p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool:&nbsp;&nbsp;two chlorine free pools, an infinity 20 meter pool perfect for relaxing and fitness, and another shallow pool ideal for toddlers and infants.</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;a 5 air-conditioned double bedrooms with king-, queen, and prince-sized beds, with each has an en-suite bathroom with bathtub as well as shower (3&nb