(36, 1, 'Villa Saba', 'villa-saba', 2, 0, '<p><strong>SABA</strong>&nbsp;is a cleverly designed complex of five, luxurious, self-contained villas, four with two bedrooms, one with one bedroom, and each with a private entrance, a private swimming pool, and interconnecting garden doors. Each property can therefore be linked or remain totally separate and private, presenting guests with a choice of any combination from a one-bedroom to a nine-bedroom renting option.&nbsp;</p><p>Furthermore, SABA offers guests the choice of different levels of service, ranging from completely private, self contained living, up to the luxurious option of being fully pampered with chefs, butlers and a comprehensive menu of services.</p>', '<p>SABA&nbsp;embraces seclusion, relaxation and comfort within a tranquil setting surrounded by rice paddies in the village of Berawa on Bali''s southwest coast, less than 10 minutes from the bustling heart of trendy Seminyak.&nbsp;The name&nbsp;SABA&nbsp;appropriately means "a place frequented" or "a meeting place" in Sanskrit, the originating language for Balinese.&nbsp;</p><p>This beautiful setting offers the double attraction of being relatively close to everything that guests might need, while also offering visitors a privileged insight into the traditions of rural Bali. Cows are herded through the fields, the sound of ritual music is carried on the breeze, and guests can witness the farmers hand-ploughing the fields or harvesting the rice.&nbsp;</p><p>Designed by internationally-renowned architect, Ross Franklin, the contemporary styled properties feature large bedrooms, garden bathrooms, open air living and dining pavilions, well equipped kitchens, swimming pools, gorgeous tropical gardens, sculptures, commissioned artwork, water features, cable TVs and DVD players, as well as WiFi internet access throughout.</p><p>All five villas are situated around a private, central courtyard with parking facilities for up to five cars, and a 24-hour staffed, service area with a fully equipped service kitchen and laundry, plus power back-up generator.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast and afternoon tea during stay at the villa.</li>	<li>Free access to Canggu Club.</li>	<li>No charge using bicycles.</li>	<li>Gratis shuttle bus to local area.</li>	<li>Personal chef and two cooks&nbsp;prepare complimentary daily breakfast, plus lunch and dinner choices from an extensive and competitively priced menu.</li>	<li>Butlers are able to prepare snacks, giving 24-hour room service.</li>	<li>In-house SPA by fully trained theraphist (extra charge).</li>	<li>Arranging a car included&nbsp;driver at negoitable price.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools:&nbsp;Five&nbsp;pools of between 8 and 15 metres in length.</li>	<li>Living Areas:&nbsp;Open-sided lounge and dining areas with well-equipped kitchenettes in three villas; air-conditioned dining rooms and open-air lounge pavilions in two villas. All villas offer either garden&nbsp;balé&nbsp;pavilions or pool decks with sun loungers.</li>	<li>Communication:&nbsp;WiFi internet access; laptop and printer for guest use; mobile phone coverage.</li>	<li>Entertainment:&nbsp;Satellite TV; DVD player; hard drive media player; iPod dock and speakers (loaded iPod on request).</li>	<li>For families:&nbsp;Saba is exceptionally well equipped for families. Facilities include: baby cot; high chair; booster seat; DVDs; games; pool safety fence (on request at extra cost).</li>	<li>Transport:&nbsp;The villa provides a twice-daily shuttle to Seminyak and the Canggu Club (drop off only). Alternatively, the villa staff may call one of Bali’s safe and reasonably priced metered taxis, or arrange for car and driver hire (24 hours notice required, additional cost).</li>	<li>Area for weddings &amp; events&nbsp;for up to 50 people (seated) can be held at Saba when the villas are jointly rented.</li>	<li>A car and driver is available on request and may be arranged at a special discounted rate</li>	<li>Additional Facilities:&nbsp;Barbecue; back-up generator; safety deposit box; massage beds; mountain bikes.</li>	<li>Canggu Club Facilities: more information &nbsp;<a href="http://www.cangguclub.com/">www.cangguclub.com</a></li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Description</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Arjuna - 1 Bedroom Villa</strong></p><p>Intimate but bright and airy, 1-bedroom Villa Arjuna comprises an open-sided living and dining pavilion complemented by a well-equipped kitchenette, separated by antique double doors from the spacious bedroom. An ensuite garden bathroom gives direct access to the 8-metre pool set within the villa’s private garden. This tasteful villa is ideal for a honeymoon couple.</p><p><strong>Villa Yudhistira &amp; Villa Bima - 2 Bedrooms Villa</strong></p><p>As well as its two spacious ensuite bedrooms, Villa Yudhistira features a large air-conditioned dining room and integrated, well-equipped, modern kitchen. Connected to the dining room via a covered walkway is the beautiful, open-sided living pavilion. The living pavilion is positioned beside the 15-metre pool set within the well-tended tropical gardens. At the far end of the pool is a shady, comfortable&nbsp;<em>bale</em>.</p><p>A large, sliding wall panel separates Yudhistira from the other master villa, Bima. Guests who book both villas can request the staff to open the wall panel to provide a huge garden area with the two swimming pools – ideal for family groups requiring four bedrooms and plenty of space for the children to have fun. This open set-up also lends itself to weddings and birthday parties.</p><p>The Villa Complex:&nbsp;Five&nbsp;private, self-contained but adjoining villas comprising 4 x 2-bedroom villas; 1 x 1-bedroom villa.</p><p><strong>Villa Nakula &amp; Villa Sadewa - 2 Bedrooms Villa</strong></p><p>As well as two spacious ensuite bedrooms, Villa Nakula has a large open-air living/dining area, complemented by a separate, fully equipped kitchen. A 13-metre pool with a timber deck is set within a lovely tropical garden.</p><p>A large, sliding wall panel next to the pool separates Villa Nakula from two-bedroom Villa Sadewa. Guests who book both villas can request the staff to open the wall panel to provide a joined garden area with the two swimming pools – ideal for family groups requiring four bedrooms and space for the children to have fun.</p><p><strong>Connecting Villas</strong></p><dl></dl><p>This wonderfully adaptable five-villa complex meets the demands of every holidaymaker – from solo traveller to party of 18, with bedroom options ranging from one (the intimate Villa Arjuna) to nine (all five villas).</p><p>The ingenious sliding wall panels between each villa effectively open up the gardens to create one property and a sense of shared space, but slide back to embrace each villa in its own peaceful tropical garden when privacy is preferred.</p><p>1 bedroom – Arjuna<br />2 bedrooms – Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />3 bedrooms – Arjuna and Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />4 bedrooms – Any two of Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />5 bedrooms – Arjuna and any two of Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />6 bedrooms – Any three of Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />7 bedrooms – Arjuna and any three of Yudhistira OR Bima OR Nakula OR Sadewa<br />8 bedrooms – Yudhistira, Bima, Nakula and Sadewa<br />9 bedrooms – Arjuna, Yudhistira, Bima, Nakula and Sadewa</p><p>This floor plan shows the position of each villa in relation to the others.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Villa Manager</li>	<li>Chef</li>	<li>Butlers</li>	<li>Garden and pool attendant</li>	<li>Maintenance</li>	<li>Security</li>	<li>Driver</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checkin in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates includes Airport transfer, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>Rates are subject 10.5% Tax and 5% service charge.</li>	<li>Grocery bills plus 15% handling fee.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;subject to availability</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low season:&nbsp;Jan-9 to Feb-5;&nbsp;Feb-12 to Mar-24;&nbsp;Apr-2 to Jun-15;&nbsp;Sep-1 to Dec-20 (minimum 2 nights)</li>	<li>High season:&nbsp;Feb-6 to Feb-11;&nbsp;Mar-25 to Apr-1;&nbsp;Jun-16 to Aug-31 (minimum 3 nights)</li>	<li>Peak season:&nbsp;Dec-21 to Jan-8, 2017;&nbsp;Dec-21, 2017 to Jan-8, 2018 (minimum 5 nights)</li></ul>', NULL, '115.14489730', '-8.66936200', 18, 9, 5, 15, NULL, 7, '2016-09-14 21:36:13', '2016-09-23 11:39:56', NULL),
(37, 1, 'Villa San', 'villa-san', 4, 0, '<p><strong>Villa San </strong>is&nbsp;a private and serene oasis in central Bali, position less than 300 meter north of Ubud''s Royal Palace.&nbsp;Designed as a labour of love, the villa is only minutes from sensational shopping, superb spas, classic cultural performances and luxuriant rice fields.</p><p>Showcasing an impressive array of artworks and handicrafts originating from China, Africa and Indonesia, Villa San comfortably accommodates 12 people in six large bedrooms (three doubles, three twins). These buildings are nestled around a 25m lap pool and set within lush gardens which incorporate elegant sculptures and a tranquil meditation terrace.</p>', '<p>Guests at Villa San are spoiled for choice when it comes to ways to relax. Reflecting the owners’ artistic and spiritual leanings, there’s the loft studio for painting, a telescope for star-gazing from the function room at night, and a Buddhist stupa and yoga terrace tucked in a quiet corner of the property for group or individual meditation and yoga practice.</p><p>The spacious grounds offer freedom and flexibility for both families and groups of friends, with hammocks and sun loungers arranged around the 25 x 5m pool and a pool pavilion seating up to 15 people. Inside, as well as the living and dining spaces, there are two well-equipped entertainment rooms – one is part of the two bedroom master suite, the other adjacent the informal dining room – a gym and a children’s playroom. The villa showcases some exquisite art and handicrafts from China, Ghana and Indonesia.</p><p>Villa San comprises six large bedrooms – three doubles and three twins. French doors from all the bedroom pavilions look out over tranquil gardens, only steps away from the long sloping lawn and the inviting pool.</p><p>A friendly, helpful team of staff are on hand around the clock, with a butler and chef available to meet every request. They are knowledgeable about local Hindu cultural activities, art galleries and the myriad options for exploring and learning about the region (guests can take a craft or cooking class, or book an in-house meditation or yoga session) and will recommend the best of local restaurants, cafés and Spas.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Serving Breakfast daily.</li>	<li>Knowledgeable and English speaking staffs.</li>	<li>F&amp;B services.</li>	<li>Villa will offer a suggestion menu (including Asian and Western dishes), but the guest&nbsp;can easily discuss with Chef on their own requests.</li>	<li>Villa Manager will assist any booking required of&nbsp;activities nearby or daily tour,&nbsp;as well as helps arrange transport.</li>	<li>Fasilitating&nbsp;in-house Yoga/Meditation&nbsp;teacher (applied cost).</li>	<li>Arranging a car and driver at a special rate of USD25++ daily for 8 consecutive hours (excluding petrol).</li>	<li>Staffs are friendly and kind to children.</li>	<li>Full-time babysitters can be organised (extra charge)</li>	<li>Laundry services (surcharge)</li>	<li>Spa treatment (price on request)</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pool: Private swimming pool 25 m x 5 m.</li>	<li>Living areas: Open-sided living area; dining area for 14; studio; garden&nbsp;balé&nbsp;and function room;&nbsp;6 air-conditioned bedrooms with en-suite bathroom.</li>	<li>Families: 2 baby cot;&nbsp;2 baby high chair;&nbsp;2 baby car seat;&nbsp;Children''s books;&nbsp;games and toys.</li>	<li>Entertainments: TV, Satellite TV, DVD Player , Stereo system with CD Player, iPod adaptor, iPod speakers dock at TV Room,&nbsp;DVD Library,&nbsp;Book library, and&nbsp;Board games.</li>	<li>Communications: Telephone landline (local access);&nbsp;Wireless Internet connection.</li>	<li>Other facilities: Hair dryer;&nbsp;Pool Deck Chairs;&nbsp;BBQ;&nbsp;Mini safe in bedroom 1, 5, &amp; 6.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Villa Manager</li>	<li>Full time chef</li>	<li>Butlers and housekeepers</li>	<li>Gardener and pool attendant</li>	<li>Security</li>	<li>Spa staff/masseuse (on request)</li>	<li>Yoga/meditation teachers (on request)</li></ul><dl>	<dd>&nbsp;</dd></dl>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer roundtrip, Breakfast,&nbsp;other complimentary&nbsp;services and villa facilities.</li>	<li>Rates are subject to 10 % Tax and 5.5 % Service charge</li>	<li>Plan meals with the chef the evening before, or over breakfast.</li>	<li>The villa’s food and beverage service is operated on a cash basis and all provisions are charged at the market cost plus 20% handling fee&nbsp;(to cover pick-ups/delivery and stock ingredients).</li>	<li>Check-in time : 15.00 Pm</li>	<li>Check-out time : 12.00 Noon</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.26441100', '-8.50285600', 12, 6, 3, 11, NULL, 6, '2016-09-15 08:50:46', '2016-09-23 11:42:14', NULL);
