(38, 1, 'Villa Echo Beach', 'villa-echo-beach', 2, 1, '<p>The Villa at&nbsp;<strong>Echo Beach</strong>&nbsp;is a masterpiece of elegance and comfort; handcrafted with simple lines to reflect the Island''s laidback, easy lifestyle. As guests enter the wooden gates they will leave the outside world behind.</p><p>The Villa is a stunning example of modern tropical architecture with rustic tones and random rock walls, emphasising an appreciation of earth, sand and sea. In the creation of this remarkable property, the multi-talented Australian designer Stuart Membery has brought something unique to Bali.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Echo Beach</strong>, located only 250 meters from Canggu’s Echo Beach, boasts a villa complex built between 2009-2010, suitable for up to 30 guests. All fully equipped villas feature their own private pool, sun lounges, western kitchen, king koil beds, ensuites, living room, balcony, dining room and more spread across 330-350m2.</p><p>The Villa comprises an expansive, open air living and dining area, an AV room, four bedrooms each with ensuite bathrooms, and numerous relaxation areas. The long corridors and high ceilings, present a feeling of enormous space. Fresh white walls, polished cement floors, honey-coloured serai stone and dark timber accents form the primary colours, offset by the Villa''s deep-blue tiled pool and rich green lawns. Large pieces of artwork adorn the walls, while furnishings, artefacts, accessories and lighting are all of the highest quality.</p><p><strong>The Beach House Restaurant</strong>, on the beach 150 metres away, is the place where the local community gathers in the evenings to watch the legendary sunsets.&nbsp;Tables spill out onto a beachside bluff where you can enjoy a comprehensive international menu, together with a daily barbeque of fresh fish, lobster, giant prawns, clams, steaks, kebabs etc. Live music, performed by accomplished local bands, takes place on Sunday evenings, starting at around sunset. This is a great social scene, it can get very busy and lively, and the smaller local warungs (eateries) beside the Beach House, accommodate the overflow of customers.&nbsp;</p><p>The rugged beach is renowned for its world-class surf breaks, offering an exposed reef break with consistent surf. May to October (dry season) is the favoured time for waves. Reef breaks provide lefts and rights-in fact, Canggu presents one of the few right-hand waves on the west coast of Bali.</p><p>The trendy Seminyak area, with its wide choice of international restaurants-including the famous ''Ku De Ta'', ''Kafe Warisan'', ''Living Room'', ''Hu''u'',''La Lucciola'' and ‘Sarong''-together with a plethora of chic cocktail bars, exciting nightclubs, lavish spas and elegant boutiques, is 25 minutes'' drive away.&nbsp;</p><p>The location offers easy access up to the mountains and rice terraces on the western slopes of the island; it is one hour''s drive from the famous cultural and artistic town of Ubud, and just 25 minutes'' drive from the Sunset Route, gateway to the eastern side of the island. It is also convenient for all of Bali''s shopping malls and main tourist attractions.</p><p>The international airport is 45 minutes'' drive. The nearby Greg Norman designed ''Nirwana Bali Golf Course'' is just 15 minutes away by car, and is situated beside the dramatic, waved-lashed sea temple of Tanah Lot. For horse lovers, the ''Umalas Equestrian Centre'' is just an easy drive away.&nbsp;</p><p>Guests staying at the villa may also enjoy visiting Hotel Tugu, situated within easy walking distance beside the beach at Canggu. The hotel is a living museum of priceless antiques and rare cultural artefacts, and it also offers the attractions of fine dining together with the facilities of an enchanting spa.</p>', '<p>​​​​​​<strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Service&nbsp;daily breakfast – American / Indonesian or Healthy.</li>	<li>Free cook&nbsp;for all lunches/dinners (only pay for ingredients) by&nbsp;the villa''s top class chef (from snacks to five-course dinners).</li>	<li>Unlimited drinking water</li>	<li>Free using a car and driver up to 8 hours a day (included petrol).</li>	<li>Daily housekeeping..</li>	<li>Traditional Balinese massage for each adult &amp; welcome bowl of fruit (5N min stay applies)&nbsp;</li>	<li>Organizing all available tours.</li>	<li>Surcharge &amp; require notice:&nbsp;Babysitting/Nanny service;&nbsp;Catering for parties/larger groups for non-guests;&nbsp;Temporary Pool Barrier.</li>	<li>Arranging (applied cost): in house SPA service; medical attention; a day trip to other areas in Bali; additional car/driver service;&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: private swimming pool with beach towels;&nbsp;sun lounges with mattresses; sun umbrella.</li>	<li>Living areas: a 4 Air-conditioned bedrooms &amp; ceiling fans in semi outdoor rooms; open sided&nbsp;living &amp; dining; AV room; fully equipped European kitchen.</li>	<li>Entertainment:&nbsp;&nbsp;satellite TV in living room on LCD 42″ TV with surround sound stereo;&nbsp;TVs with DVD players.</li>	<li>Families:&nbsp;Baby bath (on request);&nbsp;Baby cot and high chair.</li>	<li>Communication:&nbsp;Fibre Optic WiFi (50 Mbps).</li>	<li>Sport: Gym;&nbsp;Pool fencing on request (extra charge).</li>	<li>Area: private carparks;&nbsp;all spaces Non-Smoking (public and private).</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;CCTV 24/7 perimeter surveillance;&nbsp;ensuites; safety boxes; toiletries; solarium; Barbecue (on request).</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Description</strong></p><p><strong>2 Bedroom Villa</strong>&nbsp;– Choose from either 2 bedrooms upstairs or one on the ground level opening to private pool and the 2nd room upstairs. One room has choice of King Bed or Twin Setup. All bedrooms have ceiling fans, air-conditioning, King Koil mattresses, private ensuites, safety boxes, 32″ LCD TVs with DVD player.&nbsp; All living areas have ceiling fans. Accommodates up to 4 persons plus 1 infant (cot). &nbsp;Land size 300-330m2, bedroom/ensuite size 23-26m2, building size 200m2. &nbsp;</p><p><strong>3 Bedroom Villa</strong>&nbsp;– One bedroom on the ground floor that opens up to your private pool and 2 bedrooms upstairs with balcony. One bedroom has the choice of King Bed or Twin Beds. All bedrooms have ceiling fans, air-conditioning, King Koil mattresses, private ensuites, safety boxes, 32″ LCD Tvs with DVD player. All living areas have ceiling fans. Accommodates up to 6 persons plus 1 infant (cot). &nbsp;Land size 300-330m2, bedroom/ensuite size 23-26m2, building size 240m2. &nbsp;</p><p><strong>4 Bedroom Villa</strong>&nbsp;– One bedroom on the ground floor that opens up to your private pool and 3 bedrooms upstairs with balcony. One bedroom has the choice of King Bed or Twin Beds. All bedrooms have ceiling fans, air-conditioning, King Koil mattresses. Two of the bedrooms have private ensuites, safety boxes, 32″ LCD TVs with DVD player. The 3rd and 4th bedroom share an ensuite. All living areas have ceiling fans. Accommodates up to 6 adults, 2 children plus 1 infant (cot). &nbsp;Land size 300, 2 x bedroom/ensuite size 24-26m2, 2 x bedroom size 10m2 + shared ensuite 7.3 m2, building size 260m2. &nbsp;</p>', '<p>The Villa Echo Beach is supported by a carefully selected team of highly trained, friendly staff who will ensure their guests experience a truly enjoyable stay in Bali. The team includes an in-house chef, housekeepers, gardener, pool attendant and security guards and are available to assist guests during their stay. The chef is trained in the preparation of both local and international cuisine, and is responsible for all the market shopping, in accordance with guests needs.</p>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers, other complimentaries and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10.5% VAT and 5.% service charge</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 PM</li>	<li>Early Checkin is:&nbsp; 40% nightly promo rate&nbsp;any time from 10.00am onwards and includes also an early transfer, no earlier than 8.30am (If your flight arrives earlier than 8.30am then additional charges will apply).</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;<strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM (includes use of car/driver for 8 hours).</li>	<li>Charge for late check out&nbsp;until 8.00 PM: pay 70%&nbsp;of the nightly rate (includes use of car/driver for up to 8 hours with an immediate transfer to the airport).</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>The contract</strong></p><p>This contract entered here relates to the short term hire of Villa Echo Beach (located, at Jalan Pantai Batu Mejan, Gang Echo, Canggu, Bali, Indonesia), (hereafter referred to as “The Villa” or “The Property”), and is between Villa Echo Beach Management (hereinafter referred to as “The Villa Management” or “we”), and the primary holidaymaker (the person whose name under the booking is made), (hereinafter referred to as “The Hirer” or “you”). This contract is effective on written confirmation by The Villa Management of the receipt of the necessary deposit payment by The Hirer, for the specified rental period as confirmed by The Villa Management.</p><p><strong>Cancellation / No show / No contact</strong></p><p>Payments are non refundable but can be transferred across to another booking within 12 months of the original intended arrival date.&nbsp; This is on the condition that cancellations are made no less than 3 months prior to the arrival date and will incur a 15% penalty fee.  INSERT INTO `villas` (`id`, `status`, `title`, `slug`, `area_id`, `featured`, `intro`, `description`, `services`, `facilities`, `staff_detail`, `term_condition`, `other`, `longitude`, `latitude`, `occupied_max`, `bedrooms_no`, `environment_id`, `staff_no`, `position`, `created_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`) VALUES
(40, 1, 'Khayangan Estate', 'khayangan-estate', 6, 0, '<p>The name comes from the old word for ‘Seventh Heaven’. This private Bali villa estate is truly heavenly. In fact,&nbsp;<b>we believe it is the very best Bali luxury villa</b>. It rests on the south west tip of Bali in lovely gardens on a high cliff top, above a white sand beach. The villa offers one of the best views in Bali, with a grand vista of the ocean. It is hard to find another luxury Bali villa&nbsp;with such a good view.&nbsp;</p><p>The villa’s charm lies in its design. It is made up of two clusters of traditional, antique, wooden houses from Java. These were once the homes of noble men. They have been carefully grouped to echo the mood of an old village. The villas are set in a huge garden, with dense beds of yellow flowers, gently swaying palms, shrubs and trees. The villa is quite different from any other luxury Bali villa&nbsp;or luxury Bali resort.</p>', '<p><strong>Khayangan Estate</strong> is located in a beautiful area known as The Bukit - a limestone plateau rising sharply from the sea, fringed by steep cliffs and some of the most idyllic beaches in Bali. Characterised by wide open spaces and clear blue skies, the turquoise waters are the playground of migrating whales. A tropical, equatorial climate means year-round balmy temperatures and, even in the rainy season, The Bukit - which is much drier than the rest of the island - is a reliable sun-trap. When the southeast trade winds blow offshore and the southern ocean swells hit the reefs, the barrelling surf breaks are among the best in the world. The only other activity is seaweed farming, still traditionally practiced by the original Balinese coastal families.&nbsp;</p><p>With Bulgari Resort Bali as its prestigious neighbour, Khayangan Estate is only 30 minutes'' drive from Bali''s International Airport and no more than 45 minutes'' from the endless shopping, vibrant nightlife and international restaurants of Kuta and Seminyak. The world-class Bali Golf and Country Club in Nusa Dua is a mere 15 minutes'' drive, and Ubud - Bali''s centre for fine arts and cultural performances - is about 90 minutes'' drive to the north. The remainder of the island offers a rich mosaic of cultures, tastes, sights and sounds, together with a wide array of activities.</p><p>This is a place of mesmerising beauty with cliffs over 170 metres high, rolling surf, pristine white sand beaches, and magnificent 180-degree views of the Indian Ocean.</p><p>The original charm of these one hundred year old buildings has been kept. These Bali luxury villas are made of old teak wood. Here, you will find rich furnishings, as well as state of the art facilities. Bathrooms are the coolest on the island, especially those of the two master bedrooms. Each has a private water garden, where a dreamy bath tub appears to float in a clear pond.&nbsp;</p><p>The design of this luxury Bali villa estate presents guests with the choice of a three bedroom or a six bedroom renting option. There are two big lap pools, two smaller pools, and a cold plunge pool. There is also a business centre, a cliff edge bale,&nbsp;a gym, and a spa.&nbsp;</p><p>All of this not only makes for a great Bali holiday villa, but is also the best choice for a Wedding Villa.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport tranfers: pick up &amp; drop off.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and refreshment towel once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>A full complement of English-speaking staff, highly trained in the business of Bali luxury villas.</li>	<li>Personal butlers, on call 24 hours, are ready to help you make arrangements for a range of services.&nbsp;</li>	<li>24h security for a whole Estate.</li></ul><p><strong>Services for Wedding</strong></p><ul>	<li>Khayangan’s tropical wedding caterers will delight with their stylish, artistic expression.&nbsp;The wedding banquet may be a sumptuous four-course dinner.</li>	<li>For wedding events, professional hair and make up services will be made available for bride and&nbsp;attendants.</li>	<li>Specialised bridal boutiques present exquisite gift items and a wide selection of wedding dresses and men''s attire in a range of sizes, for the bride, groom, family and guests.&nbsp;Styles include designer labels, and gifts include sophisticated souvenir items.</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;<strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Living areas: Six&nbsp;ultra-lavish bedroom suites with the most romantic en-suite bathrooms;&nbsp;Two grand&nbsp;living and dining pavilions; A fully equipped modern kitchen;&nbsp;A fully equipped private office;&nbsp;A fully equipped gymnasium</li>	<li>Support facilities:&nbsp;Cliff edge Bale; Business Centre; A professionally equipped SPA;&nbsp;A cliff-top relaxation pavilion;&nbsp;</li>	<li>Pools: Two big lap pools;&nbsp;two smaller pools;&nbsp;and a cold plunge pool.</li>	<li>Entertainments: Individual sound system with iPod connections in every suite;&nbsp;A library of books;&nbsp;DVD’s and board games;&nbsp;Outdoor games including badminton, boules and lawn croquet</li>	<li>Communications:&nbsp;WiFi internet access throughout the estate.</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Khayangan Estate - Accommodation</strong></p><p><strong>Living &amp; Dining Pavilion</strong></p><p>Serenaded by the tranquil sound of water, guests will traverse an ornamental pond before entering the living and dining pavilion. This is the largest of the time-honoured teakwood Joglos, created over 100 years ago in Central Java in an area where skilled artisans have developed the art of carving wood to the highest degree of refinement. The Joglo''s most striking feature is its towering core of four intricately and exquisitely carved pillars, showcasing traditional patterns and flowers. Destined to be demolished, this wonderful old building was saved and carefully transplanted to Bali to create the heart and social hub of Khayangan Estate.</p><p>This expansive, air-conditioned living and dining area embraces the spectacular view with the incorporation of glass walls on two sides. It has been furnished with large sofas and chairs, a coffee table, a dresser and a rustic dining table for twelve, all custom-made from antique wood. White drapes fall between the central pillars, recycled floorboards are scattered with rugs, and the muted colour theme follows the natural hue of the timber. Antique statues and carvings from the islands of East Nusa Tenggara have been fondly placed in well-lit settings that show them off to their best advantage. Funky wrought iron lamps and lanterns, designed by the owners, channel a soft light by night, creating a romantic ambience. A large, flat screen, satellite TV, DVD and quality sound system is provided for guests'' entertainment. To the rear is a separate, fully-fitted, modern kitchen.&nbsp;</p><p>The master bedroom and guest rooms are housed within three, separate, self-contained Joglos, complete with en-suite bathrooms, wide verandahs, and lovely views of the ocean, the garden, the pool, and the social centre of the Estate. The authentic-style is elegant and enchanting. Each Joglo is air-conditioned and furnished with fitted wardrobes, seating, mirrors and lamps. Each boasts a king-size four-poster bed, built into the beams within the central funnel of the roof. Soft muslin drapes are clutched within simple tiebacks. Paintings, local textiles and ikat cushions create a personal touch. Each bedroom is equipped with a mini bar/fridge, safe, satellite TV, stereo system and telephone as well as wi-fi internet access.</p><p>Each luxurious en-suite bathroom is characterised by unique features. Each is equipped with air-conditioning, an all-embracing rainshower, a splendidly appointed bathtub, a toilet, single or twin washbasins, large mirrors, and the thoughtful provision of cushioned bench seats.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Master Bedroom &amp; Bathroom</strong></p><p>The master bedroom is particularly spacious, and enhanced with the added feature of a bay window and curved window seat, a wall of fitted wardrobes, a desk, an armchair, and a 39-inch flat screen plasma TV with satellite TV.&nbsp;</p><p>The sumptuous, air-conditioned en-suite bathroom is a study in symmetry, equipped with large mirrors and ''his and hers'' washbasins resting upon separate wooden vanity units within two distinct areas. A toilet, together with a bidet, is discretely positioned at one end, while a walk-in rainshower with a pebbled splashback is situated at the other end. The piece de resistance, however, can be found on the far side of an external glass door. Here, in a beautiful private water-garden, and accessed by stepping stones, a dreamy oversized bathtub, complete with an overhead canopy, appears to be floating in a gin clear ornamental pond. In the far corner of the pond is a ''floating'', open-sided relaxation pavilion, sheltered by a roof and furnished with a built-in sofa and cushions. The serene picture is completed with an ancient frangipani tree, staghorn and bird''s nest ferns, and a cascading waterfall.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Business Centre</strong></p><p>The air-conditioned business centre is a rare, two-storey timber Javanese house that has been transformed into a private office or work space, with a small, open-air meeting area upstairs. This enchanting building represents a bygone era with its raised, wrap-around verandah, and two-tiered roof. It features large glass windows, and has been lovingly furnished with an antique desk, chair, bookshelves, cupboards and a kilim rug. It is well-equipped with a computer, a multi-function printer, scanner and photocopier, and free Broadband Wifi Internet, which can be accessed all over the Estate. An external staircase leads up to the breezy meeting or relaxation area, furnished with a marble-topped table and chairs. Guests'' needs are further considered with the provision of a washroom.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Cliff top Pavilion</strong></p><p>A large open-sided relaxation gazebo, fitted with cushioned seating, rests on the clifftop beside a freshwater Jacuzzi with a chiller. The pool is flanked by a timber deck furnished with canopied chairs.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Seventh Heaven Spa</strong></p><p>The architecture of the clifftop spa blends rusticity and glamour. Landscaped into the cliff, with a flat roof supporting a grassy lawn, it is built directly into the rock. The fully-equipped, air-conditioned spa with its glass-fronted curved facade, presents a Vichy shower, hot tub, steam room, massage tables, manicure and pedicure facilities, and a cave-like room for scrubs and water treatments. Overlooking the ocean and the beach, it is also a great spot for meditation. The spa menu offers a full range of massage, beauty treatments and therapies, such as the Ocean Bath, Flower Bath and Aromatherapy Bath, as well as a Cucumber Wrap for sunburnt skin.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Gardens and Pool</strong></p><p>The gorgeous landscaped gardens of Khayangan Estate present a very natural feel. Pathways are paved with timber and bordered by dense beds of tall, gently swaying yellow irises. Immaculate lawns are punctuated with palms and other carefully selected native plants and trees, such as bougainvillea, frangipanis and climbers, to provide a balance of fragrance, colour and shade.&nbsp;</p><p>The infinity-edge, swimming pool is located in front of the main living and dining area. Shaded by coconut palms and frangipani, and lined with natural stone, the pool appears to flow over the edge of the cliff. The timber pool deck is furnished with canopied sunbeds, while a barbeque and pizza oven is positioned nearby, making alfresco dining easy and fun.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sports Facilities</strong></p><p>The tennis court and a fully-equipped gym are located near the entrance to the Estate.&nbsp;</p><p>The tennis court has a covered spectator/viewing pavilion with benches and antique "gerobok" (rice storage trunks on wheels) with cushions.</p><p>The gymnasium is fully air-conditioned, and includes a full selection of machines, as well as a stereo system, satellite TV, fridge and cold water dispenser.</p><p><strong>Eco Friendly</strong></p><p><strong>Khayangan Estate</strong>&nbsp;incorporates many features designed to reduce its impact on the environment. Bio-degradable waste from the house and garden is collected, mulched and composted for use in the gardens. The garden is irrigated using an underground system that meters water usage on automatic timers. There is also a water purification plant, which produces drinking quality water in all taps. Solar panels have been installed on the roofs for heating water, and ionisers are used instead of chlorine in the swimming pool, which effectively turn the water into pure mineral water using a process approved by NASA. Low-wattage, long life, lighting fixtures keep energy costs down and timers and sensors are also used to avoid excess consumption of power. A waste water recycling system is planned.</p><p><strong>Khayangan Estate - Weddings and Parties</strong></p><p>Khayangan Estate presents the perfect setting for weddings, parties and other special events. The extensive lawns are also ideal for open-air Balinese dance performances and parties. The catering can be managed by professional caterers who have the world-class expertise to prepare a sumptuous feast in addition to the coordination of decorations, flowers, lighting and entertainment.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Estate manager</li>	<li>Executive chef</li>	<li>Professional spa therapists</li>	<li>Highly trained personal butlers</li>	<li>Kitchen staff</li>	<li>Housekeeping</li>	<li>Gardening staff</li>	<li>Engineering staff</li>	<li>Security staff</li></ul>', '<h3><strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong></h3><ul>	<li>All rates are&nbsp;quoted in US dollars per night. Reservations are confirmed by receipt of a bank transfer in US dollars.</li>	<li>Rates INCLUDE 15,5% Tax &amp; Service Charge.</li>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer, Daily continental breakfast ( 2 persons per room ), Laundry services (exclude dry clean), Internet connection.</li>	<li>Rates do NOT include long-distance/international calls, food and beverage and extra activities, spa, etc.</li>	<li>Please note that the capacity of Khayangan Estate is 12 adults for the 6 bedrooms, and 6 adults for the 3 bedrooms. Additional beds for children are available, at cost of US$ 120 per bed, per night</li>	<li>Minimum stay 3 nights (special offer for addition stay)&nbsp;*terms and conditions apply</li>	<li>Maximum capacity : 250 persons for functions/events</li>	<li>Minimum stay 3 nights (special offer for addition stay)&nbsp;<i>*terms and conditions apply</i></li>	<li>DJ/Loud Music : Allowed.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Acoustic Music : Allowed.</li>	<li>Curfew: 12 pm.</li>	<li>Curfew: 12 pm</li></ul><h3><strong>Detail Descriptions Terms &amp; Conditions</strong></h3><p><strong>Reservation</strong></p><ul>	<li>A deposit of 50% of the rental is required by bank transfer, or cash to confirm a reservation, which is confirmed with a copy of the bank transfer from the client faxed or e-mailed to Khayangan Estate within 7 (seven) business days. If a deposit is not received in time it can result in the cancellation of your booking. Full payment is required for booking less than 45 days before arrival (60 days for peak season)</li>	<li>Final payment is required at least 45 days (60 days for peak season) prior to the guests’ arrival by bank transfer. Please note that all payments must be for the full amount net of any transfer and bank fees, which are the responsibility of the renters or their agents</li>	<li>Check-in time is 2 pm and check-out time is 11am. We try our best to accommodate guests who need to extend check-out time slightly provided there are no guests arriving the same afternoon. A late check-out charge equivalent to 50% of nightly rental is applicable for guests wishing to stay at the villa past 2 pm.</li></ul><p><strong>Cancellation</strong></p><ul>	<li>Deposits will be refunded in full less USD 1,000, if the reservation is cancelled 60 days or more prior to arrival (90 days for peak Season)</li>	<li>Reservation cancelled less than 60 days (90 days for peak Season) prior to arrival are subject to forfeiture of deposit</li>	<li>Notice of cancellation must be received in writing</li>	<li>Final payments are non-refundable</li></ul><p><strong>Damage and Loses</strong></p><p>Renter is responsible for leaving the property and its contents in good order and in a clean condition. Renter will be asked to pay for any damages or losses incurred during their stay. Khayangan Estate reserves the right to repossess the villas(s) with no refund if the renter or any member of the renter’s party causes excessive damage or nuisance or engages in unlawful activities.</p><p><strong>Numbers in Party</strong></p><p>Full names, number of people in the party (Adults-Couples/Children-Ages), arrival and departure time information are required upon making a reservation. The capacity of Khayangan Estate is&nbsp;<b>12 adults</b>.<br />Additional bedding can be arranged for adult and children.<br /><b>Extra Bed</b>&nbsp;costs&nbsp;<b>US$ 120 per bed</b>&nbsp;, per night. The Price&nbsp;<b>is includes Continental breakfast</b>.</p><p><strong>Generator</strong></p><p>Management has an in-house generator set to cover for power outage or failure to ensure that there is no disruption to the high quality service provided by Khayangan Estate. It will not be sufficient to cover the extra load from additional lighting and sound system for events and parties. Please advise your event planner that they should bring in their own generator-set.</p><p><strong>Insurance.</strong></p><p>In the event that the function will involve activities at or near Khayangan Estate which are inherently dangerous.&nbsp;Event planner will be required to show evidence of inforce liability insurance that will cover any accident, injury or death arising from the activity. Should the insurance be subject to any deductible amount on claims, the renter/event planner will be required to deposit this deductible amount as a bond with Khayangan Estate. Failure to comply with this requirement may lead to the immediate eviction of the renter from Khayangan, together with forfeiture of all monies deposited.</p><h3><strong>Seasons</strong></h3><ul>	<li>LOW SEASON : Jan 9 to Jun 30, Sep 16 to Dec 18<br />	(Excluding Chinese New Year &amp; Easter week)</li>	<li>HIGH SEASON : Jul 1 – 31, Sep 1 - 15,<br />	Easter Week and Chinese New Year week</li>	<li>PEAK SEASON : Aug 1 – 31, Dec 19 – Jan 8</li></ul>', NULL, '115.11509930', '-8.84333700', 12, 6, 4, 15, NULL, 7, '2016-09-15 16:41:24', '2016-09-23 12:07:37', NULL),
(41, 1, 'Villa Tanju Bali', 'villa-tanju-bali', 2, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Tanju Bali</strong>&nbsp;is one of Bali''s very few absolute oceanfront Villas located on a cliff with access to&nbsp;<strong>Cemagi Beach</strong>. Villa Tanju Bali is located just beyond the quiet and picturesque Balinese Village of Mengening along a winding village road lined with paddy fields and featuring substantial Balinese Temples and massive Banyan Tress.</p><p>Only a approx 30 minutes from the many popular restaurants and shops of Seminyak and and approximately 45 minutes drive drive to Ngurah Rai International Airport. For the golf enthusiasts, the Nirwana Bali Golf Course - The Le Meridian Hotel and the famous Tanah Lot Temple are less than a 10 minutes drive. The Nusa Dua Golf Club and Bali Handara Golf Course are an equidistant 1 hour''s drive away.</p>', '<p><strong>Villa Tanju Bali</strong>&nbsp;is one of Bali''s very few absolute oceanfront Villas located on a cliff with access to&nbsp;<strong>Cemagi Beach</strong>. Villa Tanju Bali is located just beyond the quiet and picturesque Balinese Village of Mengening along a winding village road lined with paddy fields and featuring substantial Balinese Temples and massive Banyan Tress.</p><p>Only a approx 30 minutes from the many popular restaurants and shops of Seminyak and and approximately 45 minutes drive drive to Ngurah Rai International Airport. For the golf enthusiasts, the Nirwana Bali Golf Course - The Le Meridian Hotel and the famous Tanah Lot Temple are less than a 10 minutes drive. The Nusa Dua Golf Club and Bali Handara Golf Course are an equidistant 1 hour''s drive away.</p><p>The villa was designed and built by the same International Group who built the Four Seasons Hotel in Bali, and is refreshingly uncomplicated and simple in design with the sympathetic use of traditional Balinese architectural concepts and utilization of the best of local timbers and handcrafted stones and offers you every modern amenity.</p><p>The property&nbsp;has 4 Air-conditioned bedrooms, all with en-suite bathrooms. It has been designed with a master on ground level, two guest rooms with King-size and Twin bed in other building plus 1 king-size upstairs connect with study room. All the bedrooms have ocean views with large glass sliding doors also with split air conditioning units as well as overhead ceiling fans. The bedrooms have custom made oversized king beds with built in wardrobes. Often overlooked in tropical homes, all bedrooms have good quality curtains. The bedroom interiors have been tastefully furnished with collected antique furniture and artifacts.</p><p>The villa has the ultimate sunset panorama with views over in the south over a Balinese temple set on a large rocky outcrop in the ocean to the Java coastline in the west and the cloudy peaks of Gunung Agung to the north. Set on a 1,760 M2 square meters, gently sloping grounds, studded with coconut palms and fragrant frangipani trees, with a crystal clear 15 meter x 4,5 meter lap swimming pool this home is a wonderful retreat, far from the gaiety of tourist Bali.</p><p>The stunning main 15-meter x 4,5 meter open living and dining pavilion has been designed for relaxation and entertainment and provides optimum enjoyment of the wonderful ocean, river and unforgettable sunset views. The pavilion with its high natural alang alang grass ceiling, the tall supporting coconut columns and the cool cream terrazzo paved floors is the very essence of tropical living. Overhead ceiling fans and gentle sea breezes keep everyone cool and the ample lounge area seating assures that there is room for everyone to relax. The lounge has a music system with surround sound speakers in the ceiling. The 3 meter antique wood dining table for 6 makes for easy and elegant dining.</p><p>A separate air-conditioned indoor study has a Television unit complete with VCD or DVD and Video systems. The grounds are beautifully grassed and maintained. The wonderful 15 meter long swimming pool is lined with green stone with a white Palimanan stone surround. A swim in the pool, a surf at one of Bali''s most popular surf beaches, a beach walk, a bike ride up to the village and its surrounds or a quiet fish at the rock pools are all only a matter of steps.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Complimentary&nbsp;airport transfers: pick up &amp; drop off.</li>	<li>Welcome drink &amp; flowers upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>Complimentary daily car Toyota Innova 7-seater,&nbsp;and driver for 8 hours (exclude petrol).</li>	<li>Free laundry (except&nbsp;dry laundry).</li>	<li>Friendly and helpful staffs.</li>	<li>The cooks could&nbsp;accommodate our guest&nbsp;dining requests and special dietary needs.&nbsp;How to shop for premium quality produce and all meals are provided to our guests at cost (Indonesian cuisine and a wide selection of delicious choices,&nbsp;or vegetarian, Italian and BBQ style meals, also for kids).</li>	<li>8 hours maid daily from 8am - 4pm.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities&nbsp;</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools:&nbsp;large private swimming pool 15m x 4,5m</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;1 Master with Balinese-Four-Post-Bed,&nbsp;2 Bedrooms with double bed &amp;&nbsp;1 Bedroom with twin beds&nbsp;(all with air - conditioning and overhead ceiling fans);&nbsp;Separate Study room;&nbsp;4 en-suite bathrooms (1 Master with oversized bathtub,&nbsp;2 guest with bathtub,&nbsp;upstairs Bathroom with shower);&nbsp;Open plan living pavilion with glass sliding doors;&nbsp;Dining Pavilion adjoining western style kitchen;&nbsp;Main Dining Table Seats 6 people.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;Cable TV, VCR, Stereo, VCD Stereo Unit in all bedrooms</li>	<li>Communications:&nbsp;Telephone Line;&nbsp;Free Wi-Fi connection</li>	<li>Support facilities: Tropical landscaped garden with ponds;&nbsp;Private carparks.</li>	<li>Other facilities: a Toyota Innova for 7-seater;&nbsp;In house mineral water, tea and coffee making facilities.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Ketut Parwata&nbsp;is the manager,&nbsp;oversees the property and all staff. And assist guests during their stay at Villa Tanju Bali.</li>	<li>Ketut Yudiana&nbsp;is the cook, arranging preparation of both local and international cuisine. The cook will do all the market shopping based on guest request.</li>	<li>Ayu, Wayan Jero, Putu Supriawan&nbsp;and&nbsp;Luh Witrin&nbsp;ar our maids,&nbsp;taking care of housekeeping duties, laundry and to make sure that the villa is clean and tidy.</li>	<li>Nyoman Sukarta&nbsp;takes care of the garden,cleaning the garden and the grounds of the villa, and cleaning and maintaining the swimming pool.</li>	<li>Made Jesen&nbsp;is the driver,&nbsp;who will take guests wherever their like and bring their back again.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Nyoman Kasna,&nbsp;Kerut Alit Nawa and Agus&nbsp;are in charge of villa security.&nbsp;Their job is to patrol the grounds and the villa, ensuring the security of the guests.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer, Welcome drink and chilled towel upon arrival, complimentary 1 time breakfast (1st morning only), free wifi, free 1x6 seatercar with driver for use up to 8 hours a day (excluded petrol)</li>	<li>Rates are subject to 15.5% tax and service charge.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;subject to availability</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low Season (minimum 3 nights):&nbsp;January 11th to June 30th;&nbsp;September 16th to December 19th (Excluding Chinese New Year, Excluding Easter)</li>	<li>High Season (minimum 7 nights):&nbsp;Chinese New Year;&nbsp;Easter week;&nbsp;July 1st to September 15th.</li>	<li>Peak Season (minimum 10 nights):&nbsp;August 1 - August 31;&nbsp;December 20th to January 10th</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '115.09826630', '-8.63914200', 8, 4, 1, 11, NULL, 7, '2016-09-15 17:01:37', '2016-09-23 12:10:10', NULL),
(42, 1, 'Villa Castaway', 'villa-castaway', 6, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Castaway</strong>&nbsp;is a modern 4 bedroom villa nestled on a breezy hillside in the Bukit peninsula, just 30 min drive from Bali international airport and in close proximity to the Island most beautiful and secluded beaches.</p><p>This villa is the perfect place to enjoy a break from a busy lifestyle, to relax and revitalize. The privacy and beauty of the natural surrounding convey a serene resort feeling and the cutting edge architecture and interiors are sure to please style conscious guests with a passion for modern design.</p><p>The open plan layout makes the most of the spectacular 270 views of the Indian Ocean and surrounding forest.</p>', '<p>The <strong>Villa Castaway</strong> is set on a 1,000 M2 private ground and is arranged on two levels. The living-dining-kitchen area and two of the bedrooms are located on the upper floor. Two more bedrooms are on the ground level. Sleek modern interiors provide a luxurious atmosphere, complemented by beautifully landscaped gardens.</p><p>The private 13 mt infinity-edge lap pool runs between the living area and a large deck fitted with an outdoor dining table and lounges.</p><p>The comfortable living area is accented by colorful custom designed furniture and funky lamps.&nbsp; A solid timber dining table with upholstered armchairs is positioned along a natural stone wall.</p><p>The main double bedroom opens directly to the pool and to the ocean and forest views.&nbsp;</p><p>It features an upholstered queen size bed, with luxurious satin linen, fur blankets, walls of mirror, natural stone and frameless glass sliding doors. The en-suite bathroom is fitted with a double vanity, large shower, and walls of reflective colored glass.</p><p>The other 3 double bedrooms &amp; en-suite bathrooms open to private landscaped gardens and feature, bamboo and granite flooring, frameless glass sliding doors, block-out curtains, and plasterboard ceiling.</p><p>All bedrooms are fitted with TV, DVD player and cable TV, hidden air-conditioning units, safety deposit box, large wardrobe and desk. A DVD library is available for use by the guests.</p><p>The open plan kitchen and bar are fully equipped and an enticing in-house menu offers the opportunity to enjoy fresh meals prepared daily by the villa chef, accompanied by a selection of juices, coffees, cocktails and wines.&nbsp;</p><p>The excellent service is swift and discreet to ensure maximum privacy for the guests. Villa staff provides all the household services, cleaning and maintenance of the garden and pool, as well as the security of the property. The friendly manager will meet you on arrival and will be present daily to cater to your needs and to oversee the food and beverage preparation.</p><p>Internet connection with USB modem is available for guests with personal laptop computer. Local and International calls can be made with a pre-paid voucher using the villa mobile phone.</p><p>Upon request, guests can enjoy in-house massage and reflexology treatments, and we can assist in organizing excursions around the Island in guided car w/driver. For self driven cars there is a secure carport.</p><p>Beautiful, white sand beaches are few minutes drive away and the offshore reefs of the Bukit provide the best surfing conditions in Bali. The world famous Uluwatu temple is just 5 km distance. For golf enthusiast the new 17 holes course at Dreamland is 5 min drive and the Nusa Dua course just 20 min.</p><p>The busy district of Seminyak with its abundance of restaurants, shops and evening hang-outs is 35 min drive. Closest 5 star hotels are the Bvlgari Resort, The Ritz-Carlton (The Ayana) and the Four Seasons at Jimbaran.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers: pick up and drop off.</li>	<li>Refreshments and welcome drink upon arrival at the villa.</li>	<li>Welcome pack of cold drinks, fruits and snacks, and&nbsp;free mineral drinking water.</li>	<li>Chef could cook daily fresh meals in-house menus at the villa, with selection of juices, warm drink, cocktails and wines (at guest''s account)</li>	<li>Daily household services and cleaning</li>	<li>Maintanance garden and pool</li>	<li>24 hours a villa guard</li>	<li>Daily continental breakfast service</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities&nbsp;</strong></p><ul>	<li>Living areas: modern design 4 bedrooms with different color,&nbsp;all with ensuite bathroom and air conditioned; equipped Kitchen; and Bar.</li>	<li>Entertainment: Each room fitted with TV, DVD player and cable TV</li>	<li>Additional facilities: safety deposit box;&nbsp;first aid kits;&nbsp;safety card</li>	<li>Pool</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>​​​​​​Villa manager</li>	<li>Cook</li>	<li>House Keepers</li>	<li>Gardener/Pool attendant</li>	<li>Securities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Rates, Checking in and out</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of Continental breakfast (2 person per room), Free Internet connection, Complimentary airport transfer (1 x in and 1 x out)</li>	<li>The above rates including of tax and service</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;<strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low season&nbsp;(Min. stay 3 nights) : January 9 - July 14 (excluding Chinese New Year &amp; Easter), September 16 - December 19</li>	<li>High season&nbsp;(Min. stay 7 nights) : Chinese New Year,&nbsp; Easter week,&nbsp; July 15-31, September 1-15</li>	<li>Peak season&nbsp;(Min. stay 7 nights) : August 1-31, December 20 - January 8</li></ul>', NULL, '115.07579770', '-8.82651390', 8, 4, 4, 7, NULL, 7, '2016-09-15 17:23:44', '2016-09-23 12:11:43', NULL),
(43, 1, 'Villa Chocolat 2 bedrooms', 'villa-chocolat-2-bedrooms', 1, 0, '<h2>This 2-bedroom villa provides you both intimacy and luxury in the heart of Seminyak, Bali.</h2><p align="justify">With the 2-bedroom Villa Chocolat, you can either way enjoy a day at the beach, a dinner in a fancy restaurant or shop around the trendiest boutique of Bali, all of these being at walking distance of your luxury accommodation in Seminyak. The latter offers you a total haven of peace and privacy, with its own 75 square meter swimming pool shaded by a spacious tropical garden.</p>', '<h2 align="justify">A modern &amp; luxury Villa Chocolat in Seminyak, Bali</h2><p align="justify">Sobriety and timelessness compose the interior modern scenery of the luxury 2 bedroom Villa Chocolat, which also includes accents of Bali arts. Sober colour tones enhance the inherent luminosity, highlighted by the blend of mole grey, beige and green. The staff of the 2-bedroom Villa Chocolat is dedicated to you, and their goal is to make you spend the most perfect, luxury, relaxing and lively holidays in Seminyak, in Bali, the Island of Gods. A car driver is even at your disposal if you wish to discover more about Bali’s various areas and traditions.</p><p><strong><big>Enjoy a striking daily sunset of Seminyak from the upstairs bedrooms at your private Villas Chocolat Bali.</big></strong></p><p>The feeling of space is achieved by the blend of a sober color palette such as beige, gray and chocolate. The swimming pools are surrounded by a spacious garden with deck chairs. The interior decor is a mix of sober style and timelessness with a purified line of furniture designed with local and gorgeous materials such as sonoklin wood, and stone carving. Located in the center of Seminyak, unlike some other private rental villas in Bali, there is a safe and quiet feeling from all nocturnal nuisances. Offering the same standards and services as found in resorts in Bali and international private luxury villas, with a dedicated staff, available to provide all the services you expect of a Private Villa. Less than 400 m from the sea and 300 m from the KU DE TA, Villas Chocolat were designed to offer a vacation Villa in an urban setting, while maintaining the peaceful and quiet retreat. The Villas Chocolat Bali for rent are part of Nyaman Group. Let’s discover Nyaman Group in Bali and discover our partners, Nyaman Gallery, Nyaman boutique, Nyaman Villas Bali, our boat the Perjuangan liveaboard diving cruise, and also our 2 Rental Villas Partners, Gorgeous Villas bali and Villa Bali Booking.<br />Stay in the private Villas Chocolat, located in the vibrant city of Seminyak, in Bali.</p><p>You must have noticed that private Villas rental business in Bali is particularly crowded, because of Bali’s tourism success. However, we manage to make the difference thanks to our large range of services that are at our clients’ disposal. A manager, surrounded by a buttler, a Chef (on request), three housekeepers, a gardener and of course a person in charge of the daily pool maintenance form the staff that will take care of you during your stay. Villas Chocolat’s success in this competitive sector also depends on the large spaces they provide, in the bedrooms, the living-rooms and even the swimming-pools. The location is an asset itself since you are at walking distance of all holidays activities: the beach, the fancy restaurants and the trendy shops. So, why would you not book a stay in the Villas Chocolat? You will enjoy the daily breakfasts with your feet in the swimming pool, the vibrant lunches in the fancy restaurants of Seminyak, the long relaxing afternoons layed down on your private sunbed and the beautiful views of Bali’s sunset from the master bedroom. Finally, by booking with us, you will take advantage of the Privilege Club that will offer you a large range of exclusive benefits during your stay in one of the Villas Chocolat in Bali</p><p align="justify">&nbsp;</p>', '<h2><strong>Villas Chocolat Services included in rates</strong></h2><ul>	<li>Pick up and return airport transfers in air-conditioned car</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and tropical fruit basket</li>	<li>American or local daily breakfast</li>	<li>Butler service</li>	<li>Daily housekeeping</li>	<li>Wifi available</li>	<li>I-pod dock stations</li>	<li>Local mobile phone</li>	<li>Safety box in each room</li>	<li>Kids games at disposal “PS2 with 20 games”</li>	<li>Baby cot, baby trolley and car seat on request</li>	<li>DVD library</li></ul>', '<div class="col-lg-12 konten contains"><p style="text-align: justify;">The Villas Chocolat Bali are made to offer you a 4-star stay with luxury facilities. All the rooms of the villas have fans and air-conditioning to enjoy perfectly Bali’s climate. The large private swimming pools will refresh you after a long sunny day laying in the comfortable sunbeds. The villas have spacious open-air bathrooms, large kitchen with a bar, and a wide living room where you can enjoy your family summer retreat. And above all, Wi-Fi is available in all rooms to provide you all the comfort you deserve.</p><h2>Luxury Villas Chocolat’s facilities in Seminyak, Bali:</h2><ul>	<li>Fans &amp; air-conditioning</li>	<li>Large open-air bathroom with bath &amp; shower</li>	<li>TV with a DVD library</li>	<li>Private swimming pools</li>	<li>Lotus pond, gardens, patio</li>	<li>Private Bar &amp; kitchen</li>	<li>Open living room with lounges, dining table &amp; individual tables for breakfast</li>	<li>One additional bed is available per room for $50++ per night</li></ul></div>', '', '<p>Check in time at 14:00pm</p><p>Check out time at: 12:00 noon</p><p>Seasons:</p><p>Low seasons: From April, 1st to June, 30th, From September, 1st to December, 19th, From January 2017, 5th to 23rd, and From January 2017, 31st to March 2017, 31st.</p><p>High seasons: From July, 1st to August , 31st, &amp; Chinese New Year (From January 2017, 24th to 30th)</p><p>Peak seasons: From December, 20th to January 2017, 4th</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 2, 2, NULL, NULL, 3, '2016-09-18 08:59:10', '2016-09-24 06:50:57', NULL),
