(52, 1, 'Villa Jamalu', 'villa-jamalu', 5, 0, '<div id="maincol"><p>Perched high atop a hillside on Bali’s south coast, with sweeping views over the tranquil waters of Jimbaran Bay, sits the fabulous, four-bedroom, family friendly Villa Jamalu.</p><p>Every aspect of this stunning villa, from its clean lines to its stylish interiors, promises guests the ultimate in luxury and entertainment. Three storeys of outstanding accommodation provide endless opportunities for fun and relaxation: workout in the well-equipped gym; shoot pool or battle it out on the PlayStation; spoil yourself in the spa room; meditate in the yoga space or refresh in the 15-metre pool. While you rest and rejuvenate, a team of friendly and capable staff, including a private chef and villa manager, are on hand to make sure you want for nothing.</p><p>Just a stone’s throw from some of Bali’s finest beaches, a stay at Villa Jamalu will exceed all your holiday dreams.</p></div>', '<p>Set within the secure and exclusive Temple Hill estate, overlooking Jimbaran Bay, Villa Jamalu is equipped with everything required for a truly memorable family holiday. Even its name – a combination of the names of the owners’ three children – reflects the consideration that went into creating this fabulously well-appointed family retreat.</p><p>Children will adore the playroom, chock-full of toys, while adult and teenage guests will love the air-conditioned games room and entertainment den with its cornucopia of delights, including a pool table, 50-inch flat-screen television and PlayStation 3.</p><p>A workout in the well-equipped gym or some zen time in the dedicated yoga space could be just what the doctor ordered, or perhaps a tension-relieving Balinese massage in the private spa treatment room? &nbsp;</p><p>A state-of-the-art Bose sound system plays music throughout the villa, providing the perfect holiday playlist.&nbsp; Listen to some chill-out tunes whilst luxuriating on loungers shaded by capacious umbrellas or relax in the balé pavilion that hovers above the sparkling 15-metre swimming pool.&nbsp; Parents with youngsters can rest easy as the villa is equipped with a pool fence that can be erected to ensure the safety of little ones. And should a break from the tropical heat be desired, guests can slip indoors and savour the air-conditioned comfort of one of the many spacious living areas.</p><p>Alfresco dining on the top terrace at Villa Jamalu is an absolute treat: the villa’s private gourmet chef will prepare sumptuous meals which can be enjoyed at the twelve-seater dining table, or provide canapés to graze upon whilst sipping cocktails and lounging on the all-weather sofas as the sun sets magically over the ocean with Bali’s sacred Mount Batu Karu providing a mystical backdrop.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers roundtrip.</li>	<li>Welcome drink &amp; chilled towel upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily serving breakfast.</li>	<li>In-house chef serves breakfast, lunch and dinner, also capable of preparing a wide variety of Western and Asian dishes. Requests accommodated (including special diets).</li>	<li>Estate security guards providing 24-hour service.</li>	<li>Masseuse, Spa treatment, Yoga instructor and Babysitter on request (surcharge).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities&nbsp;</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool:&nbsp;15m x 7m salt chlorinated swimming pool.</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;&nbsp;3 downstairs bedrooms open out onto the pool area;&nbsp;study room with a single mattress daybed; 2 lounges; entertainment/games room; indoor dining for 12; outdoor living area; &nbsp;playroom/study; poolside&nbsp;balé.</li>	<li>Entertainments: &nbsp;Bose music system; iPod docking stations; 3 plasma TVs; DVD player and movies; books; pool table; gym; spa room; yoga space; PlayStation.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi broadband internet access in poolside entertainment/lounge room; local telephone calls.</li>	<li>Families: DVDs; books; games; toys; high chair; 2 cots; pool safety fence; baby monitor; children’s crockery.</li>	<li>Additional facilities:&nbsp;Large Bale;&nbsp;a double sunbed and umbrella;&nbsp;a hammock at pool level;&nbsp;Large outdoor dining with&nbsp;a 12 seater dining table;&nbsp;Gas BBQ;&nbsp;Outdoor rain shower;&nbsp;removable poolfence (imported from California;&nbsp;diesel powered generator provided.</li></ul>', '<div id="container"><div class="center" id="contentwrap"><div id="maincol"><p>Villa manager</p><p>Villa manager, Milani, has worked at Villa Jamalu since 2006 and is responsible for overall operations including staffing, special requests and guest satisfaction. Milani speaks excellent English.</p><p>Chef</p><p>Chef Komang has been preparing delicious Asian and Western cuisine at Villa Jamalu since 2008. She is at the villa daily to prepare breakfast, lunch and dinner and is very happy to accommodate special requests such as catering to dietary needs or devising dinner party menus.</p><p>Other staffs:&nbsp;Housekeeping/service staff; Gardener; Pool/maintenance; Estate Security guards providing 24-hour service. Masseuse, Yoga instructor and Babysitter on request</p></div><div class="clear">&nbsp;</div></div></div><div id="footerwrap">&nbsp;</div>', '<p><b>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</b></p><ul>	<li>Rates include of airport transfer, welcome drink &amp; chilled towel upon arrival,&nbsp;</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>All additional groceries and beverages are charged at cost price plus 20% charges for government tax and services.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 14:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 Noon</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and <b>subject to availability</b></li>	<li>Deposit and final payments are non-refundable (It is advisable to take out Travel insurance)</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.16222330', '-8.78737700', 8, 4, 4, 5, NULL, 6, '2016-09-19 16:41:23', '2016-09-23 13:01:14', NULL),
(53, 1, 'Hidden Hills Villas', 'hidden-hills-villas', 6, 1, '<p>These unique&nbsp;boutique villas, situated in the stunning hills of Uluwatu, are a family run resort business with each member coming from different parts of the world, making Hidden Hills Villas the best of many worlds. The resort has a fusion of quality and precision that comes from Switzerland, carries some of the exotic flavors that one can enjoy in Malaysia, holds the essence of ancient history and traditions deriving from China and Iran, has a hint of oriental vibe from Northern Africa and is like the cultural melting pot that is America, all coming together with the friendliness and spirituality of Bali.</p>', '<p>The Bukit (as it is commonly referred to) includes the famous cliff-hanging temple at Uluwatu, a number of Bali’s very best beaches, such as the famous Padang Padang Beach, as well as the top surfing spots on the island.</p><p>The area around Uluwatu is beautiful and offers spectacular ocean views from the cliff tops. Nearby is the famous Uluwatu Temple (5min), which is devoted to the Hindu Gods of the Sea and is considered by the Balinese, and visitors alike, to be one of the most magical temples on the island. The famous traditional Balinese Kecak dance is performed on the grounds of Uluwatu Temple every night at 6pm.</p><p>The Hidden Hills Villas locates in Uluwatu and individually designed and decorated to a specific theme and style. Guest will have their own exclusive living room, a comfortable and cozy bedroom with canopied king size beds, a beautifully appointed bathroom, a lush tropical garden with a private pool and incredible views of the ocean.</p><p>In order to save the natural environment, our villas&nbsp;have been partially constructed from recycled timber and other materials sourced from within Bali. We utilize solar panels to power parts of our resort as well.</p><p>Hidden Hills Villas is a luxurious retreat with both traditional and modern styles, combining design elements from all over the world to achieve a unique energy and look for each villa, affirming our slogan, “Bringing the World Together in Bali.”</p><p>Our staff are trained to take pride and ownership in their work and to meet the service quality demanded which is to serve each guest with passion and respect.</p><p>These demanding service standards would not be possible without treating our staff with respect and providing them with a happy and conducive work environment.</p><p>Hidden Hills Villas provides not only nightly accomodation, but for wedding ceremony as well for capacity about 40 guests, honeymoon package, and other festive days like Christmast and New Years Eve.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfer: round trip.</li>	<li>Welcome drink and refreshment towel once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast&nbsp;in-house.</li>	<li>Butler service, catering to your discerning needs with&nbsp;personalized&nbsp;attention.</li>	<li>24 hours security.</li>	<li>Daily Housekeeping.</li>	<li>Arranging and serving for Wedding Ceremony, Dining for&nbsp;Christmast Eve&nbsp;and New&nbsp;Years Celebration, and other events &amp; occassions.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: every villa has a&nbsp;private pool.</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;living room with kitchenette, lounge, dining areas and en-suite bathroom,&nbsp;cookware, dishware, utensils,&nbsp;stovetop, refrigerator, mini bar, expresso maker,&nbsp;</li>	<li>Entertainment:&nbsp;flat screen LED Smart TV’s with Global channels.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi</li>	<li>Families: Cribs/infant beds (surcharge);&nbsp;Rollaway/extra beds (surcharge).</li>	<li>Other facilities: Hair Dryer, toiletry, bathrobe, slippers.</li>	<li>Hidden Hills Villa Spa</li>	<li>Garden for weddings and other occassions for up to 40 guests (Villa Marrakesh).</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Joglo (1 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our Joglo is our only Javanese style studio villa. Although the Joglo does not have a private pool, it comes with your own personal jacuzzi, 400 thread count sateen sheets, therapedic mattresses and wonderful ocean views.</p><p><strong>Santorini (1 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our 1 bedroom villas are some of the most spacious you will find in this price category, which is why they are called&nbsp;deluxe 1 bedroom villas. They include a large garden, private pool, incredible sunset views, all bedrooms have king size beds and flat screen LED Smart TV’s, a living room with kitchenette, lounge, dining areas and of course your beautiful en suite bathroom.</p><p><strong>Marrakesh (1 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our 1 bedroom villas are some of the most spacious you will find in this price category, which is why they are called&nbsp;deluxe 1 bedroom villas. They include a large garden, private pool, incredible sunset views, all bedrooms have king size beds and flat screen LED Smart TV’s, a living room with kitchenette, lounge, dining areas and of course your beautiful en suite bathroom.</p><p><strong>Sekapa (2 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our 2 bedroom villas are ideal for bringing family or friends along. This choice will give you the luxury of two bedrooms, both equipped with flat screen LED Smart TV’s, king size beds and wonderful views of Bali’s magical sunsets. Each bedroom has its en-suite semi indoor/outdoor bathroom with lavish bathtubs that overlook that magnificent Indian Ocean. The living rooms are ideal for hanging out with your loved ones, come equipped with a kitchenette and will give you the tropical Bali feeling you have come to experience and enjoy.</p><p><strong>Sanya (2 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our 2 bedroom villas are ideal for bringing family or friends along. This choice will give you the luxury of two bedrooms, both equipped with flat screen LED Smart TV’s, king size beds and wonderful views of Bali’s magical sunsets. Each bedroom has its en-suite semi indoor/outdoor bathroom with lavish bathtubs that overlook that magnificent Indian Ocean. The living rooms are ideal for hanging out with your loved ones, come equipped with a kitchenette and will give you the tropical Bali feeling you have come to experience and enjoy.</p><p><strong>Grande (3 Bedroom Villa)</strong></p><p>Our 3-bedroom villa is truly our grandest villa, not just in size but also in regard of its features. 3 comfy bedrooms, two having unobstructed ocean views, each room comes equipped with a flat screen LED Smart TV, including en-suite bathrooms with lavish bathtubs, a grand and spacious living room with a fully equipped kitchen, a huge garden and even quarters for your own staff.</p>', '<ul>	<li>A villa manager</li>	<li>A chef</li>	<li>Butlers &amp;&nbsp;Housekeepers</li>	<li>Gardener/pool attendant</li>	<li>A driver</li>	<li>Securities</li>	<li>Spa therapists</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers, breakfast for 2 persons, free WiFi, &nbsp;</li>	<li>Rates are subjects 15.5% government tax &amp; services.</li>	<li>Arriving/leaving:&nbsp;Check-in time 2 PM-11 PM,&nbsp;Check-out time is noon.</li>	<li>The front desk is open daily from 7 AM - 11 PM</li>	<li>24-hour airport shuttle service is available.</li>	<li>In accordance with local regulations, all visitors must remain within the hotel property during Seclusion Day/Hindu New Year on March 28, 2017 (from midnight March 27, 2017 to early morning March 29, 2017). Check-in and check-out will not be possible on March 28, 2017.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Required at check in:&nbsp;Credit card or cash deposit required,&nbsp;Government-issued photo ID required, and&nbsp;Minimum check-in age is 18.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.11733030', '-8.82142100', 6, 3, 4, 15, NULL, 5, '2016-09-19 16:49:45', '2016-09-24 05:38:05', NULL),
(54, 1, 'Suluban Clifftop Bali Villa', 'suluban-clifftop-bali-villa', 6, 0, '<p>Nestled on the south west tip of Bali known as the Bukit, <strong>Suluban Cliff Villa</strong> is everpresent oceanview villa.<br />Overlooking Padang Padang Beach and beyond to the vista of Labuhan Sait and Bukit coastline ; these among the earth''s top surfing spots.&nbsp;To the villa''s west, watch the stunning Uluwatu sunsets and to the north, Bali''s mountain peaks of Mount Agung and Batukaru.&nbsp;<br /><br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Suluban Cliff Villa is located in South West Bukit Peninsula of South Bali,&nbsp;between Uluwatu and Padang Padang which are world class surfers’ beaches.</p><p>Set on the shores of the Bali Sea, this sophisticated resort occupies ultramodern suites and a villa, and lies 2.3 km from Padang Padang Beach, 11 km from the ancient Hindu temple Pura&nbsp;Luhur Uluwatu and 12 km from the Garuda Wisnu Kencana park.<br /><br />Colorful suites have sleek en suite bathrooms, and feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screens and safes. A suite includes a minifridge, while the villa adds a designer kitchen, a living area, and a dining area with scenic views and wine chillers.</p><p>The oceanfront pool terrace is such a vantage viewing deck of the rolling surf and the receding tides off Suluban Beach and beyond.&nbsp;Spot the marine life or feast on the stunning panaromic view of the Indian Ocean and north Bali skyline.Watch fishermen wade in the receding tide and fishing boats go by for their daily catch.&nbsp;As you lounge at our clifftop pool terrace, enjoy that ever constant ocean breeze.</p><p>The Suluban Cliff Edge Bale is truly the most spectacular setting to lounge &amp; chill out for that sunset cocktail or al-fresco dining.&nbsp;Only glass boundary panels separate the cliff face ensuring unhindered vista of the ocean below.&nbsp;Beyond the Bale are the cliff front lawns and garden spaces perfect for that cocktail party. In addition, to a casual, ocean-view restaurant, amenities include an ultramodern, glass-fronted infinity pool, a viewing deck and spa services.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary Airport transfers: pick up and drop off.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks &amp; refereshment towel once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>Car and driver hire is available upon request, charges apply</li>	<li>Regular laundry, pressing and drycleaning services are available (surcharge).</li>	<li>Massages and spa treatments (at cost).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools: cascading reflecting pool;&nbsp;glass-fronted infinity pool;&nbsp;elevated pool terrace.</li>	<li>Living areas:&nbsp;main villa and terrace;&nbsp;4 stand alone bedroom suites; digital deposit safe; fully equipped Kitchen; dispenser; refrigerator.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;42” Philips LCD TV and Philips HD DVD player;&nbsp;Satellite TV Channels; For Main Villa -&nbsp;52” Philips LCD TV with HD Philips DVD/VCD player, and&nbsp;Quad Hi-Fi system offering CD and iPod&nbsp;Playability.</li>	<li>Communications: Wireless High-speed Internet Access.</li>	<li>Support facilities: cliff front lawn;&nbsp;cliff edge dining bale &amp; bar;&nbsp;a spa pavilion.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>A villa manager</li>	<li>A chef</li>	<li>Housekeepers</li>	<li>Gardener/pool attendant</li>	<li>A driver</li>	<li>Securities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include Complimentary airport transfers,&nbsp;</li>	<li>Rates are subjected to 15.5% tax and service charges.</li>	<li>50% deposit of the total rental outlay will be required to secure reservation.&nbsp;</li>	<li>For Low Season bookings, final payment is required 15 days prior to check-in or immediately if booking is made less than 15 days to check in dates.For High Season bookings, final payment is required 20 days prior to check-in, or immediately if the booking is made less than 20 days prior to check-in.&nbsp;For Peak Season bookings, final payment is required 30 days prior to check-in.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.08890030', '-8.81396300', 8, 4, 4, 10, NULL, 5, '2016-09-19 17:30:36', '2016-09-23 13:21:27', NULL),
(55, 1, 'Villa Blue Lagoon Balangan', 'villa-blue-lagoon-balangan', 5, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Blue Lagoon Balangan</strong> has&nbsp;experience the singular universe of this modern tropical architectural villa in complete harmony with its environment. Be sure of an unforgettable stay when you rent this villa.This villa incorporates the indoor &amp; outdoor living concept and was designed by a well renowned international architect. Indoors and outdoors flow into one another creating a perfect harmony between nature, the villa and its occupants.&nbsp; Every room is adaptable to a modern day rhythm of live. You can choose to use the air-conditioning while closing everything or leave everything open and permit the air to circulate freely.</p>', '<p>The transparency of this villa’s structure permits you to live indoors while giving you the impression of living outdoors. The staircase is made of native logs and because of being placed partly inside and partly outside, this staircase brings a unique transparency and privacy to this villa. Because of this emplacement the air can circulate freely through the villa, which is extremely pleasant during periods of high temperatures.</p><p>The garden was created by a renowned landscape artist. Of Indonesian background and based in Bali, he worked exclusively with local plants that can only be found in Bukit near the Balangan area. While walking in this tropical garden you can experience several things: Frangipani trees (more than 100 years old), Flamboyant in full growth, red Hibiscus, coconut trees, palm trees, Aloe Vera, pink and purple Bougainvillea, white or orange flowers with sweet scents.</p><p>1. Amazing viewpoints</p><ul>	<li>Sea view and view of the sunset for the 2 master bedrooms, the swimming pool and the West terrace;</li>	<li>Panoramic view on the roof top;</li>	<li>Sunrise and view of the Bukit countryside from the East terrace;</li>	<li>Garden views from the 2 other bedrooms.</li></ul><p>2. Natural materials</p><p>Polished concrete floor, suspended ceiling with LED, wooden decorated ceiling in the living room, suspended concrete stairs, local wood decorating the staircase, exposed metal structure (I-BEAM).</p><p>3. Geometric and purified forms:</p><p>The rounded East terrace, triangular advanced Master bedrooms facing the sea at the horizon, the rectangular staircase, the play of vertical light and shadow beams displaying over the staircase…</p><p>4. Natural and soothing colours:</p><p>Sand, shades of gray, blue lagoon, beige, taupe, white.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers: pick up &amp; drop off.</li>	<li>Food starter pack.</li>	<li>Tourist Assisting.</li>	<li>Free carparks.</li>	<li>The cook will be able preparing&nbsp;Western, Asian cusines, and specialist amazing Balinese foods.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool:&nbsp;The pool with its salt water and infinity L-style size 16&nbsp;x 4 meters.</li>	<li>Entertainment: 50 Inch 3D TV; Bose sound system or the IPod Dock.</li>	<li>Living areas: living room, dining area, high table and kitchen are equipped with centralized air-conditioning take up more than 80m² with an almost 7 meters high ceiling; the kitchen is equipped with every modern day utilities: induction cooking surface, upscale oven, American style refrigerator, water boiler, blender, mixer, juicer;&nbsp;a second dining table can be found outside (8 people) with sea view;&nbsp;the office, conference room.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi.</li>	<li>Other facilities: Parking area; Gym</li></ul><p><strong>Facilities Detail Description</strong></p><p><strong>The Master bedrooms</strong></p><p>The two Master bedrooms are situated on the first floor.&nbsp;Accessible through the suspended staircase, indoors &amp; outdoors, protected by an assembly of wood and with a bridge made of concrete, metal and glass...these two big Master bedrooms are mirrors of one another. One can be found in the left aisle and the other can be found in the right aisle.</p><p>Both of them have sea view, a big equipped bathroom (bath and shower) and a terrace ideal for a romantic sunset get away. The New Kuta Golf is also visible.&nbsp;Surface (per bedroom): 45 m².&nbsp;From the bathrooms you can admire the sea and the sunset.&nbsp;Both beds ( 2 by 2) have sea view and are very comfortable.&nbsp;Central air-conditioning system.</p><p dir="ltr"><strong>The Junior&nbsp;bedrooms</strong></p><p>The two Junior bedrooms are on the ground floor and have a garden view.&nbsp;Both of them are equipped with a big shower room and lavatory. The comfort of the beds will make you feel extremely fit during the day.&nbsp;Area: 25 &amp; 20m 2<br />They are all equipped with AC.&nbsp;Equipped with:&nbsp;Hand and beach towels, bathrobe, hairdryer, sheets.</p><p><strong>Livingroom, Dining area, Kitchen</strong></p><p>The living areas are the common areas of the Blue Lagoon Villa.&nbsp;The principal area is quite majestic:&nbsp;Its living room, open kitchen and dining space take up more than 80m² with an almost 7 meters high ceiling.&nbsp;The kitchen is equipped with every modern day utilities: induction cooking surface, upscale oven, American style refrigerator, water boiler, blender, mixer, juicer.... the cook, or yourself, will be able to prepare amazing Balinese dishes.</p><p>You can eat quickly in the kitchen using the high table.&nbsp;The dining room is occupied by a veritable piece of art: a black massif Oak table of 3 meters long. (8 people)&nbsp;Television corner: a big corner sofa can be found opposite a 50 Inch 3D TV. You can enjoy your favourite music, inside and outside, through the Bose sound system or the IPod Dock.&nbsp;</p><p>The transparent sliding doors create the perfect harmony between the villa and its surrounding tropical nature. With open access to the garden, pool and West terrace. A second dining table can be found outside (8 people) with sea view, towards the Balangan beach, which is perfect for Indonesian style diners during sunset. On the other hand, why not use the Eastern terrace side with its Garden view and cool shade starting from 3 o’clock in the afternoon. The ideal place to take afternoon tea with the whole family. The open sliding doors, which touch the indoor &amp; outdoor corridor of the Junior bedrooms, create a natural aeration with the fresh air coming from the Balangan hills. This is very welcoming during high temperatures.&nbsp;Living room, dining area and kitchen are equipped with centralized air-conditioning.</p><p><strong>Roof Top</strong></p><p>The &nbsp;suspended staircase which will lead you to the roof terrace with panoramic view of the area.&nbsp;You can admire the sunset or practice a morning Yoga session.</p><ul>	<li>South: you have the New Kuta Golf</li>	<li>West: you have the sea in the direction of Balangan beach and Java (with clear skies)</li>	<li>North West: you have Kuta, Seminyak, Jimbaran...with frequent fireworks and Chinese lantern launches...</li>	<li>North: you have the chain of volcanoes (Agung,...) with clear skies</li>	<li>East: you have the Bukit countryside and the sunrise</li></ul><p><strong>Cabana by the Pool</strong></p><p>Here you can enjoy the pool on a big corner sofa (6 people) while being protected from the sun or rain (in the wet season). &nbsp;The pool with its salt water and infinity L-style is ideal for long breast strokes while looking out at the sea in the direction of the Balangan beach.&nbsp;Size :16x4m.&nbsp;It is protect by the Master 1 terrace &amp; the cabana in order to have the ideal temperature.</p><p><strong>The Office</strong></p><p>The office, conference room looks out over the pool with stunning views of the sea. This room almost seems to float. It is a quiet room and has air-conditioning.</p><p><strong>The Gym</strong></p><p>The gym is hidden behind the Zen Garden at the end of the stairs to the right of the pool. It is equipped with high-end PrimaFit-Fitness Elliptical Bike* &amp; Full weight press.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Villa manager</li>	<li>	<p>Cook</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>House keeping</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>Security guards</p>	</li>	<li>	<p>Pool &amp; Garden maintenance.</p>	</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include Complimentary airport transfers, food starter pack, tourist assistance, all tax and services,&nbsp;private shuttle between the international airport Ngurah Rai, Denpasar, and the villa Blue Lagoon, situated in the Bukit peninsula.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;<strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Late check-out subject to availability.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.12495720', '-8.79323130', 8, 4, 2, 7, NULL, 5, '2016-09-19 19:59:45', '2016-09-23 13:29:55', NULL),
(56, 1, 'Oazia Spa Villa', 'oazia-spa-villa', 2, 1, '<p>Welcome to OAZIA, a sanctuary of luxury living on the magical island of Bali. OAZIA Spa Villas is an opulent, designer lifestyle resort that is private and special. With only 3 villas, our guests enjoy a richness of feeling and comfort here that is often felt in your own home. OAZIA embodies the concept of SPA LIVING – the philosophy of having balance in all areas of one''s life. Our intent is for every guest at OAZIA to have the opportunity to completely rejuvenate mind, body and soul, by means of personal development programs and holistic therapies.</p><p>Whatever inspires you to learn more about yourself, whether it be learning to draw, to write or even to surf, here at OAZIA we have created a haven where all can be realized.<br /><br />We offer an extensive range of activities both holistic and adventurous. Allow us to tailor a complete agenda to suit whatever dream you want to follow.</p>', '<p>Oazia Spa Villas is a luxurious Spa villa with amazing design property in the hand of Interior Designer Veronika Blomgren from Rusia. Located in Kerobokan area 15 minutes&nbsp;to Eco beach and&nbsp;to Seminyak&nbsp;restaurant. The Spa villa established in 2009 consisting of 3 villas with different amazing designing with full Spa services menus, handling&nbsp;by&nbsp;highly trained and professional&nbsp;staffs pampering your holiday,&nbsp;body and your soul.</p><p>VILLA WHITE - 2 BEDROOMS</p><p>Villa White sets on both sides of a tranquil river, wrapped in the scent of frangipani and gardenia, in the shade of palm trees and bamboo groves, Villa Oazia White is best described as Utopia. The garden is filled with birdsong in the mornings and the sounds of dancing river flow at night time. The bamboo canopy creates beautiful shadows over a grand dining table, in a pavilion where lavish meals are served under ornate crystal chandeliers and twinkling candlelight. Adjacent is a beautiful white bale, piled with soft white cushions – a perfect place for afternoon meditation or a late night talk with your best friend.<br /><br />The 13 x 5m pool becomes a huge mirror at night, reflecting frangipani trees and softly draping curtains. The combination of white fabrics, limestone, natural aged timbers, antiques and modern art creates an atmosphere of dreaminess and charm. Villa OAZIA White has 2 master bedrooms and 2 separate guest rooms which are accessed over a stunning river bridge. All have unique open-air ensuites and bathtubs, so guests can soak in seclusion.<br /><br />Villa OAZIA White is great for families and perfect for gatherings of friends. Villa White is also a special venue for weddings and ceremonies where the exchange of vows can be in a 100 year old Javanese Joglo Pavilion, on a floating platform over the huge pool, or on the river bridge that separates the main pavilion from the guest rooms.</p><h3>VILLA AQUA - 2 BEDROOMS</h3><p>Villa OAZIA Aqua is all about colour. Guests enter the Villa through ornate carved doors into the water garden brimming with violet water-lilies and colourful Koi. Giant urns filled with neon-like bougainvillea are offset by the turquoise water of the swimming pool, reflecting the sky and palm trees.</p><p>Villa Aqua is also about expanse - the soaring open plan living room is filled with over-size antique sofas and décor. The 7 meter high pavilion also houses a fully equipped kitchen and 2 master bedrooms with open-air ensuites. Adjacent to the pool is a separate pavilion, traditional in Balinese design, open-air with an alang-alang roof and cool stone floors. Meals are served around a grand dining table or perhaps in the garden under the stars. Villa OAZIA Aqua is filled with contemporary pieces and curious antique décor and is, in itself, a work of art</p><p>VILLA ORCHID - 1 BEDROOM</p><p>Villa OAZIA Orchid is a traditional Javanese Joglo House. Designed with romance in mind, Villa Orchid is decorated in Balinese sculptures, antique classical pieces and adorned with delicate rare white orchids. Secret nooks provide private places to dine, to admire and to breathe in the natural beauty of the environment. Villa Orchid as well as a having its own huge pool, also has a private roof-top platform where guests can while away the afternoon watching the river glide by or gazing at the working rice fields.<br /><br />A true haven of harmony and love, guests can choose to enjoy spa treatments in their private garden or dine by candlelight under a swaying bamboo canopy. The air-conditioned bedroom is intimate and sumptuous – seemingly a cocoon unto itself, whilst the outdoor bathroom is almost fairy-tale.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Fast track service at Airport on arrival&nbsp;(additional cost).</li>	<li>Daily serving in-house Breakfast.</li>	<li>Daily serving exotic fruits.</li>	<li>Complimentary bottle of wine, and&nbsp;Fresh flowers.</li>	<li>Complimentary Bali cell phone during your stay.</li>	<li>Free of charge a car service available for pick up and drop off at local shopping/restaurant areas from 8am – 10pm (additional hours available at USD $10/hour).</li>	<li>Babysitter if required from 8am until 5pm&nbsp;(USD $7/additional hour)</li>	<li>Complimentary Balinese Massage per person.</li>	<li>Personal Assistant in attendance during your stay.</li>	<li>24h Security&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: private infinity swimming pools with towel; daybeds.</li>	<li>Living areas: 1 - 2 Air-conditioned bedrooms with en-suite bathrooms; lounge and dining areas with fully equipped kitchen;&nbsp;outdoor dining areas.</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;TV/DVD/CD with a selection of movies and music;&nbsp;sound system with iPhone docks.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi</li>	<li>Other facilities: minibar and snacks;&nbsp;organic, high-quality bath products; electronic safety box</li>	<li>OAZIA Spa: Spa &amp;&nbsp;Holistic menu; Moon Spa.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>A villa manager</li>	<li>A spa manager</li>	<li>Butlers &amp; House keepers</li>	<li>Therapists</li>	<li>Gardener / Pool attendant</li>	<li>A driver</li>	<li>Securities</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Rates, checking in and out&nbsp;</strong></p><ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers, other complimentaries, and using villa facilities.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 15.5% VAT and service charge.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 2:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 11:00 AM</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;subject to availability.</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>LOW SEASON&nbsp;January 16 - June 30;&nbsp;September 16 - December 19.</li>	<li>HIGH SEASON&nbsp;July 1 - 31;&nbsp;September 1 - 15;&nbsp;Chinese New Year; and Easter.</li>	<li>PEAK SEASON&nbsp;August 1 - 31;&nbsp;December 20 - January 15.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.15645220', '-8.64592180', 4, 2, 5, 15, NULL, 7, '2016-09-19 22:54:36', '2016-10-04 18:44:25', NULL),
(57, 1, 'Villa Sin Sin', 'villa-sin-sin', 2, 1, '<p>Villa Sin Sin is three luxurious villas nestled into a dreamy compound surrounded by rice paddies. They are the creation of Hong Kong based designer Sin Sin in collaboration with star-architect Gianni Francione. The beaches are close and so are temples and Bali''s stunning culture.&nbsp;</p><p>Sin Sin Man has a amazingl taste of art, she created&nbsp;a distinctly artistic feeling in all houses through carefully placed and chosen pieces of contemporary and antique art. The villas are landscape surrounded by lush green rice paddies, an ideal hideaway for one to rejuvenate and rediscover the lost pace of life.</p>', '<p>The three grand villas (1000 square meters and two bedrooms each) are furbished with artworks picked by the owner. They have their own private spacious pools.</p><p>Hot spring-style relaxing indoor / outdoor bathrooms in intimate settings help you regain your balance. Balinese artefacts and teak structures blend into nature. It all reflects Sin Sin\\''s way of sensuous living.</p><p>This personalized approach to design and exquisite service separates the Villa Sin Sin paradise from other resorts in Bali. It creates an ideal and unforgettable atmosphere for a private and stress-free vacation.</p><p>Created by Hong Kong-based designer Sin Sin and architect Gianni Francione, the beautiful Villa Sin Sin offers free Wi-Fi, a private pool and spa bathtubs. Enjoying views of the quiet rice paddies of Krobokan, it has pampering in-villa spa treatments</p><p>Fully air-conditioned, the spacious villa features a kitchenette and an open-concept living room decorated with fine artwork. A flat-screen TV, DVD player and iPod dock are included. Indoor/outdoor bathrooms overlook the tropical gardens.</p><p>Villa Sin Sin is a 20-minute drive from Kuta area and a 30-minute drive from Ngurah Rai International Airport. Car rentals with drivers and airport transfers can be arranged at an extra charge.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Complimentary private airport transfers roundtrip.</li>	<li>Meet and greet upon arrival.</li>	<li>Complimentary welcome drinks, and in the room serves&nbsp;fresh tropical fruits basket.</li>	<li>Serving daily sunrise Breakfast.</li>	<li>Special dietary meals and gourmet dining can also be arranged.</li>	<li>Speaking English staffs.</li>	<li>The villa manager will help you plan your activities during your exclusive stay<strong>*</strong>.</li>	<li>If you have special gourmet requests, our chef will cater to your tastes.</li>	<li>For family holidays, baby-sitting service is available (surcharge).</li>	<li>Arranging rent a car services with English speaking driver (cost extra).</li>	<li>Assisting, organizing and serving for special events like weddings, conferences and seminars.</li></ul><p><strong>*</strong>Kind of activities the Villa Manager will plan assisting:</p><ul>	<li>Rafting;&nbsp;Diving and snorkeling;&nbsp;Surfing Iesson&nbsp;with instructor at Odysseys Surf School</li>	<li>Full day cruise with choice of activites</li>	<li>Private yacht charter - relaxing on a sailing yacht;&nbsp;Helicopter charter</li>	<li>Golf - Le Meridian Nirwana Golf Course</li>	<li>Pony / horse riding - 5 minutes from Villa Sin Sin</li>	<li>Pottery classes;&nbsp;Batik painting sections</li>	<li>Yoga sessions</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pool: swimming pool with bale and daybeds.</li>	<li>Living areas: artistic building, open concepts of&nbsp;living area, decorative&nbsp;bathrooms,&nbsp;dining (outdoor, terrace and in-villa), fully equipped kitchen.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi, mobile phone, fax and Internet.</li>	<li>Other facilities: Private parking on site; Safety deposit box: tour desk; Restaurant (ala carte); Barbecue facilities.</li>	<li>Body and beauty treatments like massages, manicure, pedicure, facial and hair beauty treatments in out villa.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>A villa manager</li>	<li>A chef</li>	<li>Housekeepers</li>	<li>Gardener / Pool attendant</li>	<li>A driver</li>	<li>Securities</li></ul>', '<p><b>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</b></p><ul>	<li>Rates include complimentary airport transfers on arrival and departure, meet &amp; greet upon arrival, welcome drinks, fresh tropical fruits basket, and daily sunrise Breakfast.</li>	<li>Subjects are&nbsp;10% tax and 5% service charges.</li>	<li>Booking is confirmed after full payment of the full stay plus tax is received within 7 days upon reservation.</li>	<li>Check-in:&nbsp;after 14:00</li>	<li>Check-out:&nbsp;Until 12:00 hours</li>	<li>Early check-in or late check-out is available on request and is subject to availability</li>	<li>No cancellation is possible. All reservation must be guaranteed with a non-refundable payment of the full stay plus tax at the time of booking. Non-guaranteed reservations are not accepted.</li>	<li>Pets are allowed on request. Charges may be applicable.</li></ul><p><b>Seasons</b></p><ul>	<li>Low season: from 11th Jan to 30th Jun (except Easter &amp; Chinese New Year) and from 16th Sep to 19th Dec.</li>	<li>High season: from 1st Jul to 15th Sep, Easter week and Chinese New Year Week.</li>	<li>Peak season: from&nbsp;20th Dec to 10th Jan.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.16010710', '-8.66342680', 4, 2, 5, 10, NULL, 7, '2016-09-19 23:33:28', '2016-09-23 13:40:30', NULL),
(58, 0, 'Ametis Villa', 'ametis-villa', 2, 0, '<p>Located in Canggu, Ametis Villa is about 35 minutes from Kuta. This area maintains its cultural roots and is dotted with productive rice terraces that extend to a rugged stretch of coastline. Canggu is popular within surfing and expatriate circles, sought out for its laidback lifestyle qualities away from the crowds and concrete jungle of Seminyak.</p><p>Ametis Villa is a luxury lifestyle villa with a home-style concept that will make you feel like you truly belong. During your stay, you will be assigned a personal butler, who excels in the singular ability to anticipate your every need, and to exceed your every expectation.</p>', '<p>Conceived, built and managed with integrity, Ametis Villa is respectful of Bali''s unique cultural heritage, seeks to interact with the local community and shows sensitivity towards the immediate environment.</p><p>This property is 3 minutes walk from the beach. Located within walking distance to Batu Bolong Beach, luxurious Ametis Villa features 24-hour private butler service and offers airport shuttle service. It houses villas with large outdoor private pools. It also offers free shuttle services within Canggu, Seminyak.</p><p>Villas at Ametis are fitted with a flat-screen TV with DVD player, minibar and safety deposit box. They come with a living and dining area, and a spacious spa bathroom.</p><p>Guests can learn how to cook traditional local meals, or enjoy a relaxing massage at the spa. The lobby has a library area for some quiet reading. Butler service is available 24 hours.</p><p>Eternal restaurant serves lndonesian dishes. These are made from fresh ingredients that are grown in the villa’s own garden or bought at the Jimbaran Bay seafood market every morning.</p><p>Ametis Villa is a 3-minutes drive from Echo Beach in Canggu and is a 30-minute drive from Ngurah Rai International Airport.&nbsp;</p><p>This property is also rated for the best value in Canggu! Guests are getting more for their money when compared to other properties in this city.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Grand Villa</strong></p><p>The Grand Villa is a private haven designed to accommodate you and a small group of discerning travellers. The sheer size of this villa, with its elevated swimming pool and smart upstairs living environment, lends itself to a privileged brand of tropical luxury on the island of Bali.</p><p>Number of units: 2 sets of Premiere and Premiere Inter-Connecting, 2 sets of Premiere and Imperial Inter-Connecting<br />Number of units: 1<br />Villa Size: 550 square meters<br />Pool Size: L. 10m W: 4m D: 1.5m<br />Bed Type: King beds in master and second bedrooms, twin beds in third bedroom<br /><br />Maximum occupants:<br />4 adults + 2 children* for two bedrooms usage<br />6 adults + 2 children* for three bedrooms usage<br />*Aged between 12 to 16 years old, sleeping on sofa bed</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Inter-connecting villas</strong></p><p>Inter-connecting villas are ideal if you are travelling with friends or family and want to stay in close proximity to each other. A convenient placed sliding door in the wall links each villa but also can be closed at night to maintain a degree of privacy whilst sleeping.<br /><br />&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Imperial Villa</strong></p><p>The slightly larger Imperial Villa ensures that your every conceivable need is anticipated before it is even realised. Ideally this villa category will suit those who appreciate the finer things that life has to offer. A generous living space and gourmet kitchen provide some necessary comforts from home.<br /><br />Number of units: 5<br />Villa Size: 400 square meters<br />Pool Size: L. 13m W: 4m D: 1.4m<br />Bed Type: King<br />Maximum occupants: 2 adults + 1 child*<br />*Aged between 12 to 16 years old, sleeping on sofa bed</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Premiere Villa</strong></p><p>The Premiere Villa is a stylish retreat that is perfect if you are a honeymoon couple starting a new life together. You will be left entirely to your own devices to take pleasure in a modern bedroom suite complete with a lavish bathroom. A separate living area with gourmet kitchen overlooks the refreshing waters of the pool.<br /><br />Number of units: 8<br />Villa Size: 350 square meters<br />Pool Size: L. 13m W: 4m D: 1.4m<br />Bed Type: King<br />Maximum occupants: 2 adults</p>', '<ul>	<li>Return airport transfer with Ametis exclusive private car</li>	<li>Personal butler service</li>	<li>Personalised villa check-in and check-out</li>	<li>24 hours drop and pick-up service within the Canggu and Seminyak areas.</li>	<li>30 minute relaxing massage</li>	<li>Welcome treats (choose your preferred cocktail or mocktail upon your arrival. A chilled towel will refresh you after a long flight.)</li>	<li>Daily breakfast with a variety of menus to choose from (We offer you variety of breakfast menus, which will be served in the comfort of your villa or at Eternal restaurant. Should you have an early morning departure, we will prepare a breakfast box to take with you.)</li>	<li>Afternoon tea and sunset cocktail (Complimentary afternoon tea and a sunset cocktail are available every day).</li>	<li>Afternoon tea: 15:00 to 18:00 hours</li>	<li>Sunset cocktail: 18:00 to 20:00 hours</li>	<li>Complimentary home-made cookies, as well as dried fruits and nuts, which are available in your bedroom. These treats are also available as souvenirs to take home. (Please contact your butler to place an order.)</li>	<li>Coffee and tea (Our Ametis original blend of Indonesian coffee and a variety of teas are available in your villa kitchen).</li>	<li>Daily fresh fruit and flower arrangement in villa</li>	<li>Daily Newspaper (based on your language preference)</li>	<li>Complimentary use of mountain bike</li>	<li>Languages spoken: English, Indonesian &amp; Japanese</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Spacious landscaped compound</li>	<li>Private swimming pool and space to soak up the sun</li>	<li>Integrated semi-outdoor living and dining environment with gourmet kitchen</li>	<li>Separate air-conditioned master bedroom</li>	<li>Spa inspired en-suite bathroom with double vanities, shower booth and bathtub</li>	<li>Home entertainment system with movies</li>	<li>Flat screen television with satellite channels&nbsp;</li>	<li>Apple iPod and Harman Kardon iPod dock</li>	<li>Tea and coffee making facilities</li>	<li>Mini bar and refrigerator</li>	<li>Ametis original bathroom amenities</li>	<li>Electronic safety deposit box</li>	<li>WiFi access, 24h daily</li>	<li>Complimentary Mini Bar</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Villa Features on Request</strong></p><ul>	<li>Canopied bed</li>	<li>Sofa bed is available for child age between 12 to 16 years old at additional charge</li>	<li>Twin bed is available and subject to availability&nbsp;</li>	<li>Accommodation at Ametis Villa is available for guest aged 12 and above</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Personal butler service	<p>Our unique brand of hospitality starts before you even arrive in Bali with your personal butler sending you a courtesy email and photo as a special introduction. He will then be there waiting for you at the airport to welcome and escort you to Ametis Villa. This exceptional level of service will continue throughout your entire duration of stay to ensure an exceptional holiday experience. Once you have check-out, your personal butler will also send you a thank you letter wishing you farewell and a safe journey. This is often the beginning of a lasting friendship</p>	</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong></p><ul>	<li>Should you need to cancel your stay, as long as you do so before the hotel’s cancellation policy comes into effect, this deposit will be refunded in full</li>	<li>A 50% deposit is required for all stays during peak season (20 December - 10 January).</li>	<li>Tax 21% included</li>	<li>Rooms are non-smoking, guests can smoke on their terrace or balcony</li>	<li>Pets are not permitted</li>	<li>Tax at 21% includes 11% local tax ad a 10% service charge</li>	<li>Accommodation at Ametis Villa is suitable for guest aged 12 years old and above</li>	<li>Children aged between 12 and 16 years old can stay on a soda bed in their parents’ villa, or in the Imperial or Grand Villa (at an additional charge of US$75 a person, each night, including daily breakfast and afternoon tea) or stay separately with their parents in an independent villa</li>	<li>Eternal home-style dining and the Ametis Lounge are available for all ages, although under 12s must be accompanied by their parents or a guardian</li>	<li>Villas cannot accommodate a third adult</li>	<li>Extra beds are not allowed</li>	<li>No check-ins or check-outs are allowed on 28 March 2017, when Bali observes Nyepi Day (Day of Silence), although stays are still possible. Bali’s airport also closes for the day.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.12916420', '-8.65674310', NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, 7, '2016-09-20 00:09:25', '2016-09-20 00:09:25', NULL);
