(59, 1, 'Villa Maridadi', 'villa-maridadi', 2, 1, '<p><strong>Villa Maridadi</strong>&nbsp;is one of Bali''s very few absolute oceanfront Villas located in Cemagi with access to Mengening Beach.&nbsp;Villa Maridadi is located just beyond the quiet and picturesque Balinese Village of Mengening along a winding village road lined with paddyfields and featuring substantial Balinese Temples and massive Banyan Tress.&nbsp;</p><p>Only approx 30 minutes from the many popular restaurants and shops of Seminyak and and approximately 45 minutes drive drive to Ngurah Rai International Airport . For the golf enthusiasts, the Nirwana Bali Golf Course - The Le Meridian Hotel and the famous Tanah Lot Temple are less than a 10 minutes drive. The Nusa Dua Golf Club and Bali Handara Golf Course are an equidistant 1 hour''s drive away.</p>', '<p>The word&nbsp;<em>maridadi&nbsp;</em>means beautiful in Swahili, and Villa Maridadi more than lives up to its name.&nbsp; This stunning five-bedroom residence with traditional&nbsp;<em>alang-alang&nbsp;</em>thatched roofs, lush tropical gardens, generous green-stone swimming pool, lavish living spaces and spectacular ocean views exudes beauty from every pore.</p><p>Set on 4,100 square metres in the sleepy seaside village of Cemagi on Bali’s south-west coast this family style villa offers an authentic Balinese experience.&nbsp; Bordered by rice fields on one side and glistening black-sand beaches on the other, and with the sea temple of Pura Gede Luhur Batungaus punctuating the horizon, guests at Maridadi are not only treated to stunning panoramas but also to the most enchanting and exotic of Balinese traditions.&nbsp; It is through observing the rice farmer tending his fields and witnessing the elaborate ceremonial processions at the temple that the true essence of this&nbsp;<em>Island of the Gods&nbsp;</em>is revealed.</p><p>Thoughtfully designed for relaxation and comfort, this spacious and welcoming home mixes traditional architecture and artefacts with easy modern living.&nbsp; Throughout the villa, splashes of vibrant red – in the soft furnishings, the bright parasols and the magnificent flowering heliconias – contrast beautifully against the teak wood furniture and the green of the well manicured lawns.&nbsp; Five large air-conditioned bedrooms with luxurious garden bathrooms provide guests with total peace and privacy; two of them include twin roll-out beds, making the rooms ideal for families.&nbsp; Options for leisure and entertainment are endless with a games room, shared tennis court, 20-metre swimming pool, open-sided living and dining pavilion, massage&nbsp;balé&nbsp;and an adorable thatched rice barn, or&nbsp;lumbung, overlooking the ocean and perfect for sunset cocktails.</p><p>A treasured ingredient of a stay at this villa is the warm and friendly staff.&nbsp; From the attentive butlers to the experienced in-house chef they will gladly attend to your requests with a minimum of fuss, whether it be arranging a spa service or preparing your favourite meal.</p><p>The added beauty of Villa Maridadi is that although you may well choose not to leave this sumptuous oasis, the world famous surf breaks of Echo Beach, the Nirwana Bali Golf Course and an exciting choice of places to eat, drink and shop in up-and-coming Canggu are just a 10-minute drive away, while cosmopolitan Seminyak, with an even greater choice of restaurants and boutiques, can be reached in about half an hour. A complimentary car and driver is available to whisk guests away to al these enticing spots.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks &amp; refreshment towel once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily&nbsp;serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>Free of charge car with driver on standby for up to 8 hours a day (excluding petrol) -&nbsp;extra hours at additional cost.</li>	<li>Free using 3 mountain Bicycles.</li>	<li>Friendly and helpful staffs for children.</li>	<li>A specific request to Chef to prepare and accommodating to tailor meals or any special dietary requirements.</li>	<li>Laundry services (additional cost)</li>	<li>In-house spa treatment &amp; Babysiting on request&nbsp;(additional cost)</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pool: Private swimming pool ( 20m x 5m )</li>	<li>Living areas: 5 air-conditioned bedrooms with en-suite bathroom plus 1 study room;&nbsp;Fully equipped kitchen</li>	<li>Safety deposit box at Bedroom 1, 2, and 3</li>	<li>Families: Baby cot;&nbsp;Baby high chair;&nbsp;Children''s books, games and toys;&nbsp;Children''s videos and DVDs</li>	<li>Entertainment: TV, Satellite TV, DVD Player, and stereo system with CD Player,&nbsp;iPod adaptor on stereo,&nbsp;iPod speakers dock;&nbsp;DVD Library;&nbsp;Board games;&nbsp;Pool Table.</li>	<li>Communications: Telephone landline (local);&nbsp;Wireless Internet connection</li>	<li>Sports: Tennis court (shared with other nearby villas);&nbsp;Tennis Table / Ping Pong Table;&nbsp;Gym equipment (treadmill);&nbsp;Mountain Bike.</li>	<li>Other facilities:&nbsp;Hair dryer;&nbsp;Generator backup during power failures;&nbsp;Pool Deck Chairs;&nbsp;BBQ.</li></ul><p><strong>Detail Descriptions</strong></p><p><strong>Villa Maridadi - Accommodations</strong></p><p><strong>Setting</strong><br />With over 40 meters of private beach frontage Villa Maridadi has the ultimate sunset panorama with views over to the Jimbaran Bukit headland in the south over a Balinese temple set on a large rocky outcrop in the ocean to the Java coastline in the west and the cloudy peaks of Gunung Agung to the north.</p><p>Set on a 4,050 square meters, gently sloping grounds, studded with coconut palms and fragrant frangipani trees, with a crystal clear 20 meter x 5 meter lap swimming pool this home is a wonderful retreat, far from the gaiety of tourist Bali.</p><p>The villa was designed and built by the same International Group who built the Four Seasons Hotel in Bali , and is refreshingly uncomplicated and simple in design with the sympathetic use of traditional Balinese architectural concepts and utilization of the best of local timbers and handcrafted stones and offers you every modern amenity.</p><p><strong>Cuisine</strong><br />The staff have been trained to serve you in comfort and with elegance. Every effort is made to accommodate your dining requests and special dietary needs. The cooks know how to shop for premium quality produce and all meals are provided to you at cost.</p><p>Naturally, Indonesian cuisine is a specialty and we have a wide selection of delicious choices. Western, Vegetarian, Italian and BBQ style meals are also a favourite, and our staff is well used to children and their often simpler menu needs.</p><p><strong>Living and Dining</strong><br />The stunning main 12-meter x 8 meter open living and dining pavilion has been designed for relaxation and entertainment and provides optimum enjoyment of the wonderful ocean, river and unforgettable sunset views. The pavilion with its high natural alang alang grass ceiling, the tall supporting coconut columns and the cool cream terrazzo paved floors is the very essence of tropical living. Overhead ceiling fans and gentle sea breezes keep everyone cool and the ample lounge area seating assures that there is room for everyone to relax. The lounge has a music system with surround sound speakers in the ceiling. The 3 meter antique wood dining table for 12 makes for easy and elegant dining.</p><p>A separate air -conditioned indoor study has a Television unit complete with VCD or DVD and Video systems. A second upstairs casual open living area also has a Television unit with VCD, Video and Play station systems as well as a pool table for your enjoyment.</p><p>The grounds are beautifully grassed and maintained. The wonderful 20 meter long swimming pool is lined with green stone with a white Palimanan stone surround. A swim in the pool, a surf at one of Bali ''s most popular surf beaches, a beach walk, a bike ride up to the village and its surrounds or a quiet fish at the rock pools are all only a matter of steps.</p><p><strong>Bedrooms and Bathrooms</strong><br />The villa has 5 Air-conditioned bedrooms, all with en-suite bathrooms. The villa has been designed with a master and study bedroom bungalow on ground level, two separate guest bungalows and a separate wing with two ground level bedrooms and living area upstairs with glass sliding doors. All the bedrooms have ocean views with large glass sliding doors also with split air conditioning units as well as overhead ceiling fans.</p><p>The bedrooms have custom made oversized king beds with built in wardrobes. Often overlooked in tropical homes, all bedrooms have good quality curtains. The bedroom interiors have been tastefully furnished with a balance of modern rattan and collected antique furniture and artifacts.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Villa manager: responsible for the overall operation of the villa. He leads the staffing team to meet the expectations of guests.</li>	<li>Chef:&nbsp;The villa’s in-house chef is skilled in serving both Western and Asian cuisine.</li>	<li>Driver: drives a car (seating up to six passengers)&nbsp;for eight hours a day (excluding petrol).&nbsp;</li>	<li>Housekeepers: Four members of staff attend to daily housekeeping duties and are also trained waiters/waitresses. Two are on call from 7am to 3pm, and two from 3pm to 11pm.</li>	<li>Gardeners: Three gardeners attend daily to the Maridadi’s lush and well manicured grounds.</li>	<li>Pool attendant: an attendant works three days a week to ensure that the pool is in pristine condition.</li>	<li>Guards: Five security guards provide 24/7 protection with rotating shifts.</li>	<li>Masseuse and babysitter on request</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary airport transfer ( 1 x in &amp; 1 x out ), Free Internet connection, Free use of a car &amp; driver for up to 8 hours / day (exclude petrol)</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 10% VAT and 5.5% service charge</li>	<li>To plan meals with the chef the evening before, to make the most of the kitchen and give staff time to shop.</li>	<li>F &amp; B System : grocery bills at cost.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 3:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 AM</li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after ?6.00 PM</li>	<li>Late check-out subject to availability</li></ul>', NULL, '115.09978730', '-8.63924900', 10, 5, 1, 15, NULL, 5, '2016-09-20 12:36:27', '2016-09-23 13:47:13', NULL),
(60, 1, 'Villa Atas Ombak', 'villa-atas-ombak', 7, 0, '<p>Do you ever crave a vacation destination where you can enjoy a spectacular sunset view, relax on the beach and fully peaceful away from the crowds? Villa Atas Ombak has it all and comes to offer conveniences that every holidaymaker is seeking for. Located in Seminyak area, only 100 meters from the beach, this luxury villa professionally designed with traditional ethnic elements, which give tranquil impression. Despite the quietness is in it, but Villa Atas Ombak is near of Legian, which is favorite’s tourist site with rows of restaurants, shops, boutiques and nightclubs.</p><p>The main building is in the center of large garden and surrounded by palm trees and frangipani trees for striking effect and there is an open living and dining area that can seat up to 12 people. Not far from the sitting room there is the master suite that is air-conditioned and has a queen-sized bed, open bathroom, bathtub and dressing area whereas two other bedrooms are on the other side of the building. While the last two bedrooms are in separate guesthouse situated closer to the beach and equipped with air-conditioners, open-air bathroom and living area. Fully equipped kitchen is modernly designed to allow the guests having fine dining. Right in front of the main building is a big swimming pool that is equipped with bale and pool loungers where you can sunbathe and enjoy cold drinks.</p><p>To meet international standards of luxury yet comfort accommodation, Villa Atas Ombak is facilitated with modern amenities such as TV, VCD / CD / DVD player, internet connection, BBQ equipment, etc. as well as the villa staffs who are always ready to serve all your needs. For more exciting moments, there is spa on request and cars with drivers that is simply organized if you want to explore this beautiful island Bali.</p>', '<div class="intro"><p>Villa Atas Ombak is simply extraordinary: the very essence of Bali has been distilled into a single spectacular beachfront estate on Bali’s south-west coast that captures the hearts of newly-weds as well as the headlines of the world’s best lifestyle magazines.</p><p>As a luxury destination villa and sought-after wedding venue, the five-bedroom Atas Ombak is unrivalled. Could any other villa come close to matching the infusion of island spirit and international standards in such a spell-binding beachfront location? Villa Atas Ombak – literally ‘villa on top of the waves’ – is named after the white-crested waves that crash onto the beach just beyond the immaculate garden. Guests enjoy over 100 metres of direct beach access, and the 14-metre swimming pool is mere steps from the sand.</p><p>Set between the pool and the main villa building is the enchanting, open-sided, alang-alang-thatched living and entertainment space – the villa’s social heart. Across lotus ponds, the two-storey main building houses the dining room, media room, two guest bedrooms and the master suite with its private garden plunge pool. The two ‘Ocean’ bedrooms occupy a delightfully private pavilion to the far side of the grounds, close to the beach. All of the rooms are majestic, elegantly furnished and oriented for those magnificent ocean views.</p><p>And what of the service? Exemplary, of course – the spirit of Atas Ombak is concentrated in the amazing 27-strong staff whose professionalism and training are evident in the balance they achieve between anticipating every whim and otherwise being invisible. Key to the team are the accomplished chefs, who whip up astonishing meals from a suggestion menu, or according to special request, and take care of all the provisioning (on guest account).</p><p>While the celebrated Mosaic and W are only a few minutes’ walk away, and the charms of Seminyak not much further, it’s understandable why so many guests chose not to stray from the sanctuary of Villa Atas Ombak.</p></div>', '<p>Villa Inclusions:</p><ul>	<li>Wifi internet connection<o:p></o:p></li>	<li>Welcome drink and fresh fruit basket upon arrival<o:p></o:p></li>	<li>Turn down setup service<o:p></o:p></li>	<li>Personal service by the villa staff including full time manager, housekeeper, chef, security<o:p></o:p></li>	<li>Exclusive use of the whole villa and listed facilities<o:p></o:p></li>	<li>Return airport transfer (1x in 1x out)<o:p></o:p></li></ul>', '<p><b style="color:#174165">FEATURES AND AMENITIES</b></p><div class="faclitiesheading">Location</div><div class="facdesc">Batubelig, Seminyak, south-west Bali, Indonesia.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Capacity</div><div class="facdesc">10 people in 5 ensuite bedrooms with king-size beds (1 converts to twins).</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Living areas</div><div class="facdesc">Reception hall; large garden living pavilion; air-conditioned TV room; formal dining for 10; informal dining for 10; additional living area in Ocean guest pavilion; garden <span style="font-style: italic;">balé</span>; beachside sundeck.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Pool</div><div class="facdesc">14 x 7 metres; plunge pool by master bedroom.</div><div class="faclitiesheading">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Dining</div><div class="facdesc">A suggestion menu of Balinese, Indonesian, Asian, western and children’s meals; requests accommodated (including special diets).</div><div class="faclitiesheading">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Communication</div><div class="facdesc">WiFi internet access; telephone; mobile phone reception; fax.</div><div class="faclitiesheading">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Entertainment</div><div class="facdesc">Satellite TVs and DVD players in TV room and master bedroom; Bose surround-sound system with remote for living pavilion.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">For families</div><div class="facdesc">Villa Atas Ombak is well equipped for families.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Spa</div><div class="facdesc">Treatments selected from a comprehensive spa menu can be carried out by professional beauty therapists in the privacy of the villa (extra costs apply).</div><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="faclitiesheading">Weddings and events</div><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="facdesc">Events for up to 200 people can be held within the villa’s spacious beachfront grounds.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Additional facilities</div><div class="facdesc">Barbecue; in-room safes; back-up generator.</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="faclitiesheading">Property area</div><div class="facdesc">450sqm (villa); 6,600sqm(land).</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="facdesc">INDOOR LIVING<br />- Large, partially open air dining area with antique 12-seater wooden dining table and ocean views<br />- TV room with plasma screen Satellite TV/ DVD player, sofas and loveseats<br />- Modern kitchen adjoining dining room, equipped to restaurant standard<br />- Spacious, Balinese-style, open-sided pavilion with lounge suite, daybeds and table for four, overlooking the beach<br /><br />OUTDOOR LIVING<br />- Absolute beach frontage<br />- Large marine coloured swimming pool facing directly onto the beach with sun loungers and thatched pool pavilion &nbsp;<br />- One and a half acres of tropical gardens<br />- Three ancient Hindu temples amidst the gardens</div><div class="facdesc">&nbsp;</div><div class="facdesc">MASTER SUITE BEDROOM<br />- Large and luxurious space<br />- King-sized bed<br />- Modern art work adorning the walls<br />- Open air bathroom with sunken tub<br />- Private plunge pool<br />- Air conditioned<br /><br />MAIN HOUSE GUEST BEDROOMS<br />- Two guest bedrooms are situated in the main house, one on the ground floor, one on the first floor<br />- Private terraces<br />- Dressing areas<br />- Open air bathrooms<br />- Air conditioned<br /><br />OCEAN BEDROOMS<br />- Two ocean-facing rooms are situated off to one side of the property<br />- Close to the beach<br />- Air conditioned<br />- Large windows offering panoramic views<br />- Open air bathrooms<br />- Outside lounge areas</div>', '<div class="faclitiesheading">Staff</div><div class="facdesc">Villa manager; assistant manager; cooks and kitchen staff; housekeepers; gardeners; security. Additional staff (eg babysitter, masseuse) available on request.</div>', '<p>Check in time: 14:00pm</p><p>Check out time: 11:00am</p><p>Late check out at additional charge</p><p><strong>Seasons:</strong></p><p>Low seasons: 01 Sep 2016 to 15 Dec 2016</p><p>High seasons: 16 Dec 2016 to 25 Dec 2016</p><p>Peak seasons: 26 Dec 2016 to 02 Jan 2017</p>', NULL, '115.14260330', '-8.67196470', 10, 5, 1, NULL, NULL, 3, '2016-09-20 15:11:36', '2016-09-20 16:10:21', NULL),
(61, 1, 'Villa Canggu', 'villa-canggu', 2, 1, '<p>The spectacular 4-bedroom&nbsp;<strong>Villa Canggu</strong>, complete with 20-metre swimming pool, is located just 50 metres from the beach in the tiny fishing village of Nelayan - literally meaning ''fisherman'' - close to Canggu on Bali''s southwest coast.</p><p>Designed to maximise the natural light, and catch the cool breezes even at the hottest time of year, the property offers a blend of air-conditioned comfort and tropical open-air living. There are numerous relaxation areas, so guests will always find a private spot for peace and quiet. In fact, a large family or group of people could stay at the villa and still lose each other within its depths. In addition to this, guests have the choice of a number of different eating areas, all of which present a unique atmosphere, enhanced by the constant sound of the waves together with wonderful views of the beach and the Indian Ocean.</p>', '<p>Villa Canggu is nestled within the beautiful agricultural belt between Kuta and Tanah Lot, an area that is home to some of the most luxurious private residences on the island. The sweeping beach is renowned for its panoramic coastline views, legendary sunsets, and world-class surf breaks. Fishermen''s huts and colourful ''jukung'' fishing boats line the beach; this is where they sell their catch every morning, ensuring that fresh fish is always readily available for guests staying at the villa.</p><p>Villa Canggu as versatile because it is actually two villas in one: the main four-bedroom Villa Canggu South complete with its 20-metre swimming pool can be rented independently or in conjunction with sister Villa Canggu North, offering two more bedrooms, an additional living and dining area and an second swimming pool.</p><p>The villa is on being family friendly with plenty of facilities for children including a kiddies’ pool.&nbsp; At the same time, we think groups of adult friends will enjoy the sophisticated architecture and décor, relish the luxuriously comfortable and spacious rooms, and be captivated our private collection of artwork, which includes paintings, installations and murals by some renowned Indonesian artists.&nbsp;</p><p>Canggu is a once-sleepy village now fast evolving as the hippest beachside scene in Bali with a great choice of cafés, a few boutiques, spas galore, and activities including a surf school, yoga venues and a dance school.&nbsp; Our villa lies on the borders of Canggu in a quiet, close-to-the-beach location with the inclusive service of a car and driver should you wish to explore further afield.</p><p>The location of Villa Canggu offers easy access up to the mountains and rice terraces on the western slopes of the island; it is one hour from the famous cultural and artistic town of Ubud, and just twenty minutes'' drive from the Sunset Route, gateway to the eastern side of the island. It is also convenient for all of the shopping malls and main tourist attractions. The international airport is thirty minutes'' drive.&nbsp;</p><p>Easily accessible sporting amenities include the ''Canggu Club'', offering a state-of-the art gym, a 25-metre swimming pool and a tennis &amp; squash centre. Guests at Villa Canggu can enjoy complimentary membership of this impressive sports and leisure club for the duration of their stay. The nearby ''Nirwana Bali Golf Course'' was designed by Greg Norman, and was voted the number 1 golf course in Indonesia; it is situated beside the dramatic, waved-lashed sea temple of Tanah Lot. For horse lovers, the ''Umalas Equestrian Centre'' is just a few kilometres away.</p><p>The trendy Seminyak area, with its wide choice of international restaurants - including the famous ''Ku De Ta'', ''Warisan'', ''Living Room'', ''Hu''u'' and ''La Lucciola'' - together with a plethora of chic cocktail bars, exciting nightclubs, lavish spas and elegant boutiques are a mere twenty minutes'' drive away.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers roundtrip.</li>	<li>Welcome drink and chilled towel upon arrival.</li>	<li>Daily serving Breakfast.</li>	<li>Complimentary membership full access to the facilities of the prestigeous "Canggu Club".</li>	<li>Personal chef at Villa Canggu is serving to prepare complimentary&nbsp;daily breakfast, on request lunch and dinner.&nbsp;</li>	<li>The villa’s butlers are on hand to take care of their guests’ every need, included daily housekeeping and domestic chores.</li>	<li>Arranging a seven-seater car and driver is available at US$25 for up to 8 hours a day (excludes petrol).</li>	<li>In villa spa treatments selected from a comprehensive spa menu can be carried out by professional spa therapists (extra cost applies).</li>	<li>Serving weddings and other events for up to 40 people (can be arranged at the villa with prior notice).</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p><ul>	<li>Pools &amp; pool facilities:&nbsp; dominated by a 20 x 5.5 metre lap pool, with a waterfall at one end;&nbsp;a children''s pool fed by water spouts;&nbsp;A timber sun deck, furnished with four sunbeds and two umbrellas;</li>	<li>Living areas: Living and dining room;&nbsp;Master bedroom; The dressing room; guests bedrooms;&nbsp;en-suite terrazzo-floored bathroom;&nbsp;two cushioned chairs and a table;&nbsp;Children''s Bedroom with adjoining babysitter room;&nbsp;kitchen is fully equipped; Rooftop verandah;&nbsp;safe deposit box.&nbsp;</li>	<li>Families: a baby cot, highchair, children’s cutlery and plates, toys and games</li>	<li>Entertainments:Satellite TV; movie hard drive; DVD player; surround; CD player; iPod docks;</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi internet access; landline (local and international calls on guest account); mobile phone coverage.</li>	<li>Extra facilities:&nbsp;table tennis; Barbecue; diesel powered back-up generator.</li>	<li>Area for weddings and events facilities for up to 40 people.</li>	<li>Canggu Club facilities: more information&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cangguclub.com">www.cangguclub.com</a></li></ul>', '<p>The team is headed by a villa manager who will oversee and coordinate the staff and property, and is available to assist guests during their stay. The team also includes an in-house chef, butlers, housekeepers, gardeners, pool attendants and security guards operating on a 24-hour shift basis. The chef is trained in the preparation of both local and international cuisine, and is responsible for all the market shopping, in accordance with the needs and the whims of the guests. The housekeepers fulfill all of the housekeeping duties while also taking care of the daily laundry. Baby-sitting and massage services and the facilities of a car and driver are also available on request at an extra charge.</p>', '<ul>	<li>Rates include of Complimentary full breakfast (2 pax per room), Complimentary airport transfer, Complimentary drinking water, welcome drink and chilled towel upon arrival,&nbsp;Guest have full access to the facilities of the prestigeous Canggu Club for the duration of their stay.</li>	<li>The above rates are subject to a 15% VAT and service charge</li>	<li>Groceries and beverages are charged at cost price plus a 20% handling fee which is subject to service charge and government tax.</li>	<li>Checkin Time : 3:00 PM</li>	<li>Checkout Time : 12:00 Noon.</li>	<li>Latest Check Out Time without additional charge : Until 02:00 PM and&nbsp;<strong>subject to availability</strong></li>	<li>Charge for late check out : Half night''s rental, Until 6.00 PM and full day rate after 6.00 PM</li>	<li>Please note that late check out is subject to availability.</li></ul>', NULL, '115.11254780', '-8.65863440', 12, 6, 2, 10, NULL, 5, '2016-09-20 15:21:33', '2016-09-23 13:57:08', NULL),
(62, 1, 'Villa Wiljoba', 'villa-wiljoba', 2, 0, '<p><strong>Villa Wiljoba</strong> is an elegant 6 + 1 bedroom villa built on classical lines, large enough to comfortably accommodate a family or groups of friends while also offering intimate spaces to relax and entertain. Fully staffed with a professional team, designed with a grown family in mind, Villa Wiljoba whispers quality throughout.</p><p>Built as a private home, no expense has been spared in the construction of this sparkling new villa. Elegant living and dining spaces lead out to a wide terrace with an outdoor bar and dining area, overlooking a sparkling pool and landscaped gardens.</p><p>Just a few minutes walk to one of Canggu’s famous surf beaches, minutes from a host of great cafes and shops, Villa Wiljoba offers lifestyle, luxury and elegance for a discerning guest.</p>', '<p>A short walk to one of Canggu’s famous surf beaches, Pantai Nelayan, Tugu and Echo Beach all provide great waves and chilled bars and restaurants. Glorious beach walks in the morning or at sunset, followed by sundowners, is a favourite activity for guests at Villa Wiljoba. Alternatively, enjoy a stunning sunset on the viewing deck on the third floor of the villa, where another private entertainment area is beautifully situated overlooking the beach.</p><p>Villa Wiljoba is quietly situated in a Balinese village that is within easy distance of some of the area’s best restaurants, shops and tourist icons like Tanah Lot. A car and driver makes the short trip into Batubelig and Seminyak on request, approximately 15 minutes away. Village trips and excursions into Ubud, or the stunning rice terraces of Tegalalang, can be organised by the butler as required.</p><p><strong>Accomodations</strong></p><p>The bedrooms and an indoor entertainment room are located on the upper levels of the villa, offering views across Canggu and to the sea.</p><p>The master suite is a spacious and stylish room, with its own private verandah, features a king-sized bed, a walk in dressing room and en-suite bathroom with a bath and separate shower. Complete with beautiful amenities, the suite offers comfort, privacy and space to relax.</p><p>An adjoining children’s suite offers parents the comfort of knowing their kids are close, while still maintaining separate rooms. Two king single beds, a verandah reached through sliding doors, which can be securely locked, and a separate en-suite bathroom complete the private quarters.</p><p>Two more guest rooms are also located on this level. Luxuriously furnished with king-sized beds and stylish, spacious en-suite bathrooms, the guest rooms also lead out to a private terrace overlooking the pool and gardens, offering sea views and space to relax and enjoy the ocean breeze.</p><p>A family entertainment room on this level offers an air-conditioned play room with a large flat screen TV, comfortable sofas, a pool table, wet bar and guest bathroom. Sliding doors lead out to a small outdoor smoking area and verandah.</p><p><strong>The ultimate lifestyle.</strong></p><p>A large tiled pool is surrounded by sun lounges and overlooked by a large bale surrounded by cushion in vibrant greens. A small children’s pool has been created off the main pool and overlooked from the wet bar and the bale. Landscaped gardens explode with colour and vibrant greens providing the perfect backdrop for effortless entertaining with a compliment of staff to prepare meals to order, drinks and canapés.</p><p>For those who like to keep fit, the villa features a dedicated gym with two state-of-the-art Life Fitness machines overlooking the pool and gardens. Sliding doors can be opened or closed and a flat screen TV is mounted on the wall to allow guests to tune in or tune out.</p><p><strong>Families.</strong></p><p>Travelling with children need not be stressful. At Villa Wijoya kids of all ages are welcome and catered for. With a twin room located off the master suite to keep younger children close to spacious guest suites for older children, the staff will make children welcome and ensure they are entertained.</p><p>Dedicated entertainment areas mean that kids can happily entertain themselves with a range of games and DVDs as well as the pool and gardens. A pool fence can be hired if safety for younger children is an issue and a beautifully landscaped children’s pool is the perfect place for toddlers to get wet and have fun.</p>', '<p><strong>Services</strong></p><ul>	<li>Complimentary airport transfers on arrival and departure.</li>	<li>Welcome drinks and refreshment towel once upon arrival.</li>	<li>Serving daily Breakfast.</li>	<li>Free of charge using a 7-seater car plus&nbsp;driver for up to consecutive 10 hours a day (excluding petrol).</li>	<li>Highly trained, friendly and English speaking staffs.</li>	<li>Chefs is&nbsp;available to cook delicious cuisine from all of the villa’s state-of-the-art gourmet kitchens (Western, Asian, local cuisines &amp;&nbsp;strive to fulfill any special dietary requirements) - on request.</li>	<li>Treatments selected from a comprehensive spa menu by professional beauty therapists in the privacy of the villa (on request &amp;&nbsp;applied&nbsp;cost)</li>	<li>Masseuse and babysitters available on request (extra charge)</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<li>Pools:&nbsp;plunge pool; children pool.</li>	<li>Living areas: open-sided living pavilion; open-sided dining pavilion with table for 14; air-conditioned TV room; games room; poolside balé;&nbsp;safe deposit box.</li>	<li>Communications: WiFi internet access and local telephone calls</li>	<li>Entertainments:&nbsp;Satellite-channel TV; DVD players and DVD library; CD players and CD library; iPod docks; integrated sound system; magazines; book selection;board games and toys</li>	<li>Sports:&nbsp;Pool table; Gym room for fitness</li>	<li>Families: high chairs, baby cots</li>	<li>Other facilities: a car and a van with driver is available upon request, extra cost apply;&nbsp;electricity generator back-up; massage beds; Spa.</li></ul>', '<ul>	<li>Full-time manager:&nbsp;on call 24 hours and is responsible for the overall operation of Villa Wiljoba. Fluent in English and Greek, our villa manager is in charge of staffing, special requests and guest satisfaction. There is no request too big or too small that our villa manager, and dedicated team, cannot handle.</li>	<li>Full-time chef:&nbsp;Our in-house chef has years of experience cooking both Asian and Western meals. He is happy to accommodate any special requests or dietary needs. Dinner parties and other special events can also be catered for.</li>	<li>Butlers &amp; housekeeping:&nbsp;attend daily to all cleaning and tidying requirements at Villa Wiljoba. The same team are skilled waiters/waitresses and will assist the kitchen at mealtimes.</li>	<li>Gardeners and pool attendants:&nbsp;The gardens and pools at Villa Wiljoba are tended daily.</li>	<li>Security:&nbsp;keeps&nbsp;safe and secure 24 hours a day by four trained security staff working rotating shifts.</li>	<li>Babysitting:&nbsp;Professional babysitters are on hand to take care of any younger guests.</li></ul>', '<p><b>Rates, other conditions, checking in and out</b></p><ul>	<li>Rates include airport transfers, daily breakfast, and&nbsp;a 7 seater car + driver for up to consecutive 10 hours a day (excluding petrol).</li>	<li>Food and Beverages during your stay at our service with groceries charged at cost plus 20%</li>	<li>Check-In: 14:00</li>	<li>Check-out:&nbsp;12:00 - 12:30 hours</li>	<li>Cancellation and prepayment policies vary according to room type.</li>	<li>Children of all ages are welcome.</li>	<li>All children under 12 years are charged IDR 450000 per night for extra beds.</li>	<li>All further older children or adults are charged IDR 625000 per night for extra beds.</li>	<li>The maximum number of extra beds in a room is 2.</li>	<li>Any type of extra bed or child''s cot/crib is upon request and needs to be confirmed by management.</li>	<li>Supplements are not calculated automatically in the total costs and will have to be paid for separately during your stay.</li>	<li>Pets are not allowed.</li></ul><p><strong>Seasons</strong></p><ul>	<li>Low season (min 2 nights):&nbsp;9 Jan – 5 Feb, 12 Feb – 24 Mar, 2 Apr – 15 Jun, 1 Sept – 18 Dec</li>	<li>High season (min 3 nights):&nbsp;6 – 11 Feb (Chinese New Year), 25 Mar – 1 Apr (Easter), 16 Jun – 31 Aug</li>	<li>Peak season (min 5 nights): 21&nbsp;December to 08 January</li></ul>', NULL, '115.13174590', '-8.65867120', 12, 6, 2, 9, NULL, 7, '2016-09-20 16:08:56', '2016-09-23 14:04:11', NULL);
